title: microwave ham and noodle casserole
directions: Cook egg noodles according to directions, set aside.
In 1 1/2-quart microproof casserole, combine ham, onions, tarragon and butter.
Cook, covered, on High (max power) 3 minutes.
Add chicken soup, egg noodles, green beans and water.
Stir.
Cook, covered, on High (maximum power) 5 minutes or until hot, stirring once during cooking time.
Top with bread crumbs.
Let stand, covered, 2 to 3 minutes before serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: dorito casserole
directions: Combine soup, Ro-Tel tomatoes, onion and bell pepper.
Heat for about 30 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper to taste.

title: pumpkin pie filling(for 2 pies)
directions: Separate the egg whites from the egg yolks.
Beat the yolks in a large mixing bowl.
Add evaporated milk and beat in; add brown sugar and beat in.
Add white sugar and beat in; add pumpkin, salt, flour and milk and beat in.
Beat whites of eggs until stiff and sprinkle spices on top.
Fold in.
Divide in 2 parts and pour into pie shells.
Bake at 400° for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 325° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: fruit dessert dip
directions: Soften cream cheese and Marshmallow Fluff in microwave if necessary.
Mix together, add a few drops of milk.
Serve with any seasonal fruit pieces of varying colors.
Add toothpicks.

title: cheese meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients lightly.
Shape into meat loaf.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: chi-chi
directions: Mix all the ingredients together in a blender. This is a concentrate; it may be stored in the refrigerator for awhile. When ready to serve, mix 2 jiggers in each glass and then fill the remainder of the glass with Sprite or 7-Up.

title: ham loaf
directions: Combine the above ingredients and shape into a loaf.
Cover bottom of loaf pan with brown sugar and pineapple slices.
Bake in a 350° oven for at least 1 hour.
Invert loaf onto a serving platter.
Serves 8.

title: cathy's spaghetti salad
directions: Cook and drain spaghetti as directed on package.
Add finely chopped vegetables.
Add salad dressing, mixed as directed on package, and salad seasoning.
Chill, overnight is best.

title: sherry chocolate pudding
directions: Combine pudding and milk according to directions.
If to be heated (instant pudding does not require heating), stir sherry in after it has been taken off heat.
Put in sherbet glasses and chill.
Serve with a dollop of whipped cream which has been lightly dusted with cinnamon.
Serve with light cookies.

title: fruit delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in paper cupcake cups. Can be frozen.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Fry your ground beef first, then drain your grease.
Add your taco seasoning and 1/2 cup of water.
In a separate pot, add your enchilada sauce, 1 can green chiles and your can of mushroom soup; boil for 15 minutes.
Put tortilla shells in bottom of casserole dish; add your meat, then your sauce and cheese.
Repeat steps; cover with cheese on top.
Put in oven for 30 minutes.
Serves 5 people.

title: icebox cherry cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk, then add Cool Whip.
Place graham crackers in bottom of an 8 x 13-inch cake pan.
Pour half the pudding mixture over crackers.
Top that with more graham crackers and pour rest of mixture over second layer of crackers.
Top with cherry pie filling.
Refrigerate for at least one hour before serving.

title: baked chicken
directions: Combine egg and water.
Mix potato flakes and dressing.
Dip chicken in egg; roll in potato mixture.
Melt butter in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Place chicken in pan.
Bake at 400° for about 50 minutes.
Turn chicken pieces over once during baking.

title: fruit dip
directions: Mix yogurt, pudding and juice well.
Refrigerate.
Serve with chunks of fresh or canned fruits with toothpicks for dipping (strawberries, grapes, apples, watermelon, cantaloupe and mandarin oranges).

title: devonshire house chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into unbaked pie shell (9 or 10-inch).
Bake 1 hour at 325°.

title: chicken oriental
directions: In a bowl stir first 5 ingredients until smooth; set aside. In skillet, heat 1 tablespoon corn oil over medium-high heat.
Add vegetables and garlic; cook, stirring
rapidly (stir-fry) for 3 to 5 minutes until tender-crisp.
Remove.
Heat remaining 1 tablespoon corn oil in skillet.
Add chicken; stir-fry 4 minutes, until cooked.
Return vegetables.
Stir cornstarch mixture; add to skillet.
Stirring constantly, boil for 1 minute.
If desired, serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Boil and debone chicken, cut up and put in bottom of greased casserole dish.
Bring to boil 2 cups chicken broth and cream of chicken soup.
Pour over chicken.
Mix flour, butter, buttermilk and black pepper.
Spread over chicken mixture and bake at 325 degrees until brown.

title: poppy seed-fruit salad(low-fat)
directions: Combine cornstarch and apple juice in a small saucepan, stirring well.
Bring to a boil over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Reduce heat and simmer 2 minutes or until thickened, stirring constantly.
Pour mixture into a small bowl.
Add dressing, oil and poppy seed; stir well.
Let cool completely.

title: hot german potato salad
directions: Cook potatoes in boiling water.
Peel and dice.
Add vinegar and seasonings.
Fry bacon until crisp.
Cook eggs 4 minutes. Combine potatoes, bacon, bacon fat, soft-cooked eggs and chopped onion.
Mix well.
Serve hot salad on a bed of lettuce with big frankfurters.
Makes 8 servings.

title: cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 425°.
Prepare pastry.
In skillet cook and stir beef until brown.
Drain fat.
Stir in salt, oregano, pepper, crumbs, 1/2 cup of the tomato sauce, onion and green pepper.
Pour into pastry lined pan.
Spread Cheese Topping evenly over filling. Cover edge with 2 to 3 inches of aluminum foil.
Remove foil last 15 minutes of baking.
Bake about 30 minutes.
Cut into wedges. Stir together remaining tomato sauce and chili sauce; heat if desired.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: broccoli slaw
directions: Preheat oven to 425°. Melt 1 tablespoon of butter on cookie sheet. Combine nuts and dry crushed noodles together. Spread on cookie sheet and coat with melted butter. Brown in oven, checking every 2 to 3 minutes. Stir to brown evenly; this will burn easily. Remove when done; cool.

title: apricot chicken
directions: *Can also use packaged or chicken pieces such as breasts or thighs.

title: fan-sliced potatoes(microwave)
directions: Slice each potato in thin fan slices, being careful not to slice through the potato.
Pour melted butter, thyme, chives and parsley on potatoes.
Put in microwave-safe dish and cook on High for 10 minutes.
Let set in microwave for an additional 5 minutes. Place cheese slices on potatoes and cook long enough for cheese to melt.
Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese and salt to taste.

title: cream cheese cake
directions: Cream margarine, butter and cream cheese together until fluffy.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs, alternately with flour, ending with flour.
Add vanilla.
Beat on high for 5 minutes.
Pour into well-greased and floured 10-inch Bundt pan. Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
No peeking until time is up or the cake will fall.
Remove from oven and pan.
Serve warm or cold.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch pan or casserole dish.
Bake at 300° until brown.

title: tostadas
directions: In a small saucepan add a little oil and the onion.
Cook on medium-high.
When the onion begins to turn brown, add the drained beans and mash them.
Keep warm on low.
In a frying pan, heat oil until hot and add a tortilla until it becomes stiff.
Drain tortilla on a paper towel.

title: asparagus casserole
directions: Drain asparagus and reserve juice.
Place in baking dish layer of asparagus, grated cheese, slices of eggs, cracker crumbs, salt, pepper and butter to taste.
Repeat until all ingredients have been used, leaving a layer of cheese on top.
Pour juice and milk over top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: shredded beef barbecue
directions: Cook meat until very tender in small amount of water to which 3 teaspoons have been added.

While meat is cooking, make sauce. Melt shortening and add onion; cook until tender, but not browned. Add remaining ingredients and cook over low heat for 20 minutes. When meat is done, shred it fine.
Add meat and liquid to sauce and mix well.
Cover and cook slowly for 30 minutes.
If necessary, add a little water if mixture becomes thick.
Serve on buns.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: five flavor cake
directions: Spoon glaze over hot cake in pan.
Let set 20 minutes.
Then remove cake upside down, but turn over with glaze on top.

title: creamy tacos
directions: Simmer all until cheese melts.
Cook hamburger and drain.
Add into cheese mixture.
Add 1/2 pint whipping cream.
Stir well. Serve with chips, lettuce, tomatoes, shredded cheese, green onions, picante sauce, guacamole and anything else to give it Mexican taste.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Cream shortening; gradually add sugar and continue creaming until light and fluffy.
Dredge raisins with 1/4 cup of the flour so they will not go to the bottom.
Add well beaten eggs, milk, oats, flour, soda, salt and cinnamon, mixed with raisins.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto buttered pan.
Bake cookies about 10 minutes in a 375° oven.

title: sherried fruit
directions: Combine fruit in a large bowl.
Add sherry and mint, tossing lightly.
Cover and chill at least 2 hours.

title: shrimp quiche
directions: Melt butter in saucepan, stir in oregano, salt, pepper and nutmeg.
Saute shrimp about 2 minutes.
Add vinegar and boil rapidly until most of liquid has evaporated.
Spread shrimp in bottom of pastry shell.
Beat together eggs, milk, tomato paste and hot pepper sauce.
Pour over shrimp.
Spread cheese evenly over top of egg mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, or until knife inserted near center comes out clean.

title: lime pie
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water with lime, lemon juice and Equal.
Refrigerate until it begins to congeal.
Add Cool Whip and whip with mixer.
Refrigerate for a couple of hours.
Yields 8 servings.

title: mexican deviled eggs
directions: Cut the eggs in half lengthwise.
Remove the yolks and set aside the whites.
Press the yolks through a sieve into a bowl. Blend in the cheese, taco sauce and chili powder until well combined.
Refill the egg whites using 1 tablespoon of the yolk mixture for each egg half.
Garnish with olive slices.

title: margaret ann's jello salad
directions: Put pineapple and juice
in
pot
on stove and dissolve jello. Let cool.
Add
buttermilk,
Cool
Whip and nuts.
Mix and put in a pan sprayed with Pam.

title: peanut butter crisscrosses
directions: Thoroughly cream shortening, sugars, and vanilla. Add eggs, beat thoroughly. Stir in peanut butter. Sift dry ingredients; stir in creamed mixture. Form into tiny balls, place on ungreased cookie sheets. Press with back of fork to make crisscrosses. Dough may also be rolled and cut if desired. Bake in moderate oven at 375 for 10 minutes. Makes approximately 8 dozen cookies.

title: cranberry chiffon pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin in hot water.
Combine cranberry sauce, lemon juice and salt in saucepan.

Heat mixture just to the boiling point. Remove and add gelatin, stirring until dissolved. Cool and then chill until it begins to set. Beat egg whites until stiff. Add sugar and beat so standing in peaks.
Fold this and whipped cream into cranberry mixture.
Pour into pie shell. Chill until firm. Serve with dab of whipped cream on each piece.

title: fat-free carrot cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly coat a 9 x 13-inch baking pan with nonstick cooking spray.
Set aside.

title: fresh lemon pie
directions: Use large microwave-safe bowl to prevent mixture from boiling over.
Add sugar and cornstarch to boiling water.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes in microwave, stirring once.
Add hot liquid to egg yolks before adding to full amount of hot liquid.
Cook 1 minute more. Add lemon juice, oleo and small amount of yellow food coloring. Pour into baked pie shell.
Beat egg whites until stiff, adding 6 to 9 tablespoons sugar.
Put on top of pie and bake in slow oven until meringue is browned.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Melt 1/2 stick margarine.
Pour in large casserole dish.
Pour 3/4 cup raw rice in.
Place chicken breasts on rice.
Pour soup mix over chicken.
Pour 2 cups water over soup mix.
Mix chicken soup and 1 can of water and pour over chicken.
Cover and bake 1 1/2 hours at 350°.

title: peaches amaretto
directions: Peel ripe peaches and slice.
Sprinkle peaches with sugar and Amaretto.
Microwave for 2 to 3 minutes.
Serve with whipped cream or over ice cream.

title: taco casserole
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and set aside.
Line bottom and sides of large casserole dish with biscuits (using all but 2 or 3, depending on size of dish).
Do not bake.

title: white decorating icing
directions: Heat eggs and sugar to 150° on candy thermometer in a double boiler.
Then beat until white like a meringue.
In a large mixing bowl, mix sugar and Crisco with pie blender.
Slowly pour egg white mixture into Crisco mixture, beating as you do it.
Add vanilla and whip with mixture.
Stores in refrigerator for months.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Drain salmon, reserving liquid; flake.
Add cold water to reserved liquid to equal 3/4 cup.
Soften gelatin in liquid.
Heat over medium heat until dissolved.
Mix first 7 ingredients well in food processor or blender.
Blend in mayonnaise and half and half until entire mixture is smooth.
Pour into lightly oiled 4-cup mold.
Chill until firm, about 6 to 8 hours.
Unmold onto platter. Garnish as desired.
Serve with crackers.
Garnish with fresh dill and thinly sliced lemon.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken and then remove from broth.
Add spaghetti to broth.
Cook until tender and then drain.
While spaghetti is boiling, saute onion and bell pepper in 1 stick of butter until tender.
Melt cheese in a double boiler.
Add salsa and mushroom soup.
Mix well.
Debone chicken.
Combine all ingredients together in a pot.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix dry ingredients, set aside.
Beat eggs, oil and apples together.
Mix into dry ingredients.
Add nuts and raisins.
Bake in 9 x 12-inch pan in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.
Top with powdered sugar.

title: scalloped potatoes and ham
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter sides of a 10 x 10-inch or 2-quart casserole.
Arrange potatoes in 2 layers, topping with dabs of butter, salt and pepper, mushroom soup and milk mixture (1/2). Cheese and onions may be added to soup mixture (optional).
Top with sliced ham.
Bake 1 1/4 hours.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
While cake is hot, spread 1 can marshmallow cream on top.
Cool.

title: scots crumpets
directions: Beat the egg yolks and blend in the sifted flour, sugar, salt.
Then add in the melted butter and milk to make a thin batter about the consistency of thin cream.
Beat the egg whites to the soft peak stage and quickly add to the batter, folding with a knife or metal spoon.
Heat a lightly greased griddle or frying pan and pour in large spoonfuls of the batter.
Each crumpet should spread thinly to about 4 to 5 inch diameter and you may have to roll the pan to achieve this.
When the batter is brown underneath and slightly bubbly on top, turn and cook on the other side.
Keep warm by stacking on a clean tea towel and eat soon after.
They can be spread with butter and/or jam and rolled up before eating.

title: raisin pudding
directions: Mix flour, baking powder, salt and 2/3 cup sugar.
Add raisins and milk.
Spread batter in buttered baking dish.
Heat together water, butter and 1 cup brown sugar.
Pour the syrup over the batter.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: pima tod
directions: Boil peppers until tender.
Mash pulp/seeds out of skins. Cook tomatoes and peppers in oil on low heat until almost dry. Beat eggs and add to tomato/pepper mixture.
Cook until very dry.

title: pinch cake
directions: Cut biscuits into 4 pieces. Shake pieces in a mixture of 1/2 cup sugar and 3 teaspoons cinnamon. Place in a tube pan. Melt 1 stick margarine; mix in remaining sugar and cinnamon. Pour over cake. Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: mexican stew
directions: Combine all ingredients and cook for 3 hours or until the meat falls apart.
Serve over noodles or rice.
(Sometimes I add 1 small can of sliced mushrooms.)

title: linzer torte
directions: In food processor, separately pulverize almonds and cooked egg yolks; set aside.
Cream together in food processor butter and sugar.
Add pulverized yolks, raw yolks, brandy and lemon juice. Process briefly.
Add flour, baking powder, cinnamon and nuts and process until combined.

title: country tacos
directions: Drain crab meat and shred.
Add cheese, mayonnaise, salt and garlic powder.
Mix well.
Split muffins in half and spread mix on each side.
Place on cookie sheet and put in refrigerator or freezer to firm up.
Take out and cut each half into 6 or 8 pieces (pie shape).
Stack with wax paper between layers.
To serve, heat in toaster oven or broiler 5 or 10 minutes or brown or bubbly hot. Good and makes a lot.

title: potato casserole
directions: Cook potatoes.
When cool, grate or rice.
Mix with soup, sour cream and onions.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well and pour into a baking dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes or until bubbly.

title: lemon curd (butter)
directions: In top of double boiler, combine all ingredients and mix well. Set over boiling water and cook, stirring constantly, with wooden spoon for 15 to 20 minutes or until thick and smooth. Cool and store in refrigerator in a closed jar.
Makes about 2 1/2 cups.
Use for toast, filling for meringues, cakes, sponge rolls or as a dessert pudding and whipped cream.

title: poppy seed chicken
directions: Cook chicken.
Tear into small pieces and place in a greased casserole dish.
Mix sour cream and soup. Pour over chicken.

title: zucchini appetizers
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut in squares and serve.

title: squash casserole
directions: Line
casserole dish with dressing mix, saving some for topping.
Mix
sour cream and chicken soup.
Layer squash over dressing mix and pour mixture of soup and sour cream over all. Sprinkle
with
plenty
of
grated Cheddar cheese.
Cover with remaining
dressing
mix.
Slice butter over top.
Bake slowly at 350° until hot thoroughly, about 20 minutes.

title: cherry cheese pie
directions: Beat cream cheese; mix in Eagle Brand milk and lemon juice. Pour mixture into crust.
Refrigerate 5 to 6 hours.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all together.
Bake 30 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: beef stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet.
Combine all ingredients in a suitable sized pan and add meat.
When browned, cover and stew on medium heat until vegetables are tender.

title: drop sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter, shortening, sugar, vanilla and egg.
Mix in dry ingredients; add milk.
Drop by teaspoon on greased cookie sheet. Wet bottom of glass and dip in sugar.
Press each cookie down with glass.
Wet glass only once, but dip in sugar after pressing each cookie.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until edges are very light brown.

title: pineapple cream squares
directions: Melt the margarine and remove from heat.
Add the sugar and stir until melted.
Stir in the flour until dough forms.
Spread with fingers onto cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: campus special
directions: Fry hamburger, onion and pepper until brown.
Then add the rest of the ingredients.
Heat until hot; serve over hamburger buns.
Sprinkle with cheese.

title: chicken and wild rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Mix chicken, beans, water chestnuts, soup and mayonnaise with cooked wild rice (plain rice may be used). Put into a 3-quart casserole dish or use a 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish. Cook 30 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Serves 10.

title: microwave cone cakes
directions: Prepare your favorite cake recipe or box mix.
Using ice cream cones, fill each with 2 tablespoons of prepared batter.
When cooking more than 2 cones at a time, arrange cones in a circle. Microwave on High (100%) until surface springs back when lightly touched. Always check for doneness at minimum suggested time.
If cones are not done at the same time, remove the baked cones and continue cooking the remaining cones.
Cool, then frost.
Great for school parties!!

title: taco casserole
directions: Unroll crescent rolls and place in bottom of a 9 x 13 cake pan. Mix taco seasoning in with browned hamburger and spread over crescent rolls. Spread sour cream over browned hamburger. Smash taco chips up and place over sour cream. Top with shredded taco cheese. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes or until cheese is melted and slightly brown.

title: old fashion tomato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and put in baking dish.
Sprinkle Parmesan cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cover with foil for half of the time.
Good luck.

title: mother's jello salad
directions: Drain beet juice into cup and fill with hot water.
Put Jell-O into bowl; mix with boiling water.
Add beet juice water to Jell-O.
Add beets and pineapple.
Stir in vinegar.
Pour into mold or flat pan.
If pan is used, cut into squares and serve on lettuce.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid, sugar and water.
Add juice; mix well and chill until ready to serve.
Makes 2 gallons.

title: macaroni salad
directions: Stir and let stand 4 hours.

title: pink punch
directions: Add
boiling
water
to
Jell-O.
Stir until dissolved. Add cold
water
and juices.
Add ginger ale just before serving. Garnish punch bowl with slices of lemon or oranges.
You may use other flavors of Jell-O.

title: layered salad
directions: Layer lettuce, green peas and onion slices into glass salad bowl.
Spread mayonnaise over top, sealing to edge; sprinkle with sugar.
Top with cheese.
Chill, covered with plastic wrap, overnight.
Yield:
12 servings.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into well-greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: crock-pot chicken
directions: Place cleaned chicken in crock-pot. Salt and pepper to taste. Sprinkle paprika on top. Add chicken broth and cream of chicken soup. Place lid on crock-pot and cook all day on low (6 to 8 hours). When cooked to desired tenderness, take chicken out. Pour remaining sauce into a saucepan. Mix the flour with a cup of water until blended. Add to sauce in saucepan to thicken. Mix in slowly with wire whisk. Boil a couple of minutes to desired thickness and serve. Serve over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: boiled custard
directions: Blend together in large container that will fit in a large container of water about halfway up first container. Bring water to boil and stir often. Custard will be a little thick as slides off spoon. Beat with mixer before allowing to cool for smooth custard. Cool and store in glass jug in refrigerator; crimp tinfoil over top and not lid. Avoid plastic jug, as custard sours quickly. Will keep several days in glass.

title: sister's sour cream raisin pie
directions: Cook raisins in small amount of water over low heat for 10 to 15 minutes.
Remove from fire and cover.
Mix together the sugar, cinnamon and flour; add to raisins.
To this, add vanilla and sour cream; mix well.
Pour into prepared baked pie shell.
Chill well before serving.
Top with whipped cream.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake batter according to package directions.
Add 1 cup of coconut and 1 teaspoon coconut flavoring and bake as directed on cake mix.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: frozen fruit salad(goes fast at potluck dinners)
directions: Blend cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add dates, pineapple, cherries and nuts.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into an 8 x 8-inch tray and freeze.
Cut into squares and serve on lettuce leaf.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients together to form sauce.
Use only 1 cup of cheese for sauce.
Save 1/2 cup of cheese to sprinkle on top of casserole.
Starting with the beans, layer half of beans, water chestnuts and sauce in casserole dish.
Then do second layer of beans, water chestnuts and sauce.
Sprinkle remaining cheese over top of casserole.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° until brown and bubbly.

title: meatballs in sauce
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients and shape into 24 meatballs.
Roll in flour.
Brown in hot oil in a large pan.
Add onion and green pepper to meatballs and cook until golden, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well. Bring to a boil; cover tightly, then simmer 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: chicken with sun-dried tomatoes
directions: Season flour and dredge chicken; saute in olive oil until golden brown over medium to medium-low heat.
Take chicken and place on warm serving platter.
Add butter, garlic, shallots and tomatoes to pan.
Saute until golden brown.
Add sherry and broth and bring to a boil to reduce.
Add a small amount of flour to thicken.
Spoon over the chicken and serve.
Wonderful with hot, cooked rice.

title: peaches and cream pie
directions: Mix ingredients. Layer on top of mixture and peaches. Sprinkle with cinnamon and sugar.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: sweet potato casserole i
directions: Drain sweet potatoes and mash. Mix all the ingredients together. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: java salad
directions: Mix together first 4 ingredients and chill, then add the next 5 ingredients and mix well.
Chill in a mold overnight.
Serve with melon wedges or grapefruit sections on a bed of lettuce.

title: oven fried chicken
directions: Melt oleo in a 9 x 13-inch glass pan in a 425° oven.
While the butter is melting, I shake my chicken pieces in a paper bag of flour and seasonings (a little Parmesan cheese is good).
Lay the chicken pieces with skin side down in pans of oleo.
Bake at 425° for 1/2 hour. Turn the pieces over and bake for 1/2 hour more. The best crispy chicken you've ever tasted.

title: haroseth
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Serve immediately or chill for several hours.

title: broiled salmon steaks
directions: Combine oil, lemon rind, lemon juice, garlic, sugar, pepper, salt and oregano.
Grease rack of broiler pan very well.
Lay steaks on it and brush well with oil mixture.
Put 4 inches from heat and broil 5 minutes.
Turn steaks carefully, brush with oil mixture again and continue broiling 2 to 3 minutes or until salmon flakes easily with fork.
Add sliced olives to remaining oil mixture if desired and heat just to boiling point.
Serve over salmon.

title: pea salad
directions: Rinse peas under cold water; do not cook.
Drain.
Mix with celery, onion, olives and bacon bits.
Toss with Caesar salad type dressing with cheese.

title: chocolate chip cheesecake
directions: Mix cream cheese, sugar and vanilla at medium speed until well-blended.
Blend in eggs.
Stir in 1/2 cup chocolate chips. Pour batter into a graham cracker crust pie.
Sprinkle the top with 1/4 cup chocolate chips.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until center is almost set.
Cool.
For best results, refrigerate for 3 hours.

title: busy day chicken bake(4 servings)
directions: Sprinkle dry potatoes over bottom of greased 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Mix salt and cayenne; sprinkle over chicken pieces. Place chicken pieces on potatoes with skin side up.
Blend undiluted soup with remaining ingredients, except olives and paprika.
Pour over chicken and potatoes to cover completely. Sprinkle with sliced olives and paprika.

title: 4-layer delight
directions: Bottom Layer:
Flour, margarine and 1 small package nuts.
Mix flour and margarine with fork.
Add nuts.
Spread on bottom of Pyrex dish and bake 20 to 25 minutes at 325°.

title: herbed zucchini bake
directions: Toss 1/2 cup of the croutons in 2 tablespoons melted oleo; set aside to be used for topping.
Boil squash and drain well.
Saute carrots and onion in oleo.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Spread mixture into an ungreased 9x13-inch baking dish.
Top with crouton topping.
Bake at 350 degrees for 35 minutes or until lightly browned and bubbly.

title: fried shrimp
directions: Beat eggs and milk.
Dip cleaned shrimp in seasoned flour, then in egg and milk, then in the saltines. Fry in deep fat until golden brown. Serve with cocktail sauce.

title: green chili quiche
directions: Cook crust briefly, then put cheese on bottom, then green chilies.
Mix eggs and milk; pour into crust.
Cook at 350° until set.

title: marshmallow dessert
directions: Heat the fruit juices to a boiling point.
Add marshmallows and stir until dissolved.
Chill until partly set.
Fold in whipped cream.
Crush vanilla wafers and line pan.
Add 1/2 fruit juice mixture, then add another layer of vanilla wafers, then the other 1/2 mixture of fruit juice.
Chill until cold and serve cold.

title: bananas foster
directions: Melt butter, stir in sugar, add fruit.
Cook, stir over medium heat about 2 minutes, sprinkle with cinnamon, stir in creme de cacao.
In small pan, heat rum, pour over fruit and ignite.

title: rhubarb cream pie
directions: Cream butter; gradually add flour and water.
Mix well.
Add well-beaten egg, sugar and rhubarb (cut in pieces).
Fill crust. Bake in hot oven for 35 minutes.

title: new pie or fax pie
directions: Toast coconut, almonds and butter together; set aside.
Mix together Cool Whip, cream cheese and milk until smooth.
Pour mixture into crusts.
Sprinkle coconut and almond mixture on top, then drizzle ice cream caramel over top.
Freeze until ready to serve.

title: zeppole(makes 20)
directions: Put everything together and mix.
Use tablespoon to put in oil. Deep fry in oil.

title: cheese cake pie
directions: Whip all ingredients together until smooth.
Pour into a graham cracker crust.
Chill until set.
Top with a can of fruit pie filling.
I use cherry.

title: quick cheddar cheese bread
directions: Combine Bisquick and cheese.
Combine eggs and milk.
Add liquid mixture to cheese mixture.
Stir until well blended.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.

title: ultimate cheese ball
directions: In medium bowl, mix cream cheese, green onions and dried beef.
Form the mixture into a ball, a log or a snowman.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Chill in refrigerator 2 hours before serving.
Serve with buttery, round crackers.

title: chili
directions: Remember to dice onion and garlic.

title: fruit cake(low-cholesterol)
directions: Line a 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan with foil. Coat with cooking spray and set loaf pan aside.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook chicken in salted water.
Remove from bones.
In
a large 13 x 9 x 2 1/2-inch baking dish, pour 1/3 or more stuffing mix in bottom of dish.
Mix soups together.
Pour over stuffing mix. Place chicken over soup mix.
Pour remaining stuffing mix over top.
Pour 2 or more cups chicken broth over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until hot and bubbly.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken; tear into pieces and set aside.
In large skillet, melt butter; add onion and cook until clear.
Add drained mushrooms.
Cook on low approximately 10 minutes.
Slowly add flour.
Stir in chicken stock, then tomatoes and cheese.
Stir until cheese melts.
Stir in chicken pieces and simmer.
Cook spaghetti noodles according to package directions.
Drain.

title: yum-yum salad
directions: Combine pineapple, pie filling and milk.
Then add Cool Whip and pecans.
Pour in 9 x 13-inch Pyrex dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve on lettuce leaf.

title: country-fried potatoes
directions: Heat lard in heavy skillet.
Arrange in skillet a layer of potatoes, then one of onions; repeat.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Saute, covered, over low heat about 15 minutes.
Uncover; increase heat slightly and saute 10 minutes longer or until potatoes are crisp and brown on underside.
Do not stir.
Sprinkle with parsley.
Fold in half like an omelet and serve on a hot platter.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: mom miller's crullers(german doughnuts)
directions: Beat well eggs, sugar and shortening.
Add milk and vanilla; mix.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Stir dry mixture into liquid mixture gradually.
Chill at least 2 hours, overnight if possible.
Roll out on floured surface.
If dough is too sticky, work in more flour.
Roll 1/3-inch thick.
Cut into strips about 2 x 3-inches.
Deep-fry at 375°, turning to brown both sides.
Drain on paper towels.
When cool, dip into bowl of powdered sugar.
Shake off loose sugar.

title: cereal jam squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Blend about half of the cake mix (dry), the butter and sugar.
Stir in remaining cake mix and cereal. Reserve 1 1/2 cups of the mixture; press remaining mixture firmly in ungreased 9 x 13 pan.
Stir preserves with fork to soften; spread over crumbly mixture in pan.
Sprinkle reserved mixture over preserves.
Pat gently into preserves.
Bake 25 to 30 minutes or until light brown.
Cool slightly; run knife around edges to loosen sides.
Cool completely.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares. Makes about 4 dozen squares.

title: microwave lasagna
directions: Will need large microwave-safe casserole dish.

title: chicken divan
directions: Place rice in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Place cooked broccoli on top of rice.
Place chicken pieces, which have been precooked and broken up, on top of broccoli.
Mix mayonnaise, soup, cheese and lemon juice together and spread on top of chicken.
Sprinkle top with seasoned bread crumbs.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes. (Also good made with asparagus.)

title: spanish cream
directions: Let gelatin stand in four tablespoons cold water for ten minutes.
Scald milk and slowly add to yolks of eggs, beaten with salt and pepper.
Cook over hot water until very hot.
The sugar and yolks of eggs will cool the milk.
Stir in gelatin; cook, stirring constantly, until gelatin is dissolved and mixture thickens like boiled custard.
Remove from heat and let cool.
Add vanilla and the whites of eggs, beaten stiff and dry.
Pour into a mold and chill.

title: sara's apple and sweet potato casserole
directions: Place sweet potatoes in buttered baking dish.
Add apples and cover with the marshmallows.
Mix sugar, salt, cinnamon, nutmeg and nuts.
Sprinkle over marshmallows.

title: barbecued pork(twaejibulgogi)
directions: Cut pork into flat, thin pieces.
Score finely; sprinkle with ginger juice and mix well.
Combine soy sauce, salted soused shrimp, sugar, chopped garlic, chopped green onion, sesame salt, sesame oil, black pepper and m.s.g. to make seasoning sauce.
Mix the pork with the seasoning sauce and let stand.
Place seasoned pork pieces on a hot oiled grill and broil, turning often.
Pork tastes best when cooked thoroughly.

title: hot pie crust(makes 2 pie crusts)
directions: Combine boiling water and Crisco shortening in a bowl, stirring until dissolved. Mix flour and salt together; add to shortening and water. Mix and pour out onto a floured surface. Roll out pie crust.

title: vanilla ice cream
directions: Mix sugar and evaporated milk.
Add sweetened condensed milk, vanilla and salt; mixing well.
Add milk to finish filling freezer.
Freeze.

title: four fruit salad(the thickening makes it a whole new dessert!)
directions: Drain pineapple, saving 3/4 cup juice.
In a saucepan, combine sugar and cornstarch.
Add orange, lemon and pineapple juice. Cook over heat until thick and bubbly.
Remove from heat and cool. Pour sauce over fruit and toss.
Makes 12 servings.

title: brownies
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add milk and eggs, one at a time; then add vanilla.
Mix cocoa and flour; add to mixture.
Add nuts and pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan that has been sprayed with Pam. Bake at 375° for about 23 to 25 minutes.

title: homemade granola
directions: Mix oatmeal, shredded coconut, chopped nuts, sesame seed and salt in a large shallow pan.
Mix these ingredients well.
Combine cinnamon, honey, oil (and nutmeg if desired) in a separate bowl. Pour this mixture over oatmeal mixture in shallow pan.
Stir and mix all ingredients well.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes, stirring and turning pan every 5 minutes.
Add and stir in 1 cup raisins when finished baking.

title: jello mold
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in water.
Add enough water (cold) to pineapple juice to make 1 1/3 cups.
Mix remaining ingredients and pour into mold or dish.

title: chunky white chocolate macadamia cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Lightly grease cookie sheet. Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt.

Cream the butter and sugars in a large bowl of electric mixer until light and fluffy. Beat in egg and vanilla. Beat in flour mixture and stir in white chocolate and nuts. Place 1 teaspoon mixture in each mound. Flatten slightly with moistened palm of hand.
Bake 9 to 12 minutes or until lightly browned or golden.
Yields about 2 1/2 dozen.

title: sticks 'n stones
directions: Melt chocolate bits and Karo over double boiler.
Pour over the noodles.
Fold in marshmallows.
Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper on cookie sheet.
Chill for 20 minutes.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: king ranch chicken
directions: Crush chips and spread evenly in a 2-quart casserole dish. Add chicken.
Blend remaining ingredients except cheese.
Pour over chicken.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for about 40 minutes.

title: eggplant casserole
directions: Cook eggplant until very soft, drain. Add all ingredients, reserving 1/2 cup of cheese, 1/2 cup of crumbs and small amount of butter. Mix well. Pour into baking dish, sprinkle with reserved cheese, crumbs and melted butter. Bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Sift together flour, sugar, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Squeeze orange in measuring cup. Add butter to juice and fill with warm water to 3/4 cup.
Add orange rind to above mixture and beat well. Add unbeaten egg and beat well. Add cranberries and nuts.
Pour into greased pans.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Put all lettuce in bottom.
Put next items in order given. Refrigerate 8 to 10 hours before serving.
Do not stir until serving time.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Cook and drain beef. Add onion soup, tomato sauce, water, flour, salt and pepper. Let simmer. Pour into casserole dish. Boil macaroni. Drain and pour over meat. Top with sliced cheese. Heat in oven at 350 long enough to melt cheese.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Cook onion, bell pepper and celery together.
Add 2 tablespoons oil to spaghetti.
Then layer all of this together. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: peachy trifle
directions: Combine pudding mix and milk; beat at low speed until smooth and thickened.
Add cream cheese and yogurt; beat well.
Cover and chill 30 minutes.
Line bottom of glass bowl or trifle bowl with 2 cups of cake cubes.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups mixture over cubes.
Arrange 2/3 cup peaches, 2/3 cup bananas and 1/3 cup kiwi over pudding mixture.
Repeat procedure with remaining ingredients, ending with kiwi.
Cover and chill for 3 hours.
Yields 10 servings.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream sugar, shortening and milk together.
Add remaining ingredients and bake 1 hour at 350°.
Insert straw or tester in middle and if comes out clean, bread is done.
Loaf pan is suggested.

title: tandy cake
directions: Beat eggs until yellow, mix in vanilla, salt, sugar, flour, milk, oleo and baking powder.
Pour over greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: buttermilk pound cake
directions: Cream together butter, shortening and sugar.
Add eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each.
Add milk and vanilla.
Mix flour and soda and add to mixture.
Pour into greased and floured Bundt pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: shrimp foo young
directions: Combine ingredients, cook over low heat until thickened.
Keep warm.

title: nestle toll house white chip chocolate cookies
directions: Combine in a small bowl the flour, baking cocoa, baking soda and salt.
Beat in a large bowl the butter or margarine, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla extract until creamy.
Add eggs to the mixture in the large bowl.
Mix well.
Gradually add the flour mix.
Stir in morsels.
Drop by well rounded teaspoon on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 9 to 11 minutes.

title: strawberry fluff
directions: Crumble angel food cake in bottom of pan.
Dissolve strawberry jello with 1 cup of boiling water and 1 cup of cold water.
Add strawberries.
Pour over crumbled cake.
Let chill.
Make vanilla pudding and pour over cake mixture.
Frost with Cool Whip.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Spread dough on cookie sheet and bake as directed. Cool. In a mixing bowl, beat melted chips and cream. Add cream cheese; beat until smooth. Spread over cookie. Chill 30 minutes.

title: holiday macaroons
directions: Beat eggs until foamy. Gradually add sugar, beating constantly, until thickened and light in color, takes about 5 minutes on electric mixer. Fold in dry ingredients, butter, vanilla and coconut. Mix well. Drop from teaspoon on greased and floured baking sheet. Bake at 325° for 15 minutes until golden brown around edges. Let stand a few seconds on sheet. Remove and cool on bag or rack. Makes 3 dozen.

title: vegetable quesadillas(makes 4 servings)
directions: Cook broccoli for 2 minutes in water.
Set aside and keep warm. In a small saucepan, whisk milk and flour.
Cook over medium heat, stirring frequently, 4 to 5 minutes.
Stir in corn, bell pepper, chilies, salt and red pepper.
Remove from heat.
Stir in cilantro.

title: healthy slaw
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a bowl and set aside. Combine mayonnaise and remaining ingredients.
Add to cabbage mixture, tossing well.
Cover and chill.
Yields 6 servings (61 calories per 1 cup serving).

title: pretzel recipe
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water and transfer to a mixing bowl. Add salt, sugar and gradual amounts of flour to form dough.
Knead dough until smooth.
Cut into small pieces, roll into ropes. Twist ropes into pretzel shapes and place on lightly greased cookie sheets.
Brush pretzels with a beaten egg and sprinkle coarse salt on top.
Bake in 425° oven for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: microwave fudge
directions: Microwave chocolate chips and Eagle Brand milk for 2 minutes. Stir until smooth.
Add nuts, sugar and vanilla.
Stir.
Pour into 8-inch greased pan.
Refrigerate 1 1/2 hours, then can be cut into squares.

title: salsa de queso(chili and cheese dip)
directions: Saute peppers and onion in butter until soft, about 4 minutes. Mash tomatoes; add to pan with juice.
Heat to simmering.
Add cheese spread; heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts.
Add grated cheeses; heat, stirring constantly, until cheese melts. Serve hot with tortilla chips.

title: apple pie
directions: Roll out pastry for 10-inch pie shell.
Combine apples, sugar, flour, cinnamon, nutmeg and lemon juice.
Pour in pastry shell. Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: hot buttered rum
directions: Mix all ingredients until well blended.
Freeze.
Scoop about 2 tablespoons into mug.
Add hot water and rum (optional).
Makes about 4 cups mix.

title: plum pudding cake
directions: Mix sugar, oil, eggs, baby food, red coloring and vanilla. Add other ingredients.
Mix well and beat on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into well-greased tube or Bundt pan.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.
Good and easy!

title: picnic casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In an ungreased 2-quart casserole, toss potatoes, Crisco and onion.
In a medium bowl, mix frankfurters, soup, peas, milk and mustard.
Pour over potato mixture.
Bake for 40 minutes longer or until cheese melts.
Yields:
6 to 8 servings.

title: easy chile con queso dip
directions: Cube cheese and heat with chili until cheese is melted. Add taco sauce and heat again. This thickens as it cools, so keep warm in a chafing dish or crock-pot. Makes 1 quart. Serve with tortilla chips.

title: beef barbecue
directions: Cook beef in slow cooker about 8 hours with 1 cup of water on high.
Drain 1/2 of liquid into bowl and save for later if consistency is not soupy enough.

title: spareribs "aloha"
directions: Put ribs in shallow pan; sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Bake 1 1/4 hours at 350°.
Pour off fat.

title: sausage balls
directions: Melt cheese in double boiler; add raw sausage.
Mix well.
Add Bisquick and pepper.
Roll into balls.
Bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Boil chicken, onion, celery and salt in water until chicken is tender.
Remove chicken from broth and cool.
Remove bones and cut into chunks. Boil broth down to 1 1/2 cups.
Add soups.
Preheat oven to 350°.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Bake cake according to 9 x 13-inch directions.
Mix instant pudding as directed.
Add 1 container Cool Whip to pudding. Crumble 1/3 of cake in punch bowl.
Combine strawberries, bananas and crushed pineapple.
Add layer pudding, then fruit.
Layer twice more with cake, pudding and fruit.
Top with Cool Whip, sealing edges.
Refrigerate several hours.

title: italian meatball sandwich
directions: Mix thoroughly beef, crumbs, egg, onion and salt.
Shape into 24 meatballs.
Brown meatballs in skillet.
Pour off fat.
Add soup, water and oregano.
Cover.
Cook on low for 20 minutes or until done.
Serve in rolls.
Sprinkle with shredded cheese, if desired.

title: kolouria(greek butter cookies)
directions: Mix butter with sugar until well creamed.
Add eggs and beat. Add vanilla and baking powder.
Add flour 1/2 cup at a time until dough is to a consistency where you can roll it out in your hands. It should not stick to your hands nor should it crumble.
Roll into half moon or circle shapes.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet. Brush with egg and sprinkle with sesame seed.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 25 cookies.

title: sausage stir-fry
directions: Brown sausage in skillet.
Remove and drain.
In same pan, cook vegetables until tender.
Add sausage and cashew nuts.
Cook 2 minutes until warm.
Serve over rice.
Serves 6.

title: broccoli and corn casserole
directions: Melt oleo and mix with 1 1/2 cups crushed Ritz cracker crumbs (save half for topping).
Put rest of ingredients in shallow buttered dish and top with remaining cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mary's flour tortillas
directions: Mix flour, salt and baking powder into Crisco.
Cream until like meal. Add very hot water, as hot as you can stand to work with.
Mix with your fingers until all flour is mixed.
Roll into ball and let rest 10 minutes. Separate into 10 to 12 small balls and roll into tortilla shape, about 6 to 7-inches across. Be careful not to work in too much flour.
Cook on ungreased iron skillet.

title: big dipper shrimp
directions: Beat cheese until smooth.
Stir in milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate 4 or more hours.
Serve in hollowed out round bread, or a serving bowl, and dip with vegetables and/or crackers.

title: cheese cookies
directions: Blend the grated cheese and butter.
Add other ingredients in the order given.
Drop from spoon small, bite size pieces of dough, which is stiff.
Bake for 20 minutes at 325°.
They may be made ahead and frozen.
Thaw at room temperature and serve.

title: choice fruit pizza dessert
directions: Cut cookie dough into slices and press together in pizza pan. Bake for 10 to 13 minutes at 350° in a preheated oven.
Cool completely.

title: venison pepper steak
directions: Grind peppercorns in a pepper mill or crush them in a paper bag with a rolling pin or hammer.
Rub the steaks with butter or margarine and sprinkle each liberally with crushed peppercorns. Rub the pepper in with a knife and let stand at room temperature for 1 hour.
Sear the steaks in very hot butter or margarine in a skillet for about 1 minute on each side.
Remove to a hot platter. Pour the beef broth, cream and brandy into the pan and stir over high heat for 3 minutes.
Pour this over the steaks.

title: morrocan chicken
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Dredge chicken parts in mixture until covered.
Heat vegetable oil in a skillet over high heat. Brown chicken in hot oil.
Reduce heat and transfer chicken to a casserole or baking dish.
Add chopped onion and garlic; cook about 4 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, lemon, cumin, ginger and a dash of pepper.
Bring to boil and spoon over chicken.
Arrange tomato wedges around chicken.
Cover dish tightly with lid or foil.
Bake 50 minutes at 375°.
Remove lemon before serving. Garnish with parsley and black olives.
Serve with rice.
Serves 10.

title: microwave no-fail fudge
directions: In large mixing bowl, combine sugar, butter and evaporated milk.
Cook, uncovered, in microwave, 8 minutes on High, stirring occasionally.
Stir in chocolate until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla; mix well.
Pour into greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cool and cut into squares.

title: parmesan chicken breasts
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Spray a 15 x 10 x 1-inch pan with cooking spray.
Mix together the margarine, Parmesan cheese, crumbs and seasonings.
Coat chicken breasts in mixture and place in baking dish.
Sprinkle any remaining coating mix over top of chicken. Bake for 20 to 25 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: cheeseburger casserole
directions: Fry
hamburger
and onion.
Drain.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add
ketchup and tomato sauce.
Pour into baking dish. Grate
cheese
on top of mixture (or use slices).
Put biscuits on top
of
cheese.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: persimmon cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening; beat egg and add to pulp mixture.
Then add to sugar mixture.
Into flour, add spices, nuts and raisins.
Blend into sugar mixture.
Drop onto greased cookie sheets by teaspoon and bake at 350° for about 8 minutes or until golden brown.

title: banana split dessert
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, butter and sugar.
Press in a 9 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch pan.
Bake for 5 minutes at 350°, then cool.
Drain pineapple and save juice.
Blend cheese, sugar and 1/2 cup juice. Spread on cooled crumbs.
Slice bananas over mixture, then drained pineapple.
On top put Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries. Chill about 2 hours.

title: golden punch
directions: Mix all ingredients in large punch bowl.

title: chicken newburg
directions: Combine all ingredients, except pastry shells, and heat thoroughly until simmering.
Serve over Pepperidge Farm pastry shells with tops removed.

title: stuffed manicotti
directions: Cook shells according to directions.
Mix remaining ingredients together, except spaghetti sauce.
Stuff cooled shells.
Place stuffed shells in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish. Pour your favorite spaghetti sauce over shells.
Heat oven to 350°.
Bake for about 45 minutes to an hour.

title: veggie squares
directions: Stretch crescent roll dough into cookie sheet.
Bake 10 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Hidden Valley; spread on crust.
Sprinkle vegetables over in layers.
Sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: taco platter dip
directions: Mix cream cheese and French onion dip until spreadable and spread in a large round dish.
Pour taco sauce over and top with shredded lettuce, tomatoes and shredded Mozzarella cheese.
Serve with taco chips.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix all together and form a ball.
Roll in crushed croutons or nuts.

title: venison skillet supper
directions: Cut steak into bite size pieces.
Season with your favorite seasonings.
Roll in flour and set aside.
In iron skillet, melt the margarine.
Saute the onion and bell pepper.
Add steak pieces and chopped drained mushrooms.
Stir to brown steak until tender. Do not overcook (5 to 8 minutes).

title: easy peanut candy
directions: Break vanilla bark into squares and place in a medium glass bowl. Melt in microwave for 1 1/2 minutes. When melted, stir in peanut butter and microwave for 1 minute. Stir until creamy and blend in Rice Krispies, peanuts and marshmallows. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper.

title: strawberry bread
directions: Combine flour, soda, salt, sugar and cinnamon; mix well. Combine eggs, oil and berries; add to dry mixture.
Mix well with electric mixer.
Pour into 2 greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour, or until tests done.
Keep cool.

title: iced slush
directions: Boil water with tea bags.
Dissolve remaining ingredients in tea and water.
Place in large container with lid and freeze for 2 days prior to serving.
While mixture is freezing, stir twice a day.
Serve in 8-ounce rocks glasses with cherry and orange slices.

title: crock-pot macaroni and cheese
directions: Mix first 8 ingredients together.
Put into greased crock-pot.
Place sliced cheese on top.
Cook for 3 hours and 20 minutes on low.
Don't open lid while cooking!

title: flavorful catfish fillets
directions: In a shallow bowl, whisk buttermilk and mustard until smooth. In another bowl, combine the cornmeal and seasonings.
Dip fillets into buttermilk mixture, then into cornmeal mixture place 1 in apart on a wire rack coated with non stick cooking spray.
Place rack on a baking sheet.
Broil 4 in from the heat for 3 to 4 minutes on each side or until fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve with lemon if desired.
Yield 4 servings.

title: round steak roll-ups
directions: Spread mustard over all steak, cover with onion slices and mushrooms.
Sprinkle garlic salt, pepper and dried onion.
Roll up into meat roll and tie with meat string.
Bake at 350° until done to your taste.
Slice into pinwheels to serve.

title: english pea salad
directions: Mix thoroughly and refrigerate before serving.

title: chocolate chip pie
directions: Combine margarine, sugar and vanilla in large mixing bowl; beat well.
Add eggs, one at a time; beat well.
Stir in flour. Gradually stir in chips, pecans and coconut.
Pour into 2 deep dish pie shells.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: orange-banana shake or frosty
directions: Combine ingredients, except ice; blend.
Add the crushed ice to thicken.
Serves 6.

title: orange kiss me cake
directions: Grind together orange, raisins and walnuts.
Set aside.
Sift together flour, salt, soda and sugar.
To flour mixture, add shortening and 3/4 cup milk.
Beat for 2 minutes.
Add eggs and 1/4 cup milk.
Fold in raisin mixture.
Bake in greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Drip orange juice over warm cake.
Combine 1/3 cup sugar, cinnamon and 1/4 cup chopped nuts and sprinkle on cake.

title: mary shelly's zucchini nut bread(breakfast bread)
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, oil, zucchini and vanilla; stir.
Add flour, salt, baking soda, baking powder and cinnamon.
Stir until blended, then add nuts and raisins.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour in an ungreased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Makes 2 loaves.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Stir until all ingredients are combined.
Place in greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° about 35 minutes.

title: franks and bacon
directions: Fill each frankfurter with cheese strip.
Place on bacon strip and wrap bacon around frankfurter, securing with a toothpick. Place on ungreased cookie sheet, cheese side up.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes, or until bacon is done.

title: hot o.j. sipper
directions: Bring water to a
boil.
Add sugar, cloves, cinnamon and tea to water and mix.
Remove from heat and add orange juice.
Mix thoroughly and serve hot.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Combine beef with all ingredients. Shape into balls the size of hickory nut or a little larger and arrange in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Boil chicken.
Season with salt, pepper and garlic powder. Cook spaghetti and drain.
Cut Velveeta cheese into chunks.
Stir into spaghetti.
Drain can of Ro-Tel.
Put with spaghetti mixture and add cream of mushroom soup.
Cut chicken breasts into pieces and add to other mixture.
Place in a casserole dish and top with cup of finely chopped mild Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 350° until cheese melts.

title: chicken in french cream sauce
directions: Season chicken breasts with salt and pepper; melt butter in heavy skillet and brown chicken pieces on all sides quickly. Remove to warm platter.
Add garlic, shallots and mushrooms to butter in skillet and cook for 3 minutes.
Sprinkle with flour and cook 2 minutes, stirring constantly.
Blend in chicken broth slowly.
Add herbs and bring to a boil, stirring to scrape all of the cooked-on particles into the sauce.
Simmer 5 minutes.
Return chicken to pan and cook until tender (approximately 8 minutes). Place chicken on warm dish.
Add cream to liquid in pan and simmer 3 minutes; do not boil.
Season to taste and pour sauce over chicken.
Serve with rice or noodles.
Serves 6.

title: apple-pineapple salad
directions: In medium saucepan, mix pineapple, flour, sugar, and salt. Cook until thick.
Add margarine and cool.
Add chopped apples. Pour into serving dish and chill.
Top with whipped topping and nuts.

title: robby's barbeque sauce
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Use as a marinade.

title: spareribs
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except ribs, together. Pour over ribs. (if ribs are in a rack, cut all apart). Marinate 4 hours. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Brown hamburger; cook with onions and green pepper.
Cook noodles.
Mix ingredients except cheese.
Put in a 9 x 13-inch cake pan; top with cheeses.
Bake 20 minutes at 350°.

title: westport room salad
directions: Blend all ingredients together except cauliflower, lettuce and spinach.
Refrigerate for at least 1 hour.
Grate half a head of cauliflower and refrigerate, covered.
Pour dressing over bite size pieces of lettuce and spinach.
Sprinkle grated cauliflower over top and toss.
Top with stuffing cubes.

title: lucy's recipe (hamburger)
directions: Brown hamburger. Add all ingredients, plus some butter, salt and black pepper to taste. Simmer as long as you like. Just before serving, add cooked noodles.

title: mexi chili casserole
directions: Brown meat.
Add beans, both sauces, onions and 1 1/2 cups cheese and 1 cup chips.
Mix well and pour into 2-quart casserole dish.
Bake uncovered 20 to 25 minutes at 350°.
Spread sour cream on top and sprinkle rest of cheese on top.
Bake 3 to 4 minutes longer.
Serve over a handful of corn chips.

title: beef corn stew
directions: In large skillet, brown hamburger and onions; drain off fat. Add diced potatoes, cream-style corn, beef broth, salt and pepper. Mix well.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 to 25 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Makes 4 servings.

title: banana pudding
directions: Beat pudding and milk until thick and smooth.
Add sour cream, Cool Whip, bananas and vanilla wafers.
Put in deep baking dish.

title: oven roasted sweet potatoes
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Cut the sweet potatoes into spears about 1-inch long and 1/2-inch wide.
Put the sweet potatoes in a bag or container and toss with the oil, salt and pepper.
Place potatoes on a baking sheet and bake, turning occasionally, until the sweet potatoes are tender and golden brown, 40 to 45 minutes.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onion in margarine.
Add the broccoli and cooked rice.
Add mushroom soup and milk; mix well and put into greased casserole dish.
Pat toasted almonds or shredded cheese on top.
Bake in 350° oven 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 4 to 5.

title: peanut butter krispie treats
directions: Boil brown sugar and Karo; remove from heat.
Add peanut butter and vanilla; mix until blended.
Slowly add Rice Krispies; stir until well mixed.
Drop by spoonfuls onto waxed paper; allow to cool.

title: divine coconut cake
directions: In a 9 x 13-inch pan, bake cake mix according to directions on box.
While cake is baking, mix sugar and pineapple and boil for four minutes.
Puncture warm cake with fork and pour warm pineapple mixture over cake.
Let cake cool.
Mix pudding according to directions on box.
Pour over cake.
Top with whipped topping; sprinkle with coconut, chopped nuts and maraschino cherries.
Refrigerate.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Grease an 8 x 8-inch dish.
Drain pineapple and put on bottom. Mix sugar and flour; sprinkle over pineapple.
Mix cheese and crackers; put on top.
Pour margarine over crackers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: party biscuits
directions: Prepare sauce by melting margarine in saucepan.
Add mustard, poppy seed and 1 finely chopped onion.
Mix well and place in refrigerator overnight.

title: shrimp bisque
directions: Melt 2 tablespoons of the butter in large saucepan.
Saute carrots and onion until tender; add bay leaf, thyme, wine and shrimp.
Cook just until shrimp turn pink, about 30 minutes.
Drain shrimp into a bowl, reserving liquid.
Melt remaining 6 tablespoons butter in same saucepan; stir in flour.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Add reserved shrimp liquid to saucepan along with salt, paprika and milk, stirring constantly until thickens.
Chop shrimp and add to bisque.

title: baked cream potatoes
directions: Mix sour cream, milk, minced onion, parsley, salt and pepper together.
Put half of the potatoes in greased baking dish. Add half the sauce and rest of the potatoes.
Cover with remaining sauce.
Put cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: pizzella
directions: Add enough flour to make soft batter.
Bake in pizella iron.

title: black-eyed pea casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Garnish with crisp bacon bits, if desired.

title: hawaiian banana nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix flour, sugar, pecans, baking soda, salt and cinnamon together in large bowl; set aside.
Combine eggs, bananas, oil, pineapple and vanilla in medium bowl.
Stir by hand into reserved flour mixture until flour is just moistened. Grease 1 (9 x 5 x 3-inch) loaf pan.
Turn batter into pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool in pan for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.
Cool on rack.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: ice cream sandwich dessert
directions: Place 6 sandwiches on the bottom of a freezer safe casserole dish.
Smother about half of cool whip on top.
Drizzle about half of the jar of hot fudge sauce on top of cool whip and sprinkle with 1/4 cup pecans.
Repeat these steps for the second layer. Freeze for about 2 hours.
Let sit out for 20 minutes before cutting.

title: foil wrapped dinners
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Cut beef into 1-inch cubes.
Rinse frozen peas to separate.
Drain.
Tear off 4 pieces heavy-duty aluminum foil, each 18 x 15-inches.
On center of each piece, place 1 carrot (thinly sliced), 1 potato (cut into fourths) and 1/4 of the beef. Mix mushroom soup and onion soup mix.
Spoon mixture over beef and top with peas or corn.
Wrap securely in foil.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake until beef is tender, about 50 minutes.
Makes 4 servings.

title: zucchini with walnuts
directions: Wash the zucchini and cut off ends.
Cut into 1/2-inch slices. Heat oil in skillet and saute zucchini and green onions for 5 minutes, stirring frequently.
Pour in wine, lemon juice and water. Simmer for 5 minutes longer. Gently but thoroughly stir in walnuts. Transfer to serving dish and serve hot.

title: whiskey sours
directions: Blend together and add 2 teaspoons powdered sugar and blend again.

title: zola's cornbread
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: savory stuffed mushrooms
directions: Preheat oven to 400°. Twist off stems from mushrooms. Spray in large shallow pan with nonstick cooking spray. Arrange mushrooms, rounded side up, in pan. Spray lightly with cooking spray. Sprinkle with salt and pepper. Cook in oven for 8 minutes and remove.

title: fruit and nut bread
directions: Sift flour with baking powder, soda and salt.
Cream shortening and sugar.
Add eggs and beat.
Add fruit and mix well. Put into greased tins and bake at 350°.

title: coffee bars
directions: Mix well with mixer.
Spread into cookie sheet.
Sprinkle 6 ounce or 12 ounce package of chocolate chips.
Nuts are optional. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: tortilla chip dip
directions: Brown meats and drain.
Add tomatoes and cubed cheese.
Heat until cheese melts.
Serve warm with chips.

title: "almond roca"
directions: Bring butter and sugar to 300° (medium-hard crab stage).
Mix almonds and chocolate morsels.
Put half of almond and chocolate mixture on cookie sheet.
Pour sugar mixture on, then finish with remaining almonds and chocolate.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package; drain and set aside.
Add margarine, cheese and lemon juice.
Mix well and put in buttered casserole dish.
Spread cracker crumbs over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: snowballs
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add beaten egg yolks, pineapple and nuts.
Fold in beaten egg whites.
Spread mixture on cookies and stack 3 high.
Put in refrigerator for at least 4 hours.
Cover with whipped cream, seasoned with sugar and vanilla.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Can be done 4 to 5 hours before serving.
Looks pretty served on paper doilies.
Makes a festive Christmas dessert with a candle.

title: refrigerator rolls
directions: Measure all ingredients.
Thoroughly mix undissolved yeast with 1/3 of the flour and all ingredients. Heat margarine and water until very warm and add to dry ingredients.
Beat for 2 minutes at medium speed, scraping bowl occasionally.
Add remaining ingredients and egg.
Beat on high speed for 2 minutes. Spoon into greased muffin pans. Bake at 375° for 20 minutes. Mixture may be kept in refrigerator for several days.

title: chicken and dressing surprise
directions: Remove skin and bones from chicken and cut into small size pieces.
Butter bottom of glass baking dish, 9 x 13-inch.
Place chicken pieces on bottom.
Place cheese slices over chicken.
Mix together the 2 soups with whip.
(Do not add any liquid.)
Spread soup mixture over cheese.
Sprinkle whole canister of dressing mix over soup.
Dot with margarine.
Cover with foil.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes; remove foil and bake another 5 to 10 minutes.

title: butterscotch-oatmeal cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt and soda.
Cream butter, sugars and eggs, creaming well.
Blend dry ingredients gradually to butter mixture.
Stir in rolled oats and chopped nuts.
Chill 1 hour. Divide dough in half.
Shape into rolls 1 1/2-inch in diameter. Wrap in foil and chill 2 hours to overnight.
Cut into slices about 1/4-inch thick and place on greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool on cake rack.
Makes 6 to 8 dozen.

title: noodles alfredo
directions: Melt butter and 3/4 cup cheese with heavy cream over low heat. Add pepper and salt.
Stir until cheese is melted and smooth. Cook noodles according to directions.
Pour sauce over noodles. Top with remaining 1/4 cup cheese.
Sprinkle with parsley.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Mix butter, baking soda and vanilla.
Set aside.

title: beets polynesian
directions: Combine brown sugar, flour and salt in saucepan.
Stir in vinegar and water.
Add pineapple, raisins and oleo.
Cook, stirring constantly, until bubbly.
Add beets and heat.

title: easy pork marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Marinade meat for 24 hours before grilling.
Baste with any remaining marinade.
Recipe will marinade 4 pork chops.

title: shrimp casserole
directions: Saute green pepper, onions and celery in butter.
Add catsup, sugar and Worcestershire sauce.
Cook slowly over low heat for 10 minutes. Add shrimp and simmer 10 minutes.
Serve over Minute rice.

title: lime chiffon salad
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Add reserved juice; cool until slightly thickened.
Beat until frothy.
Fold in pineapple, cottage cheese, mayonnaise and nuts.
Place in a 13 x 9-inch pan or mold.
Refrigerate until firm.
Serve on lettuce or other crisp salad greens.
Makes 7 servings.

title: shrimp scampi 1
directions: Melt butter in pan or wok.
Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are pink.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.

title: no fuss peanut butter fudge
directions: Butter an 8 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan or small rectangular pan. In a 2-quart saucepan, mix brown sugar, evaporated milk and salt. Stir over low heat.
Bring to a boil; boil for 3 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Stir in chocolate chips, peanut butter and vanilla until chips are melted and mixture is smooth.
Pour into baking pan.
Refrigerate at least 4 hours, or until firm.
Cut into small squares.

title: bishop's court bread
directions: Beat eggs; add
sugar,
salt,
oil,
cinnamon,
nutmeg, pumpkin, water, soda and flour.
Bake in 325° oven for 1 hour. Makes 4 small loaves.

title: russian creme
directions: Thoroughly mix
gelatin with sugar.
Add water and stir until sugar
and
gelatin
are
completely dissolved.
Stir in heavy cream.
Chill
until
slightly
thickened (35 minutes). Add sour cream and vanilla.
Blend with rotary beater and add fruit.
Beat until bubbly.
Pour into 1 quart bowl or individual molds.
Chill until set.
Unmold on plate and garnish.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Brown beef; add salsa.
Layer tortillas in round casserole dish, then beef, sour cream and cheese.
Repeat twice.
Bake for 30 minutes.

title: hot cheesy rice
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
(This prevents cheese from sticking.) Mix all ingredients, except rice, in large pan or skillet on top of stove.
Heat, stirring until cheese melts.
Add rice and simmer, uncovered, for about 25 to 30 minutes.
Stir often.
Great with barbecue.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: welsh cookies
directions: Mix flour, baking soda, baking powder, seasonings and currants.
Cut in shortening and margarine.
Add sugar, eggs and milk.
Roll out to 1/4 inch thickness; cut with round cookie cutter and drop on medium degree griddle or grill.
When one side of cookie is light brown, turn like pancake and brown other side.

title: creamy salsa dip
directions: Combine sour cream, salsa and salad dressing.
Mix well. Cover and chill at least 1 hour.
Serve with tortilla chips and raw vegetables.
Makes 2 cups.

title: eggs ahead
directions: Beat together the eggs and milk.
Tear bread and cook sausage and drain.
Layer bread, sausage, shredded cheese and beaten eggs. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Bake 35 minutes, covered.
Remove foil for the last 10 minutes to brown it.

title: mocha dessert
directions: Prepare pudding according to package.
Divide into 2 bowls.
To one bowl, add instant coffee and chocolate pieces to other bowl. Stir to dissolve.
Spoon into sherbet dishes alternating.
Garnish with coconut.
Chill well before serving.
Serves 4.

title: chili sauce(spicy)
directions: Grind all vegetables, use all juice.
Mix all ingredients together; boil for 2 hours.
Put in sterilized jars and seal.

title: dill dip
directions: Mix together and chill.
Serve with vegetables.

title: quick and easy nacho dip
directions: Spread refried beans in shallow glass dish.
Mix sour cream and taco seasoning.
Spread over beans and top with Cheddar cheese, chopped tomatoes and black olives.	Serve with tortilla chips.

title: mexican fruit cake
directions: Put into bowl; mix and pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: spam corn chowder
directions: Saute onions and pepper in oleo until golden.
Add potatoes, cook and stir 2 minutes.
Add corn and milk, bring to a boil. Reduce heat, simmer 15 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring occasionally.
Stir in Spam.
Simmer 2 minutes.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: "that dish"
directions: Cook meat, draining off liquid; add onions, peppers, chilli powder and saute. Then add all other ingredients. Bake in casserole dish at 350° until bubbly.

title: bacon cheese dip
directions: Mix together and form a ball or use as dip.

title: barbecue spareribs
directions: In large bowl, combine soup mix, water, honey, soy sauce, sherry, sugar, garlic and ginger.
Add ribs; marinate 2 hours. Turn frequently.
Preheat oven to 350°.
Place ribs on rack in shallow roaster pan.
Roast 1 1/4 hours, or until tender and crisp.
(Turn and baste occasionally with marinade.)

title: curry dip for vegetables
directions: Mix ingredients together and serve with assorted vegetables.

title: shrimp over rice
directions: Cream together the first six ingredients and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Cook the rice in the chicken broth with 3 tablespoons of butter and 1 1/2 cup minced onion.

title: chicken in wine
directions: Salt and pepper chicken; mix wine and spices.
Add chicken and marinate at room temperature for 1 hour turning occasionally in baking dish.
Sprinkle with cheese and paprika.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: norwegian pie
directions: Mix sugar, flour and eggs.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Pour into well-buttered pie pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve plain or with whipped cream.

title: sausage and vegetable soup
directions: Combine vegetables, cabbage and water in Dutch oven.
Cover tightly after it reaches a boil.
Turn down heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Combine flour and 1/4 cup water; stir into 3/4 cup of cooking liquid. Gradually add to vegetable mixture, stirring constantly.
Continue cooking soup, uncovered, for 2 minutes. Season with salt and pepper.
Makes 4 servings.

title: molasses oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix eggs, Crisco, molasses and sugar together in large bowl. Combine all remaining ingredients and mix together thoroughly. Drop teaspoon size amount onto cookie sheet and bake in 400° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: hot salmon salad
directions: Combine salmon, rice, celery and parsley in large mixing bowl. In small bowl, mix mayonnaise, lemon juice and curry powder.
Add to salmon mixture; toss lightly.
Place in one-quart casserole dish.
Sprinkle with paprika.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: savory pot roast(diabetic)
directions: Brown roast in oil.
Saute onions and garlic until tender. Add to roast.
Stir in tomatoes, 1/2 cup water, horseradish, browning sauce, salt and pepper.
Cover and simmer 2 to 3 hours until tender.
Remove roast.
Use 2 cups pan juices.
Mix flour and water; stir into juices.
Cook for 5 minutes until thick and bubbly.
Slice roast and serve with gravy.

title: molasses cake
directions: Stir well together and then add the boiling water. The batter will be very thin. Bake in a 350° oven about 35 to 45 minutes.

title: blueberry, poppy seed muffins
directions: Combine the dry ingredients in a large bowl and stir well. Make a well in the center of the mixture and set aside.
Combine the rest of the ingredients, stirring well. Add to flour mixture and stir until dry ingredients are moistened.
Spoon batter evenly into muffin pans that are greased.
Bake at 400° for 18 minutes.
Yields 1 dozen.

title: ground beef stroganoff(s.o.s.)
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, brown the beef and onion together.
(Do not drain.)
Add the 2 tablespoons of flour and mix well.
Cook on low for 10 minutes.
Add all other ingredients and cook for about 15 minutes on low heat.
You
need to stir the meat mixture often in the recipe.
If it gets too thick, add a little water.
You can use it for dinner over white rice or noodles.
My family likes it on toasted bread with a fried egg on top.
Tastes excellent the next day and freezes well.

title: lemon cake
directions: Mix ingredients together thoroughly (2 minutes).
Bake in oblong pan at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: banana burritos
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey together.
Spread on flour tortilla.
Peel banana and place on tortilla.
Roll the banana up in the tortilla.
Cut into bite size pieces.
This is very good and kids can make them themselves.

title: shepherd's pie
directions: Brown hamburger.
Drain and place into casserole dish.
Add gravy, if desired.
Cover hamburg with creamed corn; spread to cover, but do not mix.
Carefully spoon mashed potatoes over corn, spreading to cover corn.
Dot potatoes with butter; sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in 350° oven until top is brown and bubbly.

title: egg casserole
directions: Cube meat, brown and drain.
Beat eggs; add milk, mustard and bread.
Stir in cheese and meat.
Put in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight.
Before baking remove foil.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: old fashioned bread stuffing
directions: Cook and stir onion and celery in butter in medium skillet over medium heat until tender.
Stir in seasonings.
Add onion mixture and water to bread cubes in large bowl.
Toss to mix. Stuff neck and body cavities of turkey.
Roast immediately. Yield:
8 cups (enough for 12 to 14 pound turkey).

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream butter, Crisco and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Beat well.
Add vanilla.
Sift flour and cocoa with baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture, adding flour first, then 1/4 of milk until all flour and milk has been added to creamed mixture. Bake at 275° for 2 hours.
Bake this in large tube pan.
Cool in pan 10 minutes, then turn onto wire rack to completely cool.

title: saute of fresh spinach
directions: Wash spinach and thoroughly pat dry.
Strip the spinach from stems.

title: grape pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake 45 minutes at 350°.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef with salt and pepper.
Then slice potatoes and boil them.
When these two are cooked, layer each ingredient in a casserole pan.
Slice onion.
Layer on next.
Put mushroom soup next and last, put grated cheese on top.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.

title: tofu-tuna florentine
directions: Preheat oven
to
Place tofu in a large bowl and smash with
a
fork.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well. Place mixture
in
an
8-inch
square baking pan that has been sprayed with a nonstick cooking spray.
Press down gently with the back of a spoon.
Bake, uncovered, for 40 minutes.

title: old fashioned pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease and flour tube pan.
Cream butter and oil.
Add sugar.
Beat well with mixer and add 1 egg at a time.
Sift all dry ingredients together.
Alternate dry ingredients and buttermilk.
Mix.
Bake 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Beat eggs.
Add sugar and oil.
Sift flour into mixture.
Add buttermilk slowly.
Add vanilla.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: cornbread pie
directions: Brown beef well and add remaining ingredients.
Mix well and let simmer for 15 minutes.
Pour into greased casserole; top with cornbread.
Bake for 20 minutes at 350°.

title: 1-2-3-4 cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt together.
Cream shortening (I use Crisco) with sugar and vanilla until fluffy.
Add eggs. Add sifted dry ingredients and milk alternately, in small amounts, beating well after each addition.
Pour into greased pans and bake at 350° for 50 minutes.
Makes 1 large tube cake or 3 (9-inch) layers.

title: sweet 'n sour hot dogs
directions: Slice hot dogs and mix with jam in crock-pot.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Ready to serve.

title: bean salad
directions: Wash kidney beans off and let all beans drain in colander. Place in glass bowl.
Cut and dice onions.
Slice celery thin.
Cut pepper in quarters, then slice thin.
Pour over vegetables the oil, salt and pepper.
