Bring to boil the vinegar and sugar.
Pour over vegetables.
Put in refrigerator and let stand overnight.

title: enchilada casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion.
Cook until done.
Add rest of ingredients, except for Doritos and cheese.
Simmer for 5 minutes. Alternate mixture in a large baking dish with chips.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Add cheese during the last 5 minutes.

title: sweet-sour chinese chicken wings(for a large group)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Pour on chicken wings and let sit in refrigerator overnight.
Bake next day in sauce in a 325° oven for 1 hour.

title: cornmeal rolls
directions: Cook cornmeal, sugar, salt, shortening and milk in medium saucepan until thick.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add yeast, which has been dissolved in lukewarm water, then eggs.
Beat thoroughly. Add flour to form a soft dough.
Knead well; cover and let rise. Punch down.
Roll out to 1-inch thickness; cut with biscuit cutter or glass.
Brush with melted butter; dust with cornmeal (optional).
Place on cookie sheet; let rise, covered.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Yields 18 rolls.

title: mallow fruit dip
directions: Beat ingredients at medium speed with electric mixer until well blended.
Serve with any kind of fruit.
Makes about 3 cups.

title: red kidney bean soup
directions: Wash beans.
Soak dried kidney beans for 2 hours in 2 cups of cold water.
Cook beans until they are beginning to get soft.
(You may pressure cook the beans for 15 minutes instead of soaking.) Stir well.
Add ham bone or pieces of ham (fat removed) and cook for 25 to 30 minutes.
(You may use beef instead of ham.)
Add potatoes and cook for 10 minutes.
Add carrots, onions, garlic, thyme, salt and pepper.
Simmer until everything is tender.
Stir often.
Add unbroken hot pepper.
Let simmer and avoid stirring. Pepper should not break in soup.
Serve warm with slices of whole wheat bread or hard dough bread or rolls.
Enjoy!

title: banana nut cake
directions: Stir shortening to soften.
Stir in dry ingredients.
Add bananas and half the buttermilk.
Mix until all flour is dampened. Beat vigorously two minutes.
Add remaining buttermilk and eggs. Beat 2 minutes longer.
Fold in nuts.
Bake in 2 paper-lined 9 x 1 1/2-inch round pans at 350° for about 35 minutes.
Cool 10 minutes in pans.
Remove.

title: cheese and ale spread
directions: Process in processor until smooth.
If too thick, add beer. Pack in small bowl.
Let set overnight in refrigerator.
Serve at room temperature.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Large buns will need 2 slices of Spam, cut a scant 1/4-inch thick to make them about right.
Small buns will need 1 slice of Spam cut rather thick (at least 1/4-inch or thicker).

title: gramma's salamagundi bake
directions: Combine
can tomato sauce, rice, water, onion, green pepper,
salt
and	pepper.
Turn into 2-quart casserole (buttered).
Layer	ground	beef
on
top
and sprinkle with salt. Spread corn
over
beef.
Pour second can of tomato sauce over corn.
Add a few slices of bacon on top.

title: cowboy cake
directions: Measure the flour, shortening, salt and brown sugar into a bowl; work to fine crumbs.
Remove 1/2 cup of mixture; save to sprinkle on top of cake.
To the remaining crumbs, add baking powder, nutmeg, cinnamon and baking soda.
Add well beaten eggs to the sour milk, then stir into the dry mixture and beat until smooth.
Bake in layers; sprinkle with reserved crumbs.
Cinnamon and nut meats may be sprinkled on top.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: samantha's fruit kebabs
directions: You will also need bamboo skewers.

title: fruit salad
directions: Drain pineapple juice into bowl. Add pudding and Tang.
Beat well with wire whisk until thickened and dissolved. Stir in apples first, then other fruits. Keep refrigerated.

title: ham ball recipe(one of our favorites - physician services)
directions: Blend together the cream cheese and mayonnaise.
Add remaining ingredients; mix well.
Form into a ball.
Chill for at least 3 hours.
Serve with crackers.

title: waffles
directions: Crack eggs in mixing bowl.
Beat eggs until frothy.
Add milk and oil and continue beating for about 1 minute. Sift dry ingredients into the bowl and mix until well blended.
Pour 1/2 cup batter onto hot waffle iron. Bake. Serve immediately with fruit, honey or syrup.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together well while potatoes are hot and marshmallows melt.
Put into a two-quart casserole.
Bake until well heated (about 10 to 15 minutes) at 350°.
Remove and place on the topping

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix everything together except the pecans until the mixture is well blended.
Bake at 350° for about 50 minutes.

title: sweet potato pie
directions: Blend potatoes, sugar and eggs.
Add oleo and vanilla.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: grape granola bars
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels in medium saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Add jelly; stir until well blended.
Remove from heat.
Add granola, oats and chopped peanuts; mix until well coated.
Spread evenly in a buttered 9 x 9 x 2-inch square pan. Refrigerate until firm; cut into bars.
Makes 24 (2 1/4 x 1 1/2-inch) bars.

title: oysterettes
directions: Empty oyster crackers into a large bowl.
In a small bowl combine oil and seasonings; mix well.
Slowly pour oil mixture over crackers; toss well.
Store in an airtight container; toss before opening and serving.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients, then add all the rest. Grease and flour 2 bread pans. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: orange salad
directions: Cut orange slices up as desired. Layer oranges, sugar and coconut. Pour 1/2 cup orange juice over layers. Store overnight.

title: stir-fry chicken
directions: Heat oven and platter to 150 degrees.
Combine 2 tsp. cornstarch with 2 Tbsp. water and 1/2 tsp. salt; mix well with chicken.
Can be kept refrigerated for up to 24 hours.
Heat large skillet or wok until very hot.
Pour in 2 Tbsp. oil.
Add chicken. Stir-fry quickly until chicken turns white and pieces separate. Sprinkle with sherry.
Transfer to platter in oven.
Reheat skillet, add 3 Tbsp. oil.
Stir-fry vegetables quickly for about 2 minutes.
Sprinkle with 1 tsp. salt.
Add chicken.
Mix remaining cornstarch and water.
Pour into skillet stirring constantly until sauce coats chicken and vegetables.
Serve with rice and soy sauce.
Serves 4.

title: summer squash custard casserole
directions: Select the small, tender, yellow summer squash, slice and parboil; drain.
Mix eggs, salt, pepper and milk to cover in casserole.
Sprinkle nutmeg over this.
Bake in oven at 325° until set, approximately 50 minutes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Cook beets in water.
Peel and put into jars.
Combine remaining ingredients; boil and pour vinegar mixture over beets. Seal jars.

title: cranberry salad ring
directions: Sprinkle gelatin on orange juice to soften.
Let soak for 5 minutes.
Place over low heat.
Stir until gelatin is dissolved. Remove from heat and combine with cranberry sauce.
Chill until partially set.
Fold in apple, celery and walnuts.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart ring mold.
Chill until firm.
Unmold on crisp greens (if desired).

title: louisiana shrimp sauce piquant
directions: In a large skillet, saute onions in heated oil until light brown.
Add water, garlic and celery.
Cover and cook until tender.
Add tomatoes, salt, pepper, tomato sauce and Tabasco sauce.
Simmer uncovered on low heat for 30 to 40 minutes until thickened.
Add shrimp and lemon pieces.
Cover and cook 15 minutes for 2 to 3 minutes.
Before serving, add parsley and green onion.
Serve over cooked rice.
Serves 6.
Has 189 calories, 30% from fat.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order until you get to milk and flour.
Alternate these 2 with the mixture.
Drop by tablespoons and bake at 350°.
You may need a little more flour.

title: honey-mustard dip
directions: Mix well all ingredients.
May be used as a dip, spread or salad dressing.
Keeps well in the refrigerator.

title: toothpaste putty
directions: Mix toothpaste, glue and cornstarch in dish.
Mix with 1 finger.
Add water.
Mix until you have a lump of putty.
Wash and dry hands. Squeeze and roll putty into ball.
Push, pull, roll and explore putty.

title: southern fried chicken
directions: In plastic bag, combine flour, paprika, salt and pepper.
Add chicken, a few pieces at a time.
Shake to coat.
Mix egg and milk. Dip floured chicken into egg mixture.
Coat well with flour again.
In a large skillet, fry chicken in medium-hot oil, a few pieces at a time.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Melt in microwave first 2 ingredients.
Stir in next 3 ingredients.
Press in greased pizza pan.
Top with next item. Mix together 2 ounces bark and oil and drizzle over entire pizza.

title: frozen sliced pickles
directions: Pour over pickle mixture and mix well.
Freeze in bowls or other containers.

title: macaroni cheese
directions: Boil macaroni according to box directions; drain and place into a 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Cut cheese into small pieces.
Melt butter, cheese and milk over a low flame until creamy.
Mix eggs until smooth.
Pour sauce and egg mixture over macaroni and mix until evenly distributed.
Sprinkle shredded cheese over the top and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: artichoke dip ii
directions: Drain artichokes and chop in food processor.
You may also chop the green chili peppers so that they are fine.
Put all ingredients in a small greased casserole dish and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: apple and herb stuffing(servings:  4)
directions: In large skillet, cook celery and onion in margarine until tender.
Add water and bouillon; cook until bouillon dissolves. In large bowl, combine remaining ingredients except rich turkey gravy; add bouillon mixture.
Mix well.
Loosely stuff turkey just before roasting.
Place remaining stuffing in greased baking dish. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until hot.
Serve with rich turkey gravy, if desired.
Refrigerate leftovers.
Makes about 2 1/2 quarts.

title: hard candy
directions: Boil to hard ball stage.
Add coloring and flavor.
Sprinkle powdered sugar on buttered pan.

title: chili with beans
directions: Cook hamburger and onion until done.
Drain off grease.
Add remaining ingredients and simmer over low heat about 20 to 25 minutes.

title: roast wild goose 2
directions: Salt and pepper goose, inside and out.
Place a small onion, a slice of pork and a tablespoon of red wine inside goose.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli and rice each as directed.
Heat soup and Cheez Whiz until just hot, add onion and rice.
Mix thoroughly.
Fold in broccoli and serve immediately.

title: black-eyed pea dip
directions: Drain peas and mix all together.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Stir occasionally.
Serve with corn chips.

title: dump cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Use 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Dump undrained pineapple into pan; spread.
Dump pie filling; spread. Dump dry cake mix onto cherry layer; spread.
Sprinkle pecans over cake mix.
Pour butter on top.
Bake 48 to 53 minutes.
Last 10 to 15 minutes, sprinkle coconut on top, then bake the remaining time or until coconut is done.
Serves 12 to 16.

title: lefse
directions: Mash potatoes.
Measure.
Add salt, baking powder, sugar, melted lard and cream.
Beat until smooth.
Let stand until cold. Add flour when ready to bake.
Spread thin in frying pan.
Bake.

title: saucy ground beef casserole
directions: In 2 1/2-quart casserole, cook beef or sausage, garlic, onion, oregano, salt and pepper, covered, on High 4 to 6 minutes, until meat loses its pink color and onion is tender-crisp, stirring to break up meat halfway through cooking.
Stir in eggplant and zucchini.
Cook, covered, on High 8 to 10 minutes, until vegetables are almost tender, stirring halfway through cooking.
Stir in tomatoes and tomato paste.
Cook, covered, 5 to 7 minutes, until vegetables are tender, stirring halfway through cooking.
Makes 4 servings.

title: green bean and pea casserole
directions: Boil green beans until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain off liquid.

title: creamy beef in rye round
directions: Cut a lid out of a rye round (may be purchased at the deli). Remove most all of soft bread in bite size chunks, leaving a hollow round of crust.
Mix dip mixture together and pour into round.
Serve with the chunks of bread.

title: low-fat pineapple upside down cake
directions: Melt butter or margarine in 10-inch cast iron skillet. Sprinkle brown sugar over butter while still on heat.
Remove from heat and cover with pineapple rings.
Separate egg whites; set aside.
Beat yolks well and add 1/2 cup sugar; beat well again. In separate bowl, mix flour, sugar, baking powder and salt.
In saucepan, boil 1/2 cup water; alternate mixing of egg mixture and water into dry ingredients.
Beat whites until stiff and fold into batter gently.
Spoon batter over pineapple and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: taco salad
directions: Brown and drain ground beef and layer on bottom of dish.
Beat together cream cheese, sour cream and taco seasoning mix.
Smear on ground beef.
Chop onion, green pepper and tomatoes.
Grate Cheddar cheese and sprinkle on top.
Microwave on High for 10 minutes.
In regular oven, cook at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes. Double recipe for 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: sweet potato cornbread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in eggs, oil, milk and sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 35 minutes or until done.

title: *baked parmesan chicken
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, seasonings and parsley; set aside.
Saute garlic in 2 tablespoons margarine.
Brush chicken with garlic butter; roll each piece in bread crumbs.
Place chicken in a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan; sprinkle with remaining crumb mixture.
Pour on remaining margarine.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes or until golden brown.
Serves 6.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Melt margarine with cocoa.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar and eggs, mixing well.
Add flour, vanilla, salt and baking soda. Stir in pecans.
Spoon batter into greased and floured 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes or until cake tests done. Remove from oven.
Cover the cake with marshmallows while cake is still hot.

title: award-winning dream bars
directions: Mix the first 3 ingredients.
Press into an 8-inch square cake pan.
Bake 10 minutes at 375°.
Cool.

title: spinach salad
directions: Wash and stem spinach.
Allow to drain.

title: super fudgy brownies
directions: Combine butter or margarine, sugar and vanilla, then add eggs. Beat well with spoon.
Combine flour, cocoa, baking powder and salt; gradually add to egg mixture until well blended.
Stir in nuts.
Spread in greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from edge of pan.
Cool in pan.
Frost and cut into squares.

title: grandma's good cookies
directions: Cream the butter and oil; add sugars and beat well.
Add beaten egg.
Add cornflakes, oatmeal, coconut, nuts and vanilla.
Mix by hand.
Mix salt, soda and flour together and add to mixture.
Form into balls about 1 inch.
Press lightly with fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet until lightly browned at 350° to 375°. Immediately after taking out of oven, sprinkle with powdered sugar, then let cool.
Makes 100 to 120 cookies.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Saute onion in 1 tablespoon margarine.
Make sauce of milk, flour, salt and margarine.
Add shredded cheese, turkey and lemon juice.
Add to noodles.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Mushrooms or pimento may be added, if desired.

title: blueberry pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and confectioners sugar, then set aside.
Mix 2 packages Dream Whip, 3/4 cup milk and vanilla.
Then mix all ingredients together.
Place the can of blueberries in crust.

title: pineapple icebox pie
directions: Soften cream cheese in microwave for 45 seconds.
Add drained pineapple and sugar.
Mix well.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Cheaper brands are watery and pie will not set up.
Place in graham cracker pie shell and chill one hour minimum.

title: chicken curry sandwiches
directions: Combine chicken, ham, white sauce and seasoning.
Toast bread in oven on one side.
Spread untoasted side with the mixed ingredients.
Sprinkle with buttered crumbs. Bake in oven at 425° for 15 minutes.
Makes 6 sandwiches.

title: chicken or turkey salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and blend together.

title: beef barley soup stew
directions: In a large pot brown beef with onion.
Drain fat and add remaining ingredients.
Simmer for 45 minutes until barley is tender.
Serves 6 to 8.
This is a thick soup.
(Best when made a day or two ahead of time.)

title: lemon torte
directions: Mix flour, nuts and melted butter together.
Pat on an ungreased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 8 to 12 minutes at 350°. Let cool.
Blend cream cheese and powdered sugar until smooth. Add 1 cup cool Whip.
Spread on cooled nut layer.
Beat 2 packages instant pudding with milk at low speed for 2 minutes.
Put on cheese layer.
Spread with rest of Cool Whip.
Refrigerate until ready to serve.

title: peanut butter tandy cake
directions: Cream eggs, sugar, oil and salt.
Add flour alternately with milk and vanilla.

title: poppy seed cake
directions: Mix all; beat at medium speed for 4 minutes.
Pour into a well-greased angel food pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Beat butter, cream cheese and sugar until fluffy. Add vanilla, butternut extract and salt. Beat well. Add 6 eggs 1 at a time, beating well after each. Add flour. Mix well. Pour into greased 10-inch tube pan. Bake at 325° for 1 1/2 hours. Cool.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Sift dry ingredients.
Add shortening and buttermilk.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Bake for 35 minutes at 350°.

title: zippy beef-cheese sandwich spread
directions: Soften onion in sherry.
Blend cream cheese, mayonnaise, dried beef and olives.
Stir in onion mix.
Let stand overnight.
Spread on party rye bread or wheat crackers.

title: chewy caramel chocolate cake
directions: Pour boiling water over chocolate.
Stir until melted and cool.
Heat oven to 350°.
Grease and flour 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan. Beat sugar and 1/4 plus 2 tablespoons margarine in medium bowl on medium speed until fluffy.
Beat in egg yolks.
Beat in chocolate mixture and vanilla on low speed.
Beat in flour, baking soda and salt alternately with buttermilk; beat after each addition until smooth.
Beat egg whites until stiff.
Fold into batter and pour into pan.
Bake 20 minutes or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.
Heat margarine, caramels and evaporated milk over medium heat, stirring constantly, until smooth.
Pour over hot cake.
Sprinkle with chocolate chips and pecans. Bake 15 minutes.
Cool before serving.

title: barbecue chicken(part ii)
directions: In skillet, slowly brown chicken in butter (about 25 minutes).
Add sauce mixture.
Cover; cook over low heat 20 minutes or until done.
Stir often.
Serve with rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Heat grease in a large skillet.
Add vegetables and cook until done, but still crisp.

title: grandmother's cornbread cake
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Sift together flour, sugar, cornmeal, baking soda and salt.
Add beaten egg and milk to make a stiff batter.
Add shortening and beat until well mixed.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Brush top with melted butter or margarine and bake 5 to 10 minutes longer.
Serve while hot. Makes 6 to 8 servings.

title: nut bread
directions: Cream butter and shortening.
Add sugar.
Beat until light and fluffy.
Add egg, orange marmalade and cooked, mashed potatoes. Beat until blended.
Sift together 2 1/4 cups flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Use 1 tablespoon flour to toss with chopped pecans (set aside).

title: summer pasta(this pasta can be served warm or cold.)
directions: Cook down oil, garlic, tomatoes, salt and pepper. Add sliced olives, cilantro and lime juice just prior to pouring onto cooked pasta (best to serve on a shallow platter). Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.

title: dreamsicle pie
directions: Mix all ingredients well. Pour into pie crusts. Chill 8 hours.

title: cheese biscuits
directions: Mix grated cheese and butter with your hands until smooth.
Add flour gradually.
Test one to be sure they have enough flour. Chill if too soft.
Roll dough out to 1/4-inch thick and cut into small biscuits.
Put on ungreased cookie sheet.
Top each biscuit with a pecan half or piece.
Bake at 350° for about 12 minutes or until done.
Do not brown.
Makes 2 dozen.

title: spiced pecans
directions: Beat egg white and water together to soft peaks. Put all ingredients into large bowl. MIX WELL. Spread into a single layer on cookie sheet (do not grease).
Bake in 250° oven for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: cheese soup
directions: Put all ingredients in pot except croutons.
Cook on low heat until cheese has melted.
Stir occasionally.
Serve in warm bowls. Top each serving with crisp croutons.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Brown sausage and drain.
Prepare 1 cup of Comet rice as directed on box.
Combine sausage, onion and celery and simmer about 5 minutes.
Stir all ingredients together.
Pour in casserole dish and bake at 300° for about 1 hour.
Stir after first 30 minutes and cover with lid.

title: garlic souffle(6 persons)
directions: In a double boiler, make a roux of the butter and flour and cook it slowly for 5 to 8 minutes.
Mix the creams together and scald.
Remove the roux from the heat and whisk in the scalded creams.
Add the bouquet garni; cover and cook over slowly simmering water for about 1 hour, stirring occasionally.
Cool slightly before adding the rest of the ingredients.
Remove bouquet garni.
(Can be made ahead.)

title: martha washington candy
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients and roll in balls; chill before dipping.
Melt Gulfwax with chocolate chips in top of double boiler; dip balls in mixture.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Mix salt with cabbage and let stand 1 hour.
Squeeze out excess moisture.
Add carrots and pepper.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Slowly add sugar, then other ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Makes 2 deep dish or 3 regular pies.

title: hamburger potato pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix meat, 1 1/3 cups of the Potato Buds (dry), egg, salt, pepper, onion, catsup and milk.
Spread in ungreased pie pan, 9 x 1 1/2-inches.
Bake uncovered 35 to 40 minutes.

title: fish pinwheel appetizers
directions: Wash and dry fish.
Cut into strips 3-inches long and 1/2-inch wide.
Mix cheese, parsley flakes, lemon pepper and garlic powder. Coat one side of fish with cheese mixture and roll, coated side in, into a pinwheel; fasten with a toothpick.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar and eggs.
Add dry ingredients to creamed mixture.
Add soda to 1/2 applesauce and then add to remainder. Add raisins and nuts.
Bake at 350°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cook syrup, sugar and margarine until melted.
Cook for 2 to 3 minutes.
Beat eggs and pour cooked mixture over them.
Take off beater and add pecans.
Pour in crust and cook for about 35 minutes at 350°.

title: happiness cake
directions: Mix with care and fold in prayer and faith.
Serve throughout your day.

title: old english egg nog
directions: In large bowl, beat egg yolks until thick.
Gradually add granulated sugar, beating until light.
Add cream, beating until very well combined.
Slowly stir in cognac and rum.
Refrigerate, covered, until well chilled.
About 1 hour before serving, beat egg whites until foamy.
Gradually add confectioners sugar, beating well after each addition; continue beating until soft peaks form when beater is slowly raised.
Gently fold into egg yolk mixture.
Refrigerate, covered, until serving time.
Makes about 28 (4 ounce) servings.
Good without the liquor, too.

title: old fashion apple cake
directions: Mix salad oil, eggs and sugar together.
In a separate bowl, sift flour, soda, salt, baking powder and cinnamon.
Then add to egg and sugar mixture.
Mix well.
Then stir in nuts and apples.

title: banana nut cake
directions: Cream butter.
Add sugar, eggs and buttermilk, beating well. Add bananas. Then add flour and salt.
Add pecans and soda that has been dissolved in hot water.
Divide into three cake pans that have been greased and floured. Bake at 350° until done and cake leaves sides of pans.

title: fruit punch
directions: Make Kool-Aid according to directions.
Add pineapple juice. (I use gallon milk or juice jug.)
Freeze. Take out of freezer 12 to 15 hours before time to serve (long enough to get slushy). Pour into punch bowl.
(May need to cut off top of jug.)
Add chilled ginger ale just before serving.
Makes 25 to 30 (6 ounce) servings.

title: glorified rice
directions: Dissolve jello in boiling water.
Add crushed pineapple. Cool.
When this mixture is partially set, whip until creamy.
Add cooked rice then fold in whipped cream.
Chill until firm.
Top with whipped cream and a maraschino cherry if desired.
Serves 6-8.

title: spinach salad
directions: Cut up spinach and combine with bean sprouts and water chestnuts and cooked bacon.

title: jalapeno peppers
directions: Rubber gloves are a must!
Slice peppers lengthwise.
Take out seeds and veins.
Wash thoroughly to remove excess seeds.
In one pot, put peppers and cover with oil.
Cook on medium, stirring constantly, until peppers turn greyish in color.
In another pot, put sliced carrots, onions, garlic and salt; cover with vinegar. Cook until carrots are tender.
Have jars ready to seal.
Combine mixtures and fill jars.
Seal tightly.

title: pina colada fruit dip
directions: Blend and refrigerate 1 to 2 hours.
Serve with a fresh fruit tray (melon balls, apple wedges, grapes, pineapple spears, etc.).

title: hamburg and mushroom casserole
directions: Cook macaroni.
Brown hamburg, celery and onions; pour off grease.
Add tomato sauce and macaroni.
Spread cheese on top. Bake 1/2 hour at 350°.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Cut tortillas in bite size pieces and soak in milk. Meanwhile, combine the soups.
Then layer tortillas, chicken breasts, olives, peppers, chilies and onion.
Add soup.
Top with grated cheese.
Bake, covered, at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes. Serves 6.

title: pasta salad
directions: Cook, drain and cool macaroni.
Add diced vegetables.
Season with parslied garlic salt and Italian olive oil dressing.
Stir to coat evenly.
Serves 6 to 10.

title: hearty lentil soup
directions: Rinse lentils and drain.
Combine all ingredients in a 6-quart pan.
Cover and bring to a boil, over medium-high heat.
Reduce heat to low when boiling rapidly.
Simmer 2 hours.
Before serving, remove soup bone and bay leaf.

title: my favorite meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Put into loaf pan.
Cover with 2 strips of bacon (optional).
Pour over all one 8 ounce can tomato sauce.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients except cheese and chips.
Put in casserole.
Sprinkle cheese on top, then chips.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
If cold, bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: chili beef twist
directions: Add 1 tablespoon salt to 3 quarts of boiling water.
Cook noodles, uncovered, stirring occasionally, until tender.
Drain in colander.
Cook beef in oil until lightly brown and drain.
Add 1/2 teaspoon salt and chili powder and mix well.
Mix twists, beef, cheese and tomato sauce in greased casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, in 350° oven for 45 minutes.

title: italian beef
directions: Place a 5 to 6 pound rump roast on baking pan.
Combine the remaining ingredients and pour over the top of the meat.
Cover tightly with foil and bake for 3 hours at 350°.
Don't peek!!! Remove meat and slice thin.
Put back into juice.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix well and roll out into balls (approximately 100).
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Serve hot.

title: dried beef cheese ball
directions: Chop dried beef fine.
Beat all ingredients well with mixer. Shape in parsley and chopped walnuts.
Serve with bite size crackers.

title: escalloped potatoes
directions: Steam thinly sliced potatoes 10 minutes.
Bring milk to a boil
and thicken slightly.
Mix ingredients altogether and pour in a greased casserole.
Bake covered 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 400°. During
last
or
10 minutes of baking, place cheese slices on top and bake only until cheese is melted.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Mix all together and add dressing.

title: seafood salad
directions: Cut surimi seafood in half or shred.
Mix with celery, mayo, eggs, onion, juice and mustard.
Makes 4 servings.

title: fish - on the grill
directions: Cut fish steaks into 8 serving pieces.
Place in shallow dish and pour combined lemon juice and salad oil over all.
Refrigerate 1/2 hour.

title: a super way to freeze fish
directions: Mix water and lemon juice.
Sprinkle gelatine into liquid. Once mixed, heat the liquid slowly until clear.
Cool.
Dip fish into mixture.
Wrap snuggly in airtight plastic bags and freeze. Keeps fish frozen up to a year.

title: christmas fudge
directions: Break Hershey bars into small pieces.
Add Marshmallow Creme and chocolate chips.
Set aside in large bowl.
Boil the sugar, milk and butter for 8 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour this over chocolate.
Beat until smooth, but not cool.
Stir in chopped walnuts.
Spread into a buttered cookie sheet.
Cut when cool. Freezes well.

title: pear relish
directions: Grind
pears,
onions and peppers in food grinder.
Add all ingredients.
Boil
until thick (about 35 to 45 minutes). Put into jars and seal.

title: chocolate pretzels
directions: Put the round pretzels on a sprayed cookie sheet. Put one Hershey Kiss in the center of each pretzel. Place in a 275° oven for 3 minutes. As soon as you take them out of the oven, put one M&M in the center of the soft Hershey Kiss. Press down enough that the Kiss attaches to the pretzel and let cool.

title: peach pie
directions: Mix together sugar, salt and jel, then add water.
Cook until clear.
Remove from heat; add jello and cool.
Mix fresh sliced peaches into mixture and pour into baked pie crust.
Top with whipped cream.

title: steak and sweet pepper saute
directions: Heat olive oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add 1/2 the steak; cook until browned.
Remove; repeat with other half of steak.
Add vegetables; stir frequently and cook for 5 minutes. Add beef broth and vinegar; bring to a boil, stirring often.
Pour sauce over steaks.
Serves 4.

title: mackeral loaf
directions: Drain the mackeral, flake and place in a bowl.
Add the bread crumbs, milk, pickle relish, eggs, salt, margarine and onion and mix well.
Pack in a well-greased loaf pan and place bacon on top. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes, then slice.

title: fry bread for indian tacos
directions: Combine ingredients together with spoon until mixed (about 50 strokes).
You may need a little extra flour to handle.
Grab 1 handful and flatten.
Deep fry at 450°, turning over when light brown.
Drain on paper towels.

title: green goddess dressing
directions: Use low-fat mayonnaise and no fat sour cream if you want to.

title: jackie b's apple squares
directions: Mix all together.
Fold in 2 cups thinly sliced apples (takes about 3 medium apples).
Bake in a greased 13 x 9-inch pan at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: no bake brownies
directions: Mix chocolate, milk and cinnamon in saucepan.
Stir over low heat until chocolate melts and is smooth and thick.
Put aside 1/2 cup.
In mixing bowl, combine vanilla wafer crumbs, marshmallows, nuts and sugar.
Stir in chocolate mixture and blend well.
Press into buttered square pan.
Spread 1/2 cup chocolate mixture over top and chill about 1 hour.

title: banana spread
directions: Mix all together and bake at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: orange rolls
directions: Set half of this aside.
Spread half of orange mixture on dough.
Roll up tightly, beginning at 24-inch side.
Pinch edge of dough into roll to seal well.
Stretch roll to make even.
Cut into twenty four 1-inch slices.
Place slightly apart in greased round 8 x 1 1/2-inch layer pan.
Let rise until double, about 40 minutes.
Heat oven to 375°.
Bake until golden brown, 20 to 25 minutes.
Frost remaining orange mixture while warm.
Makes 2 dozen rolls.

title: leek soup
directions: In a large kettle, saute leeks, mushrooms, carrots, celery and parsnips in margarine for 5 minutes. Add broth, dill weed, salt and pepper. Add potatoes and bay leaf.
Cook until potatoes are tender. Remove bay leaf.
Add milk and meat (if used).

title: peanut butter torte
directions: Pat first 4 ingredients into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 12 minutes at 350°.
Mix cream cheese, sugar and peanut butter and put into cooled crust.
Mix puddings and milk and beat for 2 minutes.
Pour onto cream cheese mixture; top with Cool Whip.
Refrigerate.

title: egg dumplings
directions: Combine lemon juice, garlic, oregano, salt and pepper in bowl. Whisk in oil until well blended. (Marinade can be refrigerated, covered, for up to 2 days.)

title: calico bean salad
directions: Saute onion.
Brown ground beef; drain off fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in lightly greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes (cover while baking).

title: round steak ranchero
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients.
Marinate steak overnight.
Broil steak, using marinade as basting sauce.

title: barbecued shrimp
directions: Mix all ingredients except shrimp in blender.
Marinate shrimp in sauce at least 6 hours.
Thread four shrimp on small wooden skewers that have been soaked in water.
Grill to heat through.

title: scotcharoos
directions: Combine sugar and Karo syrup in 3-quart pan. Remove from heat and stir in peanut butter; mix. Add Rice Krispies.
Press into 13 x 9-inch pan. Melt together chips. Spread over mixture.

title: polynesian pot roast
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat meat on all sides with flour.
In Dutch oven, brown meat in hot Crisco.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Combine the juice, soy sauce, lemon juice, sugar, garlic and basil.
Add to meat in Dutch oven.
Cover; roast at 350° for 2 hours or until meat is tender.
Baste occasionally with the mixture.
During the last 10 minutes, top with pineapple slices. Remove meat and pineapple to warm platter.
Skim off excess fat. Add enough water to pan drippings to make 2 cups liquid.
Combine cornstarch and the cold water; stir into drippings.
Cook and stir until thickened and bubbly.
Drizzle meat with a little sauce; serve remaining sauce with meat.
Makes 6 servings.

title: shrimp soup
directions: Cook shrimp
in
margarine
until
pink.
Mix all other ingredients in a 3-quart pot
and heat until very hot, but not boiling. Add shrimp and salt
and pepper to taste.	Serve with crackers or on rice.

title: cynthia korzon's shrimp spread
directions: Mix together.
Make in morning so it sits.

title: personal pizzas
directions: Separate biscuits.
Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Pat into 4-inch circles. Spoon 2 tablespoons pizza sauce over each biscuit. Sprinkle cheese evenly over each biscuit.
Top each biscuit with choice of toppings. Bake at 425° for 10 minutes or until crust is golden brown. Serve hot.

title: dijon chicken
directions: Mince and mix garlic into mustard.
Place chicken pieces into pan.
Coat chicken (skin side) with mustard/garlic mixture. Sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Crush rosemary between fingers and sprinkle over chicken.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: easy meat loaf
directions: In medium sized bowl, mix eggs, milk, onion, salt, pepper and 2 tablespoons catsup.
Tear bread into small pieces and combine with egg mixture.
Mix well.
Add ground beef and mix well.
Shape into a loaf and place in loaf pan.
Coat top of loaf with remaining catsup.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: honey buttered chicken breasts
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a medium skillet, heat olive oil; add onions and green pepper and saute till onions are translucent, remove and clean skillet.
In skillet melt butter; add honey, mustard, curry and salt, mix well.
Dip chicken, both sides in mixture.
Place chicken in a 13x9-inch dish, top with onions and peppers, and add remaining sauce and bake 30 to 45 minutes, uncovered.
EAT.

title: cilantro pesto
directions: Combine cilantro, garlic and nuts in a blender.
Blend for 30 seconds until smooth.
With motor running, carefully add olive oil in a steady stream.
Turn off blender and add cheese, salt and pepper.
Blend.
Serve over shrimp.

title: oven beef stew
directions: Cut meat into 1-inch cubes; sprinkle with salt and pepper and dredge in flour.
Melt fat in skillet and in it, brown meat thoroughly.

title: josh's favorite strawberry pie
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch, jello, food coloring, lemon juice and water.
Cook until clear.
Pour over strawberries already placed in pie shells.
Refrigerate until chilled.
Serve with Cool Whip.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix all ingredients together and spoon in deep fryer of hot oil.
Let cook; take out and place on paper towels or brown paper bag to be sure all oil is out.

title: wisconsin fish fry
directions: Fillet and rinse fish.
Pat dry (moist) with paper towels. Combine "Frying Magic," beer and egg in concoction that resembles in consistency to pancake batter.
Heat vegetable or corn oil in pan to about 375° (just enough oil to cover half of the fillet). Slide fish into batter mix, coating liberally.
Place into hot oil about 2 minutes per side or until batter is golden brown and fish flakes when cutting through.
Remove; drain briefly on paper towels.
Serve piping hot, ideally with fried potatoes, first sliced, boiled and then chilled before frying.

title: layered lemon dessert
directions: Cut butter into flour until crumbly.
Stir in pecans.
Press into ungreased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes. Cool.

title: meatball casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small balls and place in casserole dish.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Boil chicken breast-debone and chop-set aside.
Mix melted butter with cracker crumbs-put 1/2 this mixture in a greased casserole. Cover with diced chicken.
Mix together soup, broth and sour cream and pour over top.
Cover with remaining cracker crumbs. Bake in 350 degree oven for 30 minutes or until cracker crumbs are light brown.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef and onion in frying pan.
Add tomatoes, salt, soup and pepper.
Simmer while cooking noodles.
Add cooked, drained noodles and half of cheese to meat mixture.
Pour into casserole dish and sprinkle with remainder of cheese.
Can be served immediately or can be baked in oven 15 minutes at 350°.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Defrost potatoes and mix all ingredients in a large bowl. Pour into a 9 x 13-inch dish.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes until bubbly and done.
Sprinkle on a little more cheese and some paprika and bake for another 10 minutes.
This will make it a little crispy on top.
You can make this the day before and rewarm.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Dissolve Jell-O in hot water.
Add strawberries and let melt. Add the rest of the ingredients, except the sour cream.
Put half of the mixture in a mold.
Let congeal.
Spread sour cream over the congealed salad, then add the rest of the salad mixture. Refrigerate.
Unmold to serve.

title: chicken loaf
directions: Mix and bake in a greased pan in a 300° oven for 1 hour.
Can make gravy of extra broth.

title: salmon mousse
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water in large bowl.
Stir in boiling water and whisk the mixture slowly until gelatin dissolves.
Cool to room temperature.
Whisk in mayonnaise, lemon juice, grated onion, hot pepper sauce, paprika, salt and dill.
Blend and refrigerate for 20 minutes.

title: oyster cracker snack
directions: Put crackers in a bowl.
Mix the oil, dressing mix, garlic powder and dill.
Pour slowly over crackers and stir well.
Let stand overnight in a sealed container.
Crackers will be very crisp.

title: pound cake
directions: Cream together margarine and Crisco.
Add sugar and beat until fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together and add to mixture alternately with milk.
Add flavoring.
Bake in a Bundt pan at 300° for 1 hour.

title: good punch
directions: Dissolve the jello and sugar in the boiling water.
Add the pineapple juice and the frozen orange juice; mix together.
Pour into a 1-gallon plastic jug.
Finish filling with water and freeze.
Thaw 3 hours prior to serving.
Add the ginger ale. Yields 50 servings.

title: biscuits
directions: Cut butter into the flour and baking powder.
Add sugar.
Mix in milk.
Roll slightly on floured board.
Cut into rounds.
Bake at 400° for approximately 12 minutes on a lightly greased baking sheet.

title: buttermilk honey bread
directions: In small mixing bowl, dissolve yeast and sugar in warm water; let stand until creamy (10 minutes).
Combine buttermilk, honey and yeast mixture in large bowl.
Add salt and 2 cups flour; whisk well.
Add remaining flour 1/2 cup at a time, mixing well with wooden spoon after each addition.
When dough has pulled together, turn it out onto a lightly floured surface; knead until smooth and supple (6 minutes).
Lightly oil a large mixing bowl; place in dough.
Turn to coat with oil.
Cover with a damp cloth and put in a warm place to rise until double in volume (1 hour).
Preheat oven to 375°.
Deflate dough; turn it out onto lightly floured surface.
Divide dough into 2 equal pieces; form two loaves. Place loaves into two lightly greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pans.
Cover with damp cloth; let rise until double in volume (40 minutes). Lastly, bake at 375° for 30 minutes or until tops are golden brown.

title: squash fritters
directions: Mix together and drop by tablespoons in hot grease. Turn once and cook until done.

title: mississippi mud cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix flour and cocoa together and add to egg mixture.
Add vanilla and nuts. Pour into greased and floured 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Pour 1 package miniature marshmallows on top and return to oven until melted.
Remove and cool slightly and pour icing on top.

title: mulled cider
directions: In electric coffee pot or large pot, simmer for 15 minutes. Do not boil!
Serve hot.
Store unused mulled cider in refrigerator. Spices may be used in a tea ball.

title: hot cocoa mix
directions: Combine all ingredients, stirring well.
Store in covered container.
Serve 1/3 cup and 1 cup boiling water for each serving.
Stir and it's delicious.
Makes 36 cups.

title: squash broccoli(heart healthy)
directions: Cook mushrooms in margarine in nonstick frypan.
Add remaining sliced ingredients, except grated lemon rind.
Cover; boil until vegetables are tender (about 10 minutes).
Drain and stir in lemon rind.

title: leftover turkey casserole
directions: Combine turkey, noodles, soup and water together.
Put into casserole dish with lid.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with cheese last 5 minutes of cooking time.

title: apple crisp
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.

Place rolled oats, flour, sugar, salt and cinnamon in a bowl and mix well with pastry blender or fork. Arrange peeled sliced apples in a buttered 2-quart baking dish. Spread oatmeal mixture on top and press down lightly.
Bake about 30 minutes or until topping is brown and apples are tender when tested with a fork.

title: almond roca cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream together the butter and sugars, then add the egg yolk, vanilla and flour.
Stir until mixed; it will make a stiff batter.
Spread into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake for 15 to 20 minutes.
Melt the chocolate bar (over water) and spread over hot baked dough.
Sprinkle walnuts. Finally, cool and cut into squares.

title: ed's chocolate pound cake
directions: Mix Crisco and sugar; add eggs one at a time. Add cocoa and milk; add flour, baking powder, salt and vanilla. Bake at 350° until done, about 1 hour and 35 minutes.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Mix
cocoa, cornstarch and sugar together.
Stir in hot water and margarine.
Beat in egg yolks and add vanilla.	Pour into baked pie shell.

title: chicken special
directions: Cook
celery and onions in a small amount of water with bouillon
cube or chicken broth.
Most of the liquid should be decreased.	Add soup, chicken and noodles.

title: eggless spice cake
directions: Bring to boil the sugar, water, margarine, raisins, cinnamon, allspice and cloves.
Cool, then add remaining ingredients.
Bake 45 minutes (or longer) at 350°.
May add nuts.

title: pig farmer cookies
directions: Cream butter; gradually add sugars.
Beat at medium speed with mixer.
Add eggs and beat well.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add to mixture.
Stir in oats and remaining ingredients.
Spoon on greased cookie sheet by tablespoon.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: cream of broccoli soup
directions: In a large saucepan, cook broccoli in 1 cup water with bouillon cubes until tender; do not drain.
Set aside.
Put milk, cheese cubes and flour into blender.
Cover and chop until well mixed.
Add to broccoli.
Add half and half.
Cook, stirring frequently over medium heat until mixture thickens slightly.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix beans, corn, salt and pepper.
Pour into a greased pan. Mix soup, cheese, onion and sour cream; pour over vegetables.
Add butter, crackers and almonds on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: impossible taco pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Lightly brown meat and onions; stir in taco seasoning.
Spray a 10-inch pie pan with Pam.
Pour mixture into pie pan.
Place green chilies over meat.
Mix together milk, eggs and Bisquick until very smooth.
Pour over meat.
Bake at 400° for 25 minutes.
Put cheese over cooked pie and let stand until melted or place in oven to melt cheese.
Garnish top with lettuce and tomatoes.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt margarine in pan.
Mix sugar, flour and milk to make a paste.
Pour into pan with margarine.
Cut up peaches and sweeten. Pour peaches over paste.
Cook at 425° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: corn dogs
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Dip each hot dog in separately, and drop into hot grease.

title: chicken paprika i
directions: Wash chicken and cut into size pieces desired. Saute onions in melted butter until brown. Dissolve bouillon cubes in boiling water. Add paprika, salt and chicken. Cover and cook over low heat until tender. Cook approximately 1 hour. Stir flour into sour cream. Pour slowly into hot liquid. Stir; cover and cook about 5 minutes. Serves 4.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add bananas and oil.
Mix flour with baking soda.
Add gradually until all mixed.
Add nuts and flavors.
Bake at 375° for 25 to 30 minutes. Put in several greased and floured pans.
Add coconut on top if desired.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. Grease a 13 x 9-inch glass pan. Remove 1/2 cup dry cake mix. Beat together cake mix, eggs, butter and sour cream for 2 minutes. Spread half of batter in pan. Stir together brown sugar, dry cake mix and cinnamon. Add to rest of batter. Mix well. Pour over top of batter in pan. Cook for 30 to 35 minutes. Stir powdered sugar, milk and vanilla. Poke holes in warm cake with fork. Pour glaze over top of warm cake. Cool for 1 hour before serving.

title: steak and mushrooms
directions: Brown steak, pour off grease.
Add onions, peppers and brown. Then add sherry, soup and mushrooms.
Simmer 30 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake a ready made pie crust for 10 minutes.
Sprinkle the first 4 ingredients into this.
Cool milk slightly, then beat together with eggs, salt, pepper and nutmeg. Pour custard mixture into the prepared crust with filling.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes or until the top is golden brown.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter casserole.
Sprinkle part of the crumbs to cover bottom of dish.
Mix other ingredients and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle more crumbs on top.
Dot with butter.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Add grated cheese the last five minutes.

title: oven barbecue chicken
directions: Heat all ingredients, except chicken. Place chicken in baking dish. Top with sauce. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 1 hour.

title: tuna barbecue
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Cook until mixture boils down, about 5 minutes.
Serve with slaw or onions.

title: nora's persimmon pudding
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Mix together remaining ingredients.
Mix dry ingredients into persimmon mixture.
Bake about 1 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°.
Serve with Lemon Sauce or frost with Cream Cheese Icing.

title: hawaiian barbecue sauce
directions: Combine pineapple and lemon juices, brown sugar, ketchup and mustard in a 4-cup glass measure.
Microwave, uncovered, on High for 4 to 5 minutes, stirring once.
Use half the sauce (without pineapple chunks) for basting.
Add pineapple chunks to remaining half of sauce.
Serve as condiment.
Makes 3/4 cup without pineapple chunks.

title: helen schram's two minute white frosting
directions: Combine all ingredients, except vanilla, in top of double boiler and cook over rapidly boiling water.
Beat with electric mixer on high until it stands in peaks, about 2 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla and continue to beat until right to spread.

title: texas beans
directions: In a large saucepan cook ground beef until well browned. Drain off fat. Add remaining ingredients together and bring to a boil. Reduce heat and simmer for 1 hour. Serve with cornbread or Doritos.

title: quiche
directions: Mix in bowl the butter, half and half and eggs.
Add salt and pepper. Blend with beater until fully mixed.
Add to egg mixture the cheese, green pepper, bacon, onion and mushrooms.
Mix with a large spoon until well blended.
Divide between two uncooked pie shells.
Cook at 375° for 45 minutes or until crust is brown.

title: cinnamon coffee cake loaf
directions: Combine flour, 1 cup sugar, baking powder and 1 1/2 teaspoons cinnamon.
In another bowl, combine eggs, buttermilk, oil and vanilla; stir this into dry ingredients just until smooth.
Pour half of the batter into a greased 9 x 5 x 3 loaf pan.
In small bowl, combine remaining sugar and cinnamon; stir in butter. Drizzle half over batter; cut through with a knife to swirl.
Top with remaining batter.
Drizzle with remaining cinnamon-sugar mixture.
Swirl with a knife.
Bake at 350° for 55 to 60 minutes or until done.
Cool for 10 minutes before removing from pan to wire rack.

title: fruit dip
directions: Cream together softened cream cheese and marshmallow creme. Add orange juice and a couple drops of red food coloring.
Good with watermelon, cantaloupe, pineapple, or apples.

title: five can casserole
directions: Mix together.
Place in buttered casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.
Quick and easy when in a hurry.

title: sea scallops
directions: Season	crackers
with seasonings.
Dip scallops in egg mixture, then in crumbs, coating thoroughly.
Arrange scallops on baking
sheet
in
a single layer.	Pour melted butter over all. Bake 15 minutes at 350°.

title: apple pizza
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut or rub in shortening until mixture is crumbly.
Add milk to make soft dough. Turn out on lightly floured board or pastry cloth.
Knead gently 30 seconds.
Roll out to a circle approximately 13-inches in diameter. Fit into 13-inch pizza pan or place on ungreased cookie sheet. Flute edge.
Brush with melted butter.
Arrange apple slices in successive rings on top of dough.
Mix together sugar, pecans, cinnamon (if desired) and orange rind.
Sprinkle evenly over apples.
Decorate with cherry halves (or red hots).
Bake in oven at 450° for 20 to 25 minutes or until apples are tender and edge of pizza is golden brown.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: easy pineapple cake
directions: Make cake mix as directed on box (this makes a smaller cake than regular cake mixes).
Bake 15 minutes at 350°.
Let cool. Mix pudding, milk and cream cheese.
Spread on cake.
Top with pineapple.

title: stella's pecan pie
directions: Mix together, adding pecans last.
Bake in a 9-inch unbaked pie crust at 375° for 10 minutes.
Lower temperature to 300° and continue to bake approximately 30 minutes or until firm.

title: sausage pancakes
directions: Crumble sausage in a skillet until cooked, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry salad
directions: Add cream cheese and frozen strawberries; add approximately 3 tablespoons chopped nuts.
Refrigerate.

title: sweet and sour garlic pickles
directions: In a roasting pan, pour ingredients over pickles; stir gently. Leave for 48 hours, stirring several times a day.
Put in sterile jars.
Seal with tops.
No boiling.
Very good.

title: cherry cobbler
directions: Melt butter in 11 x 7-inch Pyrex.
Mix sugar, flour, milk and baking powder.
Pour batter evenly over melted butter.
Spoon cherry pie filling over batter.
Bake at 350° for 50 minutes. Serve with ice cream.

title: fudge
directions: Combine sugar, oleo and milk in heavy pan.
Bring to a full, rolling boil, stirring constantly.
Continue boiling 5 minutes over medium heat, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and stir in chocolate until melted.
Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla.
Beat by hand until well blended.
Pour in greased 13 x 9-inch pan.
Cut when cool.

title: applesauce nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda, salt, cinnamon and nutmeg on sheet of waxed paper; set aside.

title: sue sue's casserole
directions: Brown meat and onions, drain.
In a large mixing bowl, mix peas, corn, soups and sour cream.
Add noodles and meat; mix well. Pour into a large casserole or two medium casserole dishes.
Top with cheese and bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: baked steak
directions: Mix salt and pepper together with flour. Dredge steak in seasoned flour (save excess flour) and add to hot oil. Brown on both sides and put in 9 x 13 baking dish. Add 3 tablespoons of saved flour to pan drippings (add more oil if needed). Cook until starts to brown.

title: pecan pralines
directions: Pour buttermilk, sugar and soda in large pot. Mixture will bubble up a lot. Stir until completely mixed and place over medium to low heat. Let cook until it reaches soft ball stage. Stir while cooking. The mixture will turn a brownish yellow color. When mixture reaches soft ball stage when dropping in cold water, remove from heat. Add pecans, vanilla and butter. Beat briskly by hand until mixture becomes glossy and starts to get thick. Spoon on greased wax paper. Let cool.

title: glorified hamburger balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Let stand a short time.
Form into balls, roll in flour and brown in frying pan.
Place in casserole and pour can of mushroom soup and soup can filled with milk over the meatballs.
Bake at 350°
for 45 minutes.

title: slop dogs
directions: Combine all ingredients except the bread in a saucepan on the stove top.
Heat, and add torn bits of bread into mixture and mix well.

title: chicken wings
directions: Mix last 4 ingredients and pour over chicken wings.
Marinate a few hours or overnight.
Bake in a 350° oven for about 1 hour. Also great when prebaked for 1/2 to 3/4 hour and then barbecued on grill, basting frequently.

title: corn bread
directions: Mix all together.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake at 400° for 30 minutes, or until done.

title: spinach dip
directions: Combine all and mix well. Refrigerate to blend flavors. Serve with raw veggies, such as carrot, celery, cucumber and crackers. Makes 3 1/2 cups.

title: diabetic spicy iced tea
directions: Combine tea bags, lemon, Sweet 'N Low, cinnamon and cloves in a heatproof pitcher.
Pour in water.
Let stand 1 hour, until cooled.
Remove tea bags.
Chill in refrigerator.
Strain before serving.

title: jalapeno cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Spray 9 x 13-inch baking pan with vegetable cooking spray.
Place pan in oven to warm.
Mix all ingredients except cheese in a large bowl.
Pour half of batter into warm, prepared pan.
Sprinkle half of the cheese over batter. Spread remaining batter over mixture and top with rest of cheese. Bake for 35 minutes.
Yields 16 servings.

title: red cake icing
directions: Cook flour and milk until thick. Then cool until thoroughly cold. Cream until fluffy, granulated sugar and butter. Add vanilla. Add to first mixture, but don't beat too long, just enough to mix together thoroughly. Frost cake. Keep cake refrigerated.

title: sticky fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a saucepan, over low heat, melt the butter.
Add the sugars; stir constantly until they dissolve and the mixture comes to a boil.
Cook for 10 minutes.
Add the eggs, the flour sifted with the baking powder and the extract; beat vigorously until the batter is smooth.

title: pineapple cake
directions: Make cake as directions indicate or make a cake from scratch. Let cake cool; punch holes in top and spoon pineapple over cake (juice and all).
Spread icing (recipe following) over pineapple.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix stuffing with hot water.
Let soften.
Break sausage into small bits.
Add to stuffing mix.
Stir in egg.
Roll into bite-size balls.
Place on cookie sheet.
Cover with foil and cook in a 325° oven for 10 to 15 minutes.
Uncover and continue baking until brown, about 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cheese ravioli-asparagus pie
directions: Cook ravioli according to directions and drain well.
Heat oven to 375°.
Grease a 9-inch pie pan.
Beat eggs with a fork and stir in undiluted soup.
Mix in pepper.
Stir until blended. Cover bottom of prepared pie pan with a single layer of ravioli and 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Top with zucchini, tomatoes, basil and Mozzarella.
Repeat layers, then top with the remaining 1/2 of the soup mixture.
Bake 45 minutes until set in the middle.
Cool 15 minutes before serving.

title: oatmeal chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together the first 3 ingredients.
Beat in the next 2 ingredients.
Mix next 3 ingredients and add to creamed mixture. Add last 4 ingredients.
Drop by teaspoonful onto cookie sheet. Bake in a 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: family meat loaf(microwave)
directions: Combine brown sugar, tomato sauce and mustard.	Combine beef, onion,
cracker
crumbs, eggs, salt and pepper.
Add 1/2 of the tomato sauce mixture and stir until well mixed.
Place in micro-proof dish.
Pour remaining sauce over meat.	Cook on High 12 to 14 minutes or until done.

title: ritz fruit cake
directions: Heat milk in double boiler.
Add marshmallows and heat until melted.
Pour over crackers, fruit and nuts; mix well.
Press in loaf pans and refrigerate.

title: monkey bread
directions: Combine butter and brown sugar in saucepan and melt it.
Cut biscuits in 1/4 pieces.
Mix sugar and cinnamon in bowl.
Drop biscuits in cinnamon and sugar.
Shake and cover.
Drop biscuits into angel food pan.
Pour melted butter and brown sugar over biscuits.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: quick apple crisp #1
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Place apples in lightly buttered 9 x 13-inch casserole (preferably a baking stone).
Combine sugar, cinnamon and nutmeg; sprinkle over apples.
Sprinkle dry cake mix over apple and sugar mixture.
Evenly drizzle melted butter over top of cake mix.
Bake for 35 to 40 minutes until lightly browned. Cool slightly before serving.
Top with ice cream, if desired. Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: jenny lynn drink
directions: Mix all ingredients and chill.
Makes 30 drinks.

title: chicken nuggets
directions: Beat egg with milk (just like making scrambled eggs). Cut chicken into nugget size or strips.
Dip into flour, egg/milk mixture, then bread crumbs.

title: miniature cheese cakes
directions: Beat eggs well; add cream cheese a little at a time.
Add sugar slowly, then add vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Mix the graham cracker crumbs, soft butter or margarine and sugar together.
Put paper cups into cupcake pans.
Press down 1 1/2 tablespoons of crumbs in each cup.
Add 1 1/2 tablespoons of cream cheese spread.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes in 350° oven.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Saute onion, then add the remaining ingredients. Simmer.

title: italian spaghetti casserole
directions: Place cooked and drained spaghetti in a buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour the 15 ounce can of tomato sauce over spaghetti.
Brown ground beef and onion with oregano.
Drain and sprinkle over spaghetti and tomato sauce.
Layer mushrooms, pepperoni and olives. Pour 8 ounce can of tomato sauce over all.
Sprinkle with grated cheese and bake at 350° until hot and bubbly, about 30 minutes.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Add lemon juice and rind to milk.
Add egg yolks and stir well. Pour into pie shell.
Beat egg whites.
Add cream of tartar to eggs.
Add sugar.
Put on pie filling.
Bake at 350 degrees for about 20 minutes.

title: cheese spread
directions: In
double boiler, combine evaporated milk, beaten egg, flour and
sugar.
Cook,	stirring until hot.
Add cheese and cook stirring occasionally, until smooth.
Stir in hard-cooked eggs, onion
and	pimento,
if desired.
Remove from heat and cool completely.
Stir in vinegar and transfer to jars.	Store covered in refrigerator.

title: anytime granola
directions: In medium bowl, mix well all ingredients, except raisins. Spread in large cooking pan.
Bake in 325° oven, stirring twice, 20 to 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and stir in raisins.
Cool in pan on rack.
Refrigerate in airtight container for up to 2 weeks. Freeze for longer storage.
Makes 4 1/2 cups.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Line 8 x 8 pan with foil; lightly grease with vegetable spray. Sprinkle peanuts over bottom of pan.
Put milk and sugar in a medium heavy-bottomed saucepan fitted with a candy thermometer. Boil over medium heat, stirring to keep from sticking. Cook until the mixture reaches 240° (soft-boil stage).

Remove from heat. Gently place butter, peanut butter and vanilla in pan. Do not stir. Let mixture cool down 5 minutes, then beat vigorously with a spoon or the flat beater of a stationary mixer until dense and smooth. Turn fudge out into prepared pan. Spread evenly. Let set 45 minutes. Will last up to 3 weeks in refrigerator.

title: beef roast
directions: Heat roasting pan; put oil in and brown roast on all sides. Cut onion in slices and put on top of roast.
Put enough water to make gravy.
Take 2 tablespoons flour and dissolve in warm water and put in roaster to thicken gravy.
Cook until tender as you want it.

title: orange slush
directions: Combine all ingredients in blender.
Blend until smooth. Serves 4.

title: caramels
directions: Bring to a boil.
Gradually add 2 cups whipping cream.
Keep mixture boiling over low heat.
Cook until medium firm ball forms when tested in cold water.
Add vanilla.
Pour into buttered 9 x 13-inch pan.
When cool and firm, cut in small pieces and wrap in waxed paper.

title: goulash
directions: Brown ground beef and onion; drain well.
Cook noodles according to package; drain well.
Mix meat and noodles together. Add spaghetti sauce, garlic salt, salt and pepper.
Mix well. Simmer over low heat until hot.
Stir frequently to prevent sticking.

title: mrs. field's chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter, brown sugar, sugar and eggs.
Add flour, oatmeal and soda.
Mix well.
Stir in chocolate chips, Hershey bar and chopped nuts.
Roll in balls the size of a golf ball and bake at 375° for 6 minutes.
Do not overbake!
(Received from a Tupperware party.)
This recipe can be cut in half.

title: spicy thai peanut dip
directions: In bowl, whisk peanut butter, vegetable broth and soy sauce until smooth.
Stir in remaining ingredients.
Makes 1 1/2 cups.

title: crabbies
directions: Mix first 6 ingredients.
Spread on 12 muffin halves. Cut each half into 6 pie shaped wedges.
Put under broiler until bubbly hot.
May freeze before broiling.

title: diabetic applesauce cookies
directions: Sift together flour, salt, baking soda, cinnamon, nutmeg and cloves.
Then beat together egg, margarine and liquid sweetener. Add dry ingredients and 1 cup applesauce alternately into the egg mixture.
Mix well after each addition.
Add 1/2 cup raisins and 1 cup All-Bran cereal.

title: spinach potatoes au gratin
directions: In 2-quart microwave safe dish, combine potatoes and water. Cover and microwave on High for 8 to 9 minutes or until potatoes are tender, stirring twice.
Drain and set aside.
In large microwave safe bowl, heat butter on High until melted (30 seconds). Add onion.
Microwave, uncovered, 1 to 2 minutes or until tender. Whisk in flour until blended.
Gradually stir in the milk.
Cook, uncovered, on High for 2 1/2 minutes; stir.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer, stirring every minute or until sauce is thickened and bubbly.
Stir in cheese and salt.
Pour over potatoes.
Add spinach and pimientos; mix well.
Microwave uncovered on High for 2 to 3 minutes or until heated through, stirring once.
Sprinkle with bacon.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: mamaw's chicken pie
directions: Boil chicken in large deep pot in salted water until tender. Remove bones and skin; cut into bite sized pieces and place in a well-greased 3-quart casserole (Pyrex 9 x 13-inch dish is ideal).

title: easy fudge
directions: Mix all ingredients but chips.
Boil 6 minutes.
Remove from heat and stir in chips.
Stir well until chocolate chips melt. Pour into pan.
Cut in squares.

title: mintie's yeast bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Mix shortening, sugar, salt; then add boiling water.
Add beaten eggs.
Alternate adding flour and yeast mixture.
Let double in size and use as a loaf or rolls. Shape and let rise again.
Bake in 350° oven for 50 minutes for loaf or 30 minutes for rolls.

title: peanut butter brownies
directions: In large bowl, combine peanut butter, margarine and sugars; beat until blended.
Beat in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla. Stir together flour, baking powder and salt.
Gradually stir this into peanut butter mixture until well blended.
Stir in 1/2 package of morsels.
Spread batter evenly in greased 13 x 9 x2-inch pan.
Sprinkle remaining morsels on top of batter.

title: gourmet cinnamon coffee
directions: Prepare coffee as usual in coffeemaker.
Sprinkle cinnamon over coffee grounds.
Gourmet coffee at a fraction of the price.

title: barbecue sauce
directions: Mix and bring to a boil.
Good on brisket.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Cook broccoli, strain and mix in rest of ingredients except for stuffing and butter.
Mix stuffing in melted butter and top casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until topping is brown.

title: geanine's butter crunchies
directions: Preheat oven to 300°.
Melt butter in a pan.
Add sugar and mix until butter is gone from pan sides.
Add oats and stir until coated with butter mixture.
Spread mixture evenly in a jelly roll pan.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes until lightly browned.
Remove from oven and sprinkle with chips.
Return to oven for 3 minutes to melt chips.
Spread over base.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Wait 5 minutes. Cut into squares.

title: peach cobbler
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, melt margarine, then add peaches. In a mixing bowl, combine sugar, flour and milk; mix well.
Pour mixture over fruit.
Bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: quick lasagna pie
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Layer cottage cheese and Parmesan cheese in plate.
In a bowl, mix hamburger, herbs, paste and 1/2 of the Mozzarella cheese.
Spoon on top.

title: fried cabbage
directions: Fry bacon until crisp.
Remove and set aside.
Slice onion in grease and then cabbage and then slice up tomato on top of cabbage. Add enough water to cook cabbage done.
When done crumble up bacon on top of cabbage.

title: orange sunshine cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add salt, orange juice and vanilla; beat well.
Add flour and beat well.

title: holiday wreath(makes a beautiful centerpiece for christmas)
directions: Combine marshmallows, butter, vanilla and food coloring (2 teaspoons is correct) in top of a double boiler.
Heat over water until marshmallows and butter are melted, stirring frequently. Gradually stir in cornflakes.
With hands, shape into a wreath. Decorate with red candied cherries and silver dragees.
Makes one wreath.

title: rio grande quesadillas
directions: In skillet, combine chicken, taco spices and water.
Bring to boil; reduce heat and simmer, uncovered, 15 minutes.
Stir in refried beans.
On 1/2 side of each tortilla, spread 1/3 cup of chicken and bean mixture.
Layer 1/4 each of cheese and green onions.
Fold tortilla in half.
In large skillet, heat a small amount of oil and quickly fry folded tortilla on each side until slightly crisp.
Repeat with each folded tortilla.
Cut each quesadilla in quarters and serve with chunky salsa.

title: crock-pot roast
directions: Salt and pepper roast. Brown your roast good to get the grease out and cook over low heat until tender. When you can stick a fork in it or through it or when it's falling apart some, it's done. Take roast out of pot. Leave pot on stove. Have some flour in a bowl mixed with water to make gravy. Mix flour and water good, then add to what's in pot where roast cooked. Mix well and let simmer for awhile. This makes very good gravy and can be served over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: perfect white bread
directions: Combine milk, shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm. Sprinkle yeast in lukewarm water; stir to dissolve.
Add yeast and 2 cups flour to milk mixture.
Beat with electric mixer at medium speed until smooth, about 2 minutes, or beat with spoon until batter is smooth.
Gradually add enough remaining flour to make a soft dough that leaves the side of the bowl.

Turn out onto floured surface; knead until smooth and satiny, about 10 minutes. Place dough in lightly greased bowl; turn over to grease top. Cover; let rise in warm place until doubled, about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: patio tuna squares
directions: Mix Bisquick and water.
Pat dough up sides and on bottom of a 9 x 9-inch greased pan.
Mix rest of ingredients and spread over dough.
You can add additional cheese on the top.

title: capellini with spicy tomato sauce
directions: Heat large pot of water to boiling for pasta.
Heat oil in large skillet over medium heat.
Add onion, garlic and jalapeno; cook, stirring frequently, until softened, about 3 minutes.
Add tomatoes and cook until heated through, about 5 minutes.
Add coriander, cumin, 3/4 teaspoon salt and the pepper.
Stir once and remove from heat.

title: great grandmother's sugar cookies
directions: Mix and make into big ball.
Roll out and cut.
Bake at 375 degrees 10 - 12 minutes.

title: biscuits
directions: Heat oven to 450°.
Measure flour, baking powder and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening thoroughly until mixture looks like meal. Stir in almost all milk.
If dough is pliable, add just enough milk to a soft, puffy, easy to roll dough.
Round up dough on lightly floured, dough cloth-covered board.
Roll 20 to 25 times about 1/2 minute.
Roll 1/2-inch thick.
Cut with floured biscuit cutter. Place on ungreased baking sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.

title: oriental cashew crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine first 3 ingredients in 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Set aside.
Combine remaining 4 ingredients in small bowl.
Pour over cereal mixture.
Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes.
Cool and enjoy.
Makes 10 cups.

title: chocolate candy surprise
directions: In saucepan, boil sugar and margarine for 1 min.
Put crackers in bottom of 9x13-inch pan.
Pour sugar mixture over crackers. Bake at 350° for 5 min.
Remove from oven, shut oven OFF.
Spread chocolate chips over crackers.
Put pan back in oven (Heat Off) for 3 min.
Spread chocolate evenly over crackers.
Sprinkle with chopped walnuts.
Let cool and cut into pieces.

title: p.b. and fudge ice cream pie
directions: Mix peanut butter and honey.
Stir mixture into ice cream. Spoon half of ice cream mixture into crust.
Sprinkle with half of nuts.
Drizzle 4 ounces of fudge sauce over nuts.
Spoon in remaining ice cream mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining nuts. Drizzle 2 ounces fudge sauce over nuts.
Freeze overnight. Garnish with Cool Whip and additional fudge sauce, if desired.

title: brunch oven omelet
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Heat margarine in rectangular baking dish (13 x 9 x 2-inch) in oven until melted.
Tilt dish to coat bottom. Beat eggs, sour cream, milk and salt until blended.
Stir in onions. Pour into dish.
Bake 35 minutes or until eggs are set but moist.
Yields 12 servings, 135 calories per serving.

title: wild duck pot roasted
directions: Rub duck with salt and pepper in cavity.
Put enough oil in pot to brown duck on all sides.
Add water, onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook until duck is tender.
You may need to add more water as duck cooks.
When duck is cooked, remove and thicken gravy.

title: sausage balls
directions: Mix sausage and Bisquick.
Melt cheese in double boiler.
Mix well with sausage and Bisquick.
Shape into balls.
Bake until brown.

title: bean dip
directions: Mix together all ingredients; chill for at least 1 to 2 hours before serving.
Use with crackers of your choice.

title: shrimp toast
directions: Cut crusts from bread.
With 2-inch fluted round cookie cutter, cut some circles from bread slices.
Cut remaining bread into 1 1/2-inch triangles and 2 x 1-inch pieces to make 20 cutouts in all.
In blender, blend bread trimmings to make 1/2 cup crumbs. In 1-quart saucepan, melt butter with thyme.
With pastry brush, brush cutouts with butter mixture.
Place on cookie sheet; broil 2 minutes or just until golden.
Mix shrimp, bread crumbs, cheese, mayonnaise and salt; spread some on each cutout.
Broil 10 minutes, about 7 to 9 inches from source of heat.
Garnish. Makes 20.

title: aunt hilda's rhubarb pie
directions: Mix rhubarb, pineapple, tapioca, sugar and egg yolks.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 40 to 50 minutes.
Cool on rack.

title: skillet
directions: Brown ground meat and drain off grease.
Add tomatoes, mushrooms and soup mix.
Cover and simmer.
Saute bell pepper, onion and celery and add to mixture.
Continue simmering until tender.
Serve over rice.

title: chili
directions: Cook ground beef and onion in skillet, drain fat; add ketchup, water, tomatoes, chili beans, salt & chili powder to taste.
Cook on low for 30 minutes.

title: hot mulled cider
directions: Mix together in saucepan. Heat to boiling.
Turn fire to low simmer.
Simmer 15 minutes and serve.

title: brown rice
directions: Preheat oven to 375.
Boil water and put in 1/2 stick of margarine in and stir.
Then add all of the other ingredients. Stir and bake for 45 minutes at 375 in a casserole dish.

title: swedish kringler
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Cut butter into flour.
Sprinkle with 2 tablespoons water over mixture; mix.
Round into ball; divide in half.
On ungreased baking sheet, pat each half into strip 12 x 3-inches; should be 3-inches apart.
Heat 1/2 cup butter and 1 cup water to rolling boil in medium saucepan.
Remove from heat and quickly stir in almond extract and 1 cup flour.
Stir vigorously over low heat, until mixture forms a ball, about 1 minute.
Remove from heat.
Beat in eggs, all at once, until smooth and glossy. Divide in half; spread each half evenly over strips.

title: raisin pie
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Combine syrup, eggs, sugar, butter, salt, lemon rind, allspice and nutmeg.
Mix well.
Add raisins and nuts.
Pour into pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes.
Reduce heat to 350° and bake 30 to 35 minutes longer.
Filling solidifies further on cooling.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: coconut custard pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Put all ingredients into blender, except coconut.
Blend until smooth and well mixed.
Pour into a greased 9-inch pie plate and top with coconut.
Bake at 350° until custard sets, about 30 minutes.
Serves 8.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook (boil) chicken.
Prepare Rice-A-Roni as directed on box. Preheat oven to 350°.
Cook chicken and debone.
Pour Rice-A-Roni in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Tear chicken apart and mix into rice. Prepare soup as directed on can and pour over rice and chicken. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: chocolate pecans
directions: Put butter in an iron frying pan.
Put pecans in melted butter and toast.
Sprinkle in salt and stir real good.
Dip in melted chocolate.

title: chickpea dip(hommous bi tahini)
directions: Combine all ingredients in a food processor or blender, adding only enough of the saved liquid to meet your satisfaction (the more liquid added, the thinner the dip).
Blend for 2 to 3 minutes to a smooth paste.
Place in a small platter or shallow bowl.
If preferred, sprinkle olive oil on top and garnish with parsley sprigs and lemon wedges.

title: make ahead fruit salad
directions: Blend together.
Add nuts.
Put into refrigerator until serving time, then serve on a lettuce leaf.
Top each serving with a red or green cherry.
Best when made the night before.

title: delicious sweet corn bread
directions: Mix and bake in iron skillet.

title: carrot, zucchini and apple muffins
directions: Mix all ingredients in large bowl except eggs and oil.
Beat the eggs and oil in another large bowl.
Stir flour mixture into eggs.
Spoon into greased muffin cups and bake at 375° for about 25 minutes.
Makes about 24.

title: grandma ruth's buckeyes
directions: Mix together the powdered sugar, peanut butter, margarine and Rice Krispies.
Form into small balls.

title: graham cookies
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Bring to a boil sugar and butter; add crackers.
Bake 5 minutes.
Cool 4 minutes; remove from pan.

title: coconut sheet cake
directions: Cook cake as directed.
While still hot, punch as many holes in it as you can with a fork.
Mix cup of milk and 1/2 cup of sugar; heat to boiling point.
Spoon over cake.
Let cool, then spread with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Refrigerate overnight.
Serve at room temperature.

title: green bean bundles
directions: Spray dish with Pam. Roll your whole green beans (about 4 or 5) in 1/2 slice of bacon. Use toothpick to keep together. Lay in dish. Add salt, pepper and garlic (minced) on top of bundles. Pour butter and sugar over them. Bake in 350° oven 45 minutes, covered, then uncover and cook an additional 15 minutes.

title: cowboy cookies
directions: Cream together the sugars, eggs and shortening.
Sift together the flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Add to first mixture. Fold in oats, chocolate chips and pecans.
Shape into balls.
Bake on greased tin for 12 minutes at 350°.
Makes 12 to 14 dozen.

title: italian beef
directions: Brown chuck roast.
Mix remaining ingredients.
Pour over roast.
Bake, covered, 3 hours at 350°.

title: ham (or sausage) and cheese strata
directions: Spread margarine or butter thinly on one side of slices of bread. Cut off crusts or leave on. Line a Pyrex pan with bread, buttered side down.
Scatter cheese evenly over the bread, then chopped ham, then onion. Top with bread slices, buttered side up. Mix beaten eggs, milk and seasonings.
Save 1/4 of this for tomorrow at baking time.
Pour 3/4 of the liquid evenly over layered mixture. Cover and refrigerate overnight or at least 8 hours.
Longer is okay.
Pour saved liquid evenly over top. Bake at 325° for about 45 minutes.
Remove from oven.
Loosen cover to let steam escape, 10 minutes.
Without the top layer of bread, it is like quiche.

title: tropical island punch
directions: Combine concentrates in large container.
Add water and sugar. Stir until sugar dissolves.
Refrigerate, covered, until chilled. Add ginger ale.
Pour over ice in punch bowl. With wooden picks, attach maraschino cherries to center of pineapple slices. Float pineapple, banana and lime slices on punch.
Makes about 28 (5 ounce) servings.
