title: nutty cole slaw
directions: Chop all ingredients and mix together with mayonnaise. Chill.

title: fried vegetables
directions: I fry all of this in a large iron skillet with hot oil.
Use salt and pepper to suit your own taste.

title: punch bowl cake
directions: Cut cake
layer in half.
Crumble one half in bottom of punch bowl.
Mix	together
pineapple,
pecans and cherry pie filling. Layer half of this mixture on cake crumbs.

title: pfeffernesa
directions: Bring sugar, shortening and honey to a rolling boil and cool. Add the remainder of the ingredients and mix well.
Chill for easier handling.
Roll in balls and bake in 350° oven for 8 to 10 minutes.
Dredge in powdered sugar while still warm.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs, milk and apples.
Add dry ingredients.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 40 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage and rice bake
directions: Cook sausage in a skillet until brown, stirring to crumble. Drain; set aside.
Combine rice and 1 1/2 cups cheese.
Spread mixture into a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking dish.
Sprinkle with sausage.
Combine eggs and next 4 ingredients; mix well.
Pour mixture over sausage.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese and bake an additional 5 minutes.

title: raisin cookies
directions: Cook raisins and water until half the water is left.
Cream oleo, sugar, egg and vanilla together.
Add flour, baking powder and baking soda to creamed mixture.
Add raisins and juice.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.

title: chinese coffeecake
directions: Add sugar to beaten eggs. Continue to beat and add flour and baking powder.
Mix in milk. Pour into oiled pan.
Bake at 350 degrees for 30 minutes
After taking from the oven, poke holes into cake. Melt margarine and pour over cake.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and cinnamon.

title: almond fudge topped shortbread
directions: Heat oven to 350°. Grease 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In mixer bowl, beat butter, sugar and salt until fluffy. Mix in flour. With floured hands, press into prepared pan. Bake 20 minutes or until lightly browned. In heavy saucepan over low heat, melt chocolate chips with sweetened condensed milk, stirring constantly, until chips are melted. Stir in almond extract. Spread evenly over shortbread. Sprinkle with almonds; press down firmly. Refrigerate 3 hours or until firm. Cut into bars. Store covered at room temperature. Enjoy!!

title: cinnamon and brown sugar butter
directions: Place softened butter or margarine in a small bowl. Blend with fork or hand mixer. Add sugar, nutmeg and cinnamon. Beat all ingredients until fluffy.

title: raisin bran muffins
directions: Empty box of Raisin Bran into large bowl.
Pour buttermilk over it.
Let soak 1 hour.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients together.
Roll into balls.
Place on cookie sheet in freezer to get cold.
Melt chocolate chips and wax together in top of double boiler.
Use toothpicks to dip peanut butter balls. Dry on wax paper.

title: salad deluxe
directions: Combine lettuce, avocado, drained oranges and onion.
Make dressing of remaining ingredients, adding oil one tablespoon at a time.
Toss combined ingredients with dressing.
Any remaining dressing can be used on other kinds of salads.

title: crabmeat salad
directions: Flake crabmeat; add to pasta, carrots and onion.
Mix in Miracle Whip to moisten.
Refrigerate.
If mayo is used, add 2 tablespoons wine vinegar.

title: sweet-and-sour pork kabobs
directions: In a saucepan cook carrots, covered, in a small amount of boiling water for 8 minutes; drain well.
Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
Cut pineapple slices into quarters; set aside.

title: lemon pound cake
directions: Cream butter, sugar, Crisco and eggs together.
Add remaining ingredients.
Beat vigorously.
Bake 1 1/2 hours at 325°.
This is a big cake and good!

title: polish mistakes
directions: Brown ground beef and sausage in a pan. Drain off fat. Mix with cheese. Spread mixture on rye party bread. Bake at 350°. This recipe can be frozen.

title: spinach tortilla roll-ups
directions: Combine dressing mix with sour cream and mayonnaise.
Add the rest of ingredients; mix well.
Roll up tight in plastic wrap. Secure with toothpicks.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Slice in 3/4-inch widths.
Serve on toothpicks.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream sugar and butter.
Add remaining ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake for 45 to 50 minutes in a 350° oven.

title: brown sugar cookies
directions: Mix and bake at 400° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: crescent cookies
directions: Dissolve yeast into scalded milk (cooled) and add sugar; set aside.
Mix butter, flour, sugar and well-beaten egg yolks.
Add to yeast mixture and mix until it clings together.
Form into balls.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: pineapple raspberry punch
directions: Chill ingredients, then combine in punch bowl

title: buttermilk pie(tastes like pecan pie, without the nuts)
directions: Beat sugars and oleo. Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well. Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 40 - 45 minutes.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs in bowl until frothy.
Add sugar, oil and vanilla; beat until thick.
Add dry ingredients alternately with zucchini and nuts.
Bake in 2 (8 x 4 x 3-inch) pans at 350° for 1 hour.

title: lasagna logs
directions: In baking dish cook the sausage in 350° oven until almost done (approximately 30 minutes).
Remove and cool.
Slit sausage lengthwise and stuff with Mozzarella cheese. Wrap each sausage in lasagna noodle and secure with toothpick.
Place back in baking dish and cover with sauce and Romano cheese.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Remove toothpicks before serving.

title: porcupine meatballs
directions: Combine meat, rice, egg, parsley, onion, salt, pepper and 1/4 cup Hunt's Italian tomato sauce.
Mix thoroughly.
Shape into 1 1/2-inch balls.
Place in skillet or large boiler.
Mix remaining sauce, water and Worcestershire.
Pour over meatballs.
Bring to a boil; reduce heat, cover and simmer about 40 minutes.
If you do not get pan too hot before covering, you do not have to stir. Best with deer burger.

title: lime cottage cheese jello
directions: Dissolve jello in water.
Add pineapple juice.
Let chill until mixture starts to thicken, then add rest of ingredients. Mix well.
Pour into mold or dish and chill until firm.

title: hot beef-mushroom appetizer
directions: In a skillet, saute onions in butter until tender. Stir in cream cheese until smooth. Add mushrooms, beef, Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder; mix well. Spoon into an ungreased 9 inch pie plate. Bake at 375° for 15-20 minutes. Serve warm with crackers or rye bread.

title: pecan pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Stir in other ingredients, except pecans.
Pour batter into 9 inch uncooked pie crust.
Sprinkle pecans on top. Bake at 375° until firm, about 40 to 45 minutes.

title: hamburger hot dish
directions: Brown meat in pan with onion.
Add celery, do not overcook, celery should be crunchy.
Drain off excess fat.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in casserole at 375° for 45 minutes.
Yield: 6 servings.
Carbohydrate 24 g, protein 15 g, fat 27 g, calories 399.
One serving = 2 meat low-fat exchange, 1 bread starch exchange, 1 vegetable exchange, 4 fat exchange.

title: kielbasa and pineapple
directions: Cut kielbasa into chunk pieces. Add brown sugar and pineapple. Heat in crock-pot on medium heat for about 3 hours. Serve with toothpicks.

title: fried phillipine rice
directions: Scramble eggs in butter.
Fry bacon.
Fry cabbage, carrots, onion and garlic.
Season; add rice.
Simmer until done.

title: cold cream of cucumber soup
directions: Boil milk, onion and bay leaf, then leave 10 minutes to infuse.
Peel cucumber.
Slice in half lengthwise; remove seeds. Slice into chunks; blanch 2 minutes, then drain.
Melt butter; add cucumber, sugar, salt and pepper.
Cover; cook 15 minutes.
Add stock and chopped potato; cook further 15 to 20 minutes.
Rub through a sieve or liquify, then chill.
Serve cold with cucumber slices and a swirl of cream in each bowl to garnish.

title: cheese ball-beach balls
directions: Let cream cheese soften for 30 minutes on countertop.
In small bowl, mix softened cream cheese and Cheddar cheese.
Mash the cheeses together with a fork until well blended.
Stir in sunflower nuts.
Shape cheese mixture into 1-inch balls.

title: chicken and tortilla dumpling
directions: Boil chicken until tender; cool and debone.
Cut tortillas in about 2-inch pieces.
Bring broth to a boil and add chicken.
Drop in the tortilla pieces; add milk.
Continue to boil for 6 minutes. Cover and let stand until ready to eat.

title: microwave quickie fudge
directions: Blend together confectioners sugar and cocoa in 8 x 8 x 2-inch glass dish.
Pour in milk.
Place butter on top.
Heat in microwave on High for 2 minutes or until butter is melted.
Stir well to mix ingredeints.
Add vanilla and nuts.
Stir until blended.
Place in freezer for 20 minutes or in refrigerator for 1 hour.
Chill.
Cut into 1-inch squares.
Store in airtight containers.

title: italian chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onion and garlic in shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Add 2 cups water and cook slowly at least 30 minutes.
Boil fryer.
Debone.
Add to sauce and simmer about 10 minutes.
Cook large package of spaghetti in water where chicken was cooked; drain.
Add sauce and mix well.

title: pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix crumbs with 1 tablespoon sugar. Combine crumbs and margarine.
Press into bottom of spring-form pan and chill.

title: fast fruit punch
directions: Combine all ingredients in punch bowl. Add ice and fresh fruit garnish. A pretty purple color. Makes 40 servings.

title: sweet potato-currant mini bundt cakes
directions: Sweet potato puree provides the moistness in these individual nonfat cakes.
Mini Bundt pans, each containing 6 Bundt shaped cups, are available in many cookware stores.
(By Times Food Stylists.)
Remove peel from oranges in large strips.
Remove any white pith on orange.
Finely chop peel in food processor along with currants.
Stir in juice from oranges, sweet potato puree, milk and egg substitute.
Sift together cake flour, 1 cup sugar, baking soda and salt.
Quickly stir sweet potato mixture into dry ingredients.
Divide batter among 9 mini Bundt nonstick cups sprayed with nonstick vegetable spray.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until cakes test done.
Let cool in pan 5 minutes. Remove to wire rack.

title: black coffee cake
directions: Sift together the first 5 ingredients.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add oil, coffee and milk; mix thoroughly.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: sour cream pound cake
directions: Bring butter, eggs and sour cream to room temperature.
Grease and lightly flour an 8 x 4 x 2-inch or 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan. In a bowl, stir together flour, baking powder and soda; set aside.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix corn, egg, cream, salt and pepper in mixing bowl.
Add celery, onion and green pepper.
Pour into greased baking dish in layers with cheese, butter and cracker crumbs, ending with layer of corn mixture.
Top with 1/2 cup buttered bread crumbs, if desired. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Makes 6 servings.

title: aunt joan's fiesta salad
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Chill 2 hours.
Serve for a light, summery dessert.

title: easy supper(kids' recipe)
directions: Prepare potatoes according to directions.
Add ham and peas. Bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: barbecue sandwiches
directions: Simmer until thick, about 1 hour.
Add can of corned beef and heat.
Serve on hamburger rolls.

title: blueberry dream whip
directions: Mix graham cracker crumbs, sugar and butter.
Mix cream cheese, Dream Whip, cold milk and sugar.
Using a 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, layer as follows:
Graham cracker mixture, Dream Whip mixture, blueberries, Dream Whip mixture and graham cracker mixture.
Let stand in refrigerator overnight.

title: irish scones
directions: Sieve flour, salt and soda together in large bowl.
Cut in margarine and rub in until like crumbs.
Add sugar and enough milk to make a soft ball together with egg.
Turn onto floured board and lightly knead a few times.
Roll out and cut into round cakes or cut with round cookie cutter.
Bake in hot oven (400°) for 15 minutes until risen and nicely brown.

title: fudge cream pie
directions: Note:
Top with whipped cream when cool.

title: cream pie
directions: Combine flour, sugar and salt; mix well. Scald milk with butter (about 2 to 3 minutes in the microwave). Add to flour and sugar, a small amount at a time until mixture is smooth.

title: barbecue potatoes
directions: Slice potatoes into 1/2-inch slices.
Don't peel potatoes. Combine the first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Add to sliced potatoes and toss to coat real good.
Spread lightly on a greased 10 x 15-inch baking dish and bake at 425°
for 20 minutes.

title: pineapple refrigerator cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, pecans, grape nuts and pineapple with juice.
Crush wafers to make crumbs.
In 8-inch square pan make alternate layers of crumbs and pineapple mixture. Start and finish with crumbs.
Chill at least 8 hours.
Cut in squares.
Serve with a teaspoon of cool whip on top.

title: sweet and sour hot dogs
directions: Place chili sauce and grape jelly in saucepan.
Heat.
Chop hot dogs into bite size slices.
Place hot dogs in saucepan.
The longer the hot dogs sit in the sauce the better.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Heat corn and cheese until cheese is melted.
Add rest of ingredients, mixing well.
Place in a greased 9 x 9-inch casserole dish.
Top with cereal crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: tortilla twirls
directions: Mix the cream cheese, olives and green chiles together. Spread thinly on tortilla shell and roll up.
Cut in 3 pieces. Dip in picante sauce.

title: guacamole
directions: Mix together and add fresh chopped cilantro to taste; salt and pepper to taste.

title: brown rice casserole
directions: Place in baking dish in order given.
Bake covered at 350° for 1 hour.

title: baked tomatoes(tomatoes provencales)
directions: Core tomatoes and cut in half horizontally.
Gently squeeze tomato halves to remove juice and seeds.
Sprinkle the bottom of a 9 x 13-inch baking dish lightly with salt.
Place tomatoes, cut-side up, in the dish.
Drizzle with olive oil or salad oil. Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 10 minutes.
Meanwhile, combine garlic, parsley, breadcrumbs, 1/4 teaspoon salt and pepper.
Sprinkle mixture over tomatoes and continue baking, uncovered, for 15 minutes longer, or until tomatoes are soft throughout.

title: apple puff
directions: Preheat oven to 500°.
Melt butter in iron skillet.
Combine eggs, flour and milk.
Beat until smooth. Pour into hot skillet. Place in oven. Reduce heat to 425° and bake for 20 minutes. While this bakes, warm apples. Spoon on top of cake. Sprinkle with brown sugar and cinnamon.

title: devil's food cake
directions: Beat shortening, sugar and vanilla until light.
Beat egg yolks slightly.
Add to creamed mixture and continue to beat until fluffy.
Stir together dry ingredients.
Add alternately with water and mix at medium speed of mixer until well blended.

title: bean casserole
directions: Mix a little juice, sugar, vinegar and beans. Put onions on top, then bacon. Cook for 3 hours at 275°, covered.

title: three bean salad
directions: Will make a large amount.
Will keep in refrigerator for 2 to 3 weeks.

title: nancy's punch
directions: Mix everything together, makes 2 punchbowls of punch.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or cook in crock-pot on low for 2 hours.

title: chiles and cheese squares
directions: Melt butter/oleo; stir egg mixture into this.
Add other ingredients, grating cheese before mixing into egg mixture.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes and at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Can be mixed the night before, refrigerated, and baked the next day.
Makes a terrific breakfast brunch or office potluck treat.
Cut in bite size pieces to eat (good either warm or cold).
Can line crock-pot with foil and lay squares inside, set on low and watch them disappear!

title: dill dip
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Serve with raw vegetables like carrots, cauliflower, tomatoes, zucchini slices, cucumber slices, broccoli, celery and green onions.

title: ham casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Bake in a casserole dish sprayed with Pam.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: cream spam and broccoli
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Spray 2-quart casserole with vegetable cooking spray.
Cook macaroni; drain.
In casserole combine macaroni, broccoli, Spam and red pepper.
In small saucepan mix together milk, cornstarch and pepper until cornstarch is dissolved.
Bring to a boil, stirring constantly until thickened. Combine sauce with other ingredients.
Combine bread crumbs and margarine.
Sprinkle on top.
Bake for 40 minutes or until done.

title: shrimp etouffee
directions: Peel shrimp and devein.
Heat margarine in 3-quart saucepan over medium heat until melted.
Stir in flour.
Cook about 6 minutes, stirring occasionally, until bubbly and brown.
Stir in onion, bell pepper, celery and garlic.
Cook and stir about 5 minutes or until vegetables are crisp-tender.
Stir in shrimp, water, parsley, lemon juice, salt and pepper.
Heat to boiling. Reduce heat.
Simmer, uncovered, about 5 minutes, stirring occasionally, until shrimp are pink.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: play dough (non-toxic)(fun recipe!  but not to eat.  very easy!)
directions: Mix all ingredients in a saucepan. Stir constantly over medium heat until ball forms.
Keep covered.
Stays fresh for a very long time.
Can also be scented with peppermint or almond extract.

title: pumpkin delight
directions: Cook milk, cereal, sugar and 2 tbsp butter until thick.
Stir constantly.
Remove from heat.
Cool slightly.
Fold in pumpkin, eggs and spice.
Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 9x13 inch pan layer 1/2 lb phyllo, buttering each sheet before adding another sheet. Pour pumpkin mixture over dough.
Layer the other half of dough, buttering between layers.
Score the top into 20 pieces.
Bake 1 hour until top is golden.
Dust top with powdered sugar before serving.

title: pasta e fagioli(pasta fayool)
directions: Simmer all ingredients, except kidney beans and ditalini, together until celery is tender.
Add kidney beans in their liquid to mixture to warm.
Lastly, add ditalini, about 10 to 15 minutes before serving.
Add water, as needed, throughout cooking to maintain consistency of a thick soup.

title: giant oatmeal cookies
directions: Blend Crisco, brown sugar, white sugar and eggs.
Add flour, soda and salt.
Then add oats, vanilla and raisins.
Make large balls.
Place on cookie sheet and flatten with glass bottom that has been dipped in sugar.
Bake at 400° for 6 to 10 minutes. Yields 2 1/2 dozen.

title: leftover christmas casserole
directions: You can make this recipe using any amount of ingredients desired.
Grease casserole and place in layers.
Bake, covered, in 350° oven for 30 to 45 minutes.

title: apricot glazed cornish hens
directions: Combine preserves, orange rind and orange juice.
Set aside. Remove giblets from hens, rinse with cold water and pat dry. Sprinkle with paprika.
Place hens breast side up in lightly greased roasting pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours. During last 30 minutes baste frequently with 1/2 cup of apricot glaze.
Saute cashews in butter until golden.
Drain and set aside, reserving butter.
Saute green onions in same skillet until tender. Add rice and prepare according to package directions substituting chicken broth for water.
Serve with cornish hens.

title: cheese ball
directions: Combine all but nuts and parsley.
Divide in half.
Roll into balls.
Roll one ball in nuts, the other in parsley.

title: white fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar well.
Add eggs and mix thoroughly. Mix chopped fruit and nuts with 1/2 cup flour.
Sift remaining flour with baking powder.
Fold into egg and butter mixture.
Add flavoring and mix well.
Add fruits and nuts.
Mix well.
(This mixes better by using your hand.)
Put in greased tube pan lined with brown paper bag paper.
Place in oven at 250° for 3 hours.

title: crunchy cookies
directions: Combine cereal, peanuts and marshmallows in bowl.
Melt vanilla milk chips in microwave or over boiling water.
Pour melted chips over cereal mixture and drop by spoonfuls onto cookie sheet or waxed paper.
When cool, store with layers of wax paper between layers of cookies.

title: blueberry jello salad
directions: In large bowl, mix Jell-O with water, stirring until completely dissolved.
Add blueberries, pineapple and pecans. Refrigerate until set.
Cream together cheese and sugar; fold in sour cream.
Spread over top of Jell-O salad.

title: veggie snack
directions: Flatten crescent rolls out flat on cookie sheet.
Don't separate or grease pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes at oven temperature per package.
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and dressing.
Mix vegetables and grated cheese.
Cool rolls.
Spread cheese mixture on rolls.
Sprinkle vegetable mixture over cheese mixture.
Cut to finger food size.

title: peanut butter cookies
directions: Cream first 5 ingredients together, then add peanut butter and cream it in.
Mix dry ingredients into creamed mixture.
Roll into balls and press with a fork (crisscross).
Bake at 450° for about 8 minutes on lightly greased cookie sheet.

title: crawfish and pasta
directions: Pour cream into heavy skillet over high fire.
Watch carefully! After cream comes to a boil, add thyme, basil, salt, pepper, Tabasco, green onion tops and parsley.
Cook for 3 to 5 minutes. Add crawfish tails; cook for 3 minutes.
Add pasta and cheese; cook for 2 minutes.
Serve in gumbo bowls.
It's delicious!
Makes 6 servings.

title: mashed potato casserole
directions: Peel, dice and boil potatoes until done; drain.
Add cream cheese, sour cream and garlic salt to taste.
Beat mixture until smooth.
Fold in chopped chives.
Pour mixture into greased, 3-quart baking dish.
Place pats of butter on top.
Generously sprinkle paprika on top.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 60 minutes (until crispy on top).

title: lemon poppy seed cake
directions: Stir together cake mix, dry instant pudding and poppy seed. Add remaining ingredients and beat on medium speed for 4 minutes. Bake at 350° for about 55 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes and top with mixture of 1/3 cup granulated sugar and juice of 1 lemon.
Poke holes on top of cake and drizzle on warm cake which was removed from pan.

title: swedish nut cake
directions: Mix all together by hand. Bake in a greased 9 x 13 pan at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: whole-wheat dinner rolls
directions: Soften the dry yeast in lukewarm water. Set aside.
Scald the milk.
Add sugar, salt and shortening. Cool this mixture to lukewarm. Add the yeast mixture and beaten eggs.
Mix well. Add 3 cups whole wheat flour and 3 cups bread flour, 2 cups at a time (you can use the mixer).
Place in a large, greased bowl. Cover and put in refrigerator for at least 2 hours (overnight is better).

title: marinade
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Marinate meat or vegetables for several hours.
Great for grilling.

title: egg roll
directions: Shred cabbage and carrots.
Cut up onion; add to carrots and cabbage.
Brown ground beef and drain off fat.
Combine all ingredients.
Cook over low heat until cabbage is soft.
Set it aside and let cool.
Place 2 tablespoons of mixture in the center of the egg roll wrapper.
Roll and deep fry until golden brown.

title: graham cracker eclairs
directions: Mix pudding, milk and Cool Whip together.
Put one layer of graham crackers in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with half of pudding mixture.
Add another layer of graham crackers and cover with remaining pudding mixture.
Top with another layer of graham crackers.
Frost with chocolate frosting.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.

title: german potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes; peel and cube them.
Boil eggs; peel and cube. Fry bacon until crisp and then chop up the bacon.
Save the bacon grease.
Chop up the onion and saute.
Mix all together in large bowl.
Add vinegar, bacon grease and sugar together and then mix into the potato salad and keep warm.

title: super goodies
directions: Melt almond bark in microwave or double boiler.
Mix ingredients.
Add marshmallows last.
Drop by spoonfuls on waxed paper.

title: peanut butter bars
directions: Cream together shortening, eggs, peanut butter and vanilla. Add remaining ingredients.
Spread on lightly greased cookie sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 25 minutes.

title: rum goody
directions: Mix and put in freezer at least 24 hours before serving. Serve as an icy slush.

title: chicken livers and bacon roll-ups
directions: Dip chicken livers in buttermilk.
Wrap a half slice of bacon around each liver and secure with toothpick.
Coat with cracker crumbs.
Place in 8-inch square baking dish.
Bake at 425° for 25 minutes.

title: crab spread
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Grease a small ovenproof baking dish. Mash the cream cheese and milk until creamy.
Blend in the chopped onion, crabmeat and horseradish, mixing well.
Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle top with paprika.
Bake for 15 to 20 minutes. Serve on crackers.

title: pecos peanut logs
directions: Trim crusts from bread. Cut each slice into 5 finger-sized strips.
Lightly toast crusts and strips on a cookie sheet for 1 hour at 200°.
Pulverize crust in blender (corn flakes may be added for volume).
In blender combine oil and peanut butter. Dip strips in mixture and roll in crumbs.
Place on cookie sheet and bake 45 minutes at 200°.
These freeze well.
Yields a baker's cord of logs.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat; drain.
Tear bread into pieces and mix remaining ingredients all together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch casserole dish.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: pea salad
directions: In medium bowl, put drained peas, diced cheese, eggs and pickles.
Add mayonnaise, salt and pepper to taste.
Mix together and chill.

title: empanadas
directions: Combine flour and salt; cut in shortening until mixture resembles coarse meal.
Stir in beer with a fork until well blended.
Roll dough into 1/8-inch thickness on a lightly floured surface.
Using about a 5-inch saucer to measure, cut out circles with a knife.
Place a rounded tablespoon of potato mixture in center of each circle; moisten edges with water and seal with a fork.
Place empanadas on a cookie sheet and bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Combine sugar and cinnamon; sprinkle over hot empanadas.

title: tasty squash casserole
directions: Cook squash, salt and onion until tender; drain and mash.
Add eggs; mix well.
Arrange in baking dish a layer each of squash mixture, cracker crumbs and cheese.
Dot with butter.
Repeat layers.
Pour milk over all.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until brown on top.

title: kentucky cornbread
directions: Mix and bake at 400°
for 30 minutes.

title: lo-cal reduction vegetable soup
directions: Cut vegetables into medium size pieces and boil, covered, with water for 10 minutes.
Turn on low and cook until vegetables are done.
Eat this soup mixture anytime and as much as you want; the more you eat the more you lose.

title: spinach madeleine
directions: Cook spinach; drain and reserve liquor.
Melt butter in pan over low heat.
Add flour, stirring until blended and smooth, but not brown.
Add liquor slowly, stirring constantly to avoid lumps. Add evaporated milk.
Cook until smooth and thick, continuing to stir.
Add seasoning and cheese which has been cut into small pieces and stir until melted.
Combine with spinach.
Serve immediately or put in casserole and top with buttered bread crumbs.
Keep overnight in refrigerator for improved flavor, then heat in oven and serve.
Serves 6.

title: funny putty
directions: Combine glue and starch; mix well and allow to dry slightly until workable.
Store in airtight containers.

title: "grandma blackwelder's" 3 layer cake
directions: Cream sugar and margarine.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add milk and vanilla.
Then add one cup of flour at a time.
Mix well. Bake in 3 layers at 350° until brown.
Frost with your favorite icing.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Combine eggs, sugar, salt and spices.
Gradually add scalded milk and mix, then add pumpkin, using spoon.
Mix all the ingredients until smooth.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes.
Lower flame to 375°; cook for 1 hour, or until knife inserted in pie at center comes out clean.
Top with whipped cream.
Serve cold or heat and eat warm.

title: no bake cheese cake
directions: Beat cream cheese, sugar and sour cream together.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Add vanilla and lemon juice.
Place in pie crust and chill.
May be served with fresh fruit on top.

title: pork chop casserole
directions: Place pork chops in baking pan. Layer on top, sliced potatoes, then sliced onions. Add cream of mushroom soup. Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: homemade bubbles
directions: Mix well and enjoy!

title: citrus poke cake
directions: Poke holes in cooled cake with a butterknife or fork. Pour soda evenly over top. Mix pudding and milk until well blended. Fold in Cool Whip. Spread over cake and store in refrigerator until serving time.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Cook, drain and break meat into bite-size pieces.
Place meat into bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with bread and cheese.
In bowl mix eggs, milk, mustard, salt and pepper.
Pour over cheese layer.
Refrigerate overnight.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: congealed carrot salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in boiling water.
Drain pineapple.
Add enough water to liquid drained from pineapple to make 2 cups and stir into the gelatin.
Refrigerate until partially congealed, then stir in pineapple, carrots, cheese and pecans.
Chill until firm.

title: refrigerator cucumbers and onions
directions: Soak cucumbers, onions and green pepper in salt for 2 hours. Wash and drain; blot in a towel. Mix vinegar, sugar, mustard seed and celery seed. Mix with vegetables. Put in quart jars and store in refrigerator. Stir every day for 4 days. Eat as is or can freeze in small containers. These will keep for months in refrigerator.

title: baked bean casserole
directions: Saute onion in oil until soft.
Remove from heat and combine with remaining ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix thoroughly.
Put mix into 2-quart casserole dish and place in a preheated 350° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes, uncovered.
Sprinkle with shredded Cheddar cheese and bake 10 minutes longer or until cheese melts. Serves 4.

title: kenrod's spicy ranch dressing
directions: In a large bowl, whisk together sour cream, milk and mayonnaise.
Whisk in horseradish, creole seasoning, coriander, pepper sauce, ranch dressing mix and buttermilk.
Great with chicken wings, fries, onion rings or anything you want and like to dip!

title: barbecue beef and pork
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 2 1/2 to 3 hours, stirring every hour.

title: slush punch
directions: Freeze first 6 ingredients in 5 gallon bags.
When ready to serve, add ginger ale, one bottle to each gallon of frozen juice.

title: tuna salad
directions: Boil eggs and noodles.
In a large bowl, add tuna, pickles, eggs, mayonnaise, onion, green pepper, noodles, tomato and mustard.
Stir well.
Add salt and pepper to taste.
Garnish with 6 cherry tomatoes.
Put in refrigerator to cool and serve with crackers.

title: grilled italian steak
directions: Put steaks in a large shallow non-aluminum baking dish. Combine the Italian dressing, cheese, basil and pepper.
Add to steak and turn to coat.
Cover and marinade 4 to 5 hours in refrigerator, turning occasionally.
Remove the steak from the marinade, reserving the marinade.
Barbecue, grill or broil the steaks, turning once or until steaks are done to test.
In a small pan bring the reserved marinade to boil and continue boiling for one minute.
Pour over steak and serve.

title: escalloped corn
directions: Saute the onion and celery in margarine.
Layer the ingredients in order, beginning with cracker crumbs and cheese and ending with cracker crumbs and cheese.
Bake in 2-quart Pyrex dish for 40 minutes.

title: basic spaghetti sauce
directions: In saucepan, saute garlic in oil until golden brown, then add all ingredients.
Simmer for 1 hour stirring often.
Serve with your favorite macaroni, sprinkle with grated cheese.

title: homemade ketchup
directions: Cook 1 hour and put through strainer.
Add 5 tablespoons cornstarch or Clear Jell.
Mix together and stir into juice; boil 10 minutes and can and seal.

title: pecan puffs
directions: Cream butter and sugar together. Add vanilla. Mix ground pecans and flour together. Add to creamed mixture. Roll into firm small balls and place on baking sheet. Bake in slow oven at 325° about 45 minutes or until done. Remove from baking sheet and roll in powdered sugar while hot. Cool and roll again in powdered sugar.

title: cream pies
directions: Mix everything together.
Pour into 2 pie crusts and refrigerate.

title: lime jello salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Chill 4 hours.
(I use sugar free jello, Cool Whip Lite and 1% low-fat cottage cheese.)

title: zucchini cheese muffins
directions: Combine all ingredients except vegetable oil.
Stir until well blended.
Heat 1 teaspoon vegetable oil in each muffin cup.
Spoon batter into each cup.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown and puffed.
Makes 12.

title: rolls
directions: Take milk, sugar, salt and Crisco; bring to a boil. Let cool. Then add eggs, yeast and flour. (Use 6 1/2 cups flour and 1/2 cup to roll out.) Let rise once. Roll out. Make rolls; butter them. Let rise again. Form into rolls, rise and bake at 350° until browned.

title: chicken-swiss cheese bake
directions: Place chicken breast in single layer in buttered casserole dish.
Salt and pepper each piece.
Cover each breast with slice of Swiss cheese.
Mix soup and milk and pour over the chicken and cheese.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: beef macaroni skillet
directions: Break beef and brown in skillet.
Add garlic and onion.
Cook until tender.
Add tomatoes and blend in pepper, salt, bouillon, Worcestershire sauce, macaroni and mushrooms with liquid. Reduce heat after this mixture comes to a boil.
Cover and simmer for about 30 minutes, stirring frequently.

title: sweet and sour salad dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients in a blender.
Store in refrigerator.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream together oleo, sugar and shortening.
Mix in egg yolks. Add flour, soda and vanilla alternately with buttermilk.
Add pecans and coconut; mix well.
Fold in stiffly beaten egg whites. Fill 3 (8-inch) pans or 9 x 13-inch pan which have been floured and greased.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.
Cool and frost with Italian Cream Frosting.

title: spaghetti pie
directions: Cook spaghetti and drain.
Stir in margarine, Parmesan cheese and eggs.
Form into crust in a 10-inch pie pan.
Spread cottage cheese over crust.
Brown and drain beef and onion.
Mix with rest of ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into crust.
Bake, uncovered, 20 minutes at 350°.
Sprinkle Mozzarella on top and bake 5 minutes.

title: date pudding
directions: Cream the sugar and butter.
Sift the flour, cinnamon and baking powder.
Add to creamed mixture alternately with milk.
Add nuts, dates and vanilla.
Drop dough into hot sauce in baking pan, spooning tablespoon at a time and bake 35 minutes at 350°.

title: sausage skillet dinner
directions: Brown sausage with onion.
Drain.
Add mushroom soup, rice, bouillon cubes and hot water.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat. Simmer 20 minutes.
Add frozen peas and chopped pimentos.
Simmer 5 to 10 more minutes.

title: cheese ball
directions: Chop green onion stems and 1 jar of beef; mix with Worcestershire sauce and Accent.
Mix this with the cream cheese. Roll into ball.
Roll ball in second jar of diced beef.
Wrap in double Saran Wrap and chill at least 4 hours.
Excellent served on small pumpernickel bread or wheat crackers.

title: black-eyed pea salad
directions: Rinse black-eyed peas well.
Soak overnight.
Rinse with fresh water again, then cook until tender.
Drain.
Pour lemon juice and garlic over warm peas and let cool while marinating.
Add remaining ingredients to black-eyed peas after they are cool. Toss well. Chill 2 hours.

title: homemade syrup
directions: Cook until liquid is clear.

title: beef and beer casserole
directions: Heat oven to 325°.
Dredge the beef with flour and brown in oil for a few minutes.
Do a few pieces at a time, then put in a large 6 to 8-quart casserole.
Add onions and garlic to oil and brown lightly (add more oil, if needed).
Add to casserole along with the sugar, 2 tablespoons vinegar, parsley, bay leaves, thyme, salt and pepper.
Stir once or twice.
Skim off any remaining oil left in skillet and add the broth; heat over low flame to loosen brown bits on bottom of the pan.
Then pour this over meat in casserole.
Add beer and cover.
Bake at 325° for 2 hours until the meat is tender.
Remove from oven; add 2 tablespoons remaining vinegar.
Cook over heat until bubbling.
Add biscuits on top, cover, put back in oven and steam for 15 minutes.

title: olive meatball bites
directions: Mix first four ingredients well.
Mold around each olive and bake on a well greased cookie sheet on broil for 10 minutes.
Serve hot with fancy toothpicks.

title: play dough
directions: Mix all ingredients (except food coloring) together in saucepan. Cook over medium heat until a ball is formed.
Knead until smooth. Color as desired with food coloring.
After dough is cool, store in an airtight container.

title: crazy cookies
directions: Mix sugar, margarine, cocoa and milk together in saucepan. Bring to a boil slowly over low heat.
At boil, count 1 and 2 and 3 and . . . to 10.
Take off heat and add peanut butter and oatmeal. Stir together and drop by teaspoon on wax paper.
Cool.
Makes 4 dozen.

title: cheese crispies
directions: Mix until smooth first 5 ingredients.
Gently stir in Rice Krispies.
Roll into pecan size balls.
Mash with a fork.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: chewy date torte
directions: In a mixing bowl, beat eggs.
Gradually add sugar, beating until thoroughly blended.
Combine flour, baking powder and salt and stir into mixing bowl.
Add milk, margarine and vanilla, stirring until blended.
Stir in dates and nuts.
Pour into a greased 9-inch square pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until it tests done.
Cool.
Cut into squares and top with whipped cream.
Yields 9 servings.

title: baked broccoli
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a 1 1/2-quart shallow bake dish, combine soup, milk, soy sauce and pepper.
Cut up broccoli; add to soup.
Stir in 1/2 of the onions.
Bake for 25 minutes.
Stir and add remaining onions.
Bake 5 minutes more.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Mix sugar, syrup and salt together in glass bowl with wooden spoon
and microwave on High 7 minutes.
Stir after 4 and stir again after 3 minutes.
Add nuts and 1 tablespoon of butter and vanilla.
Cook 2 minutes on High until golden brown.
Add baking soda and pour on greased baking sheet.

title: baked chicken and rice
directions: Stir together canned milk, 1/2 can water and soup. Mix rice into soup mixture. Put this in baking dish. Put mushrooms on top. Add chicken or pork chops. Sprinkle with Mrs. Dash.

title: salmon patties
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Fry in a nonstick pan or on grill sprayed with Pam.

title: tomato dumplings
directions: Heat tomatoes to a medium boil.
Add baking soda.

title: mom's barbecue
directions: Cook the meat and onion over low flame until browned.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cook slowly in covered saucepan.
If sauce is too thick, add a little more water.

title: pozole
directions: Put the first 10 ingredients in a large kettle; bring to a boil.
Turn heat to low; simmer gently, covered, for at least 1 hour, or until pork and chicken are tender.
Add hominy; cook 15 minutes longer.
Garnish with avocado slices, chopped green onions, grated Monterey Jack cheese or tortilla chips.

title: mexican delight
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil until light brown.
Add beef and cook until done; sprinkle with salt and chili powder.
Add tomato sauce and 1/4 cup water; simmer 1/2 hour.
Add cooked noodles, corn, mushrooms and sliced olives.
Add half of cheese and turn into casserole dish.
Sprinkle remaining cheese on top and cook 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: lemon whippersnaps
directions: Grease cookie sheet.
Mix cake mix, egg and Cool Whip.
Roll teaspoon size balls in powdered sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 15 minutes.

title: quick appetizer dip
directions: Place finely shredded lettuce in a layer on a serving plate or platter.
Top with sour cream and salsa.
Sprinkle with the shredded cheese.
Serve with tostados or chips.
Quick and delicious.

title: redi-mix hot rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water. Sift dry ingredients together. Add liquid ingredients and combine. Add eggs and mashed potatoes.

title: pickled beets
directions: Drain beets, reserving 1/4 cup liquid.
Combine beet liquid and remaining ingredients in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add beets. Cover, reduce heat and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and cool slightly.
Transfer to a covered container and chill overnight.
Yields 2 1/2 cups.

title: spinach dip
directions: In covered blender container, blend all ingredients at high speed just until finely chopped.
Cover and refrigerate at least 4 hours.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.
Serve with radishes, cauliflower, carrot, celery, etc.

title: pork fried rice
directions: Slice pork into 1/4-inch thick slices.
Cut into small strips. Cook rice according to package directions.
Heat oil in nonstick Dutch oven or 12-inch skillet over medium heat.
Add cabbage, red peppers and 2 tablespoons of water.
Cook, covered, 8 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Stir in pork and ginger.
Cover and cook 3 to 5 minutes or until pork is no longer pink in the center.
Remove from heat.
Stir in rice, green onion and peas.
Stir soy sauce and sesame oil into rice mixture.
Cook 2 minutes and serve.

title: icebox pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers, onions and bell peppers.
Sprinkle salt over them and refrigerate for two hours.

title: krispy date ball cookies
directions: Combine dates, sugar, eggs and margarine.
Boil mixture over low heat for 20 minutes.
Remove from heat and wait until mixture stops boiling, then add Rice Krispies and nuts.
Mix well.
Roll into balls and roll into coconut.

title: anything bread
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix by hand.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Makes 2 regular loaves or 5 mini loaves.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: Cut cabbage up fine; cut up celery, onion and green pepper. Put drippings in heavy skillet.
Then add all ingredients, except cheese.
Cook over slow heat until tender.
Then add shredded cheese; slide out onto a flat bowl and serve.

title: tortilla pie
directions: Cook all ingredients except tortillas and cheese 20 to 30 minutes or until translucent.
Mixture should be pourable. Alternate layers of tortillas (cut if necessary), bean mixture and cheese ending with tortillas.
Cover; bake in preheated oven at 375° for 35 minutes.

title: italian cream cake
directions: Cream shortening, sugar and margarine well.
Add egg yolks one at a time, beating after each one.
Gradually add flour and buttermilk, beating well.
Fold in coconut, pecans and beaten egg whites.
Bake in 3 cake pans for 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.

title: reese balls
directions: Mix first four ingredients together; roll out into 1/2 to 1-inch balls.
Melt chocolate drops in double boiler.
Add paraffin until chocolate becomes thin.
Dip balls into chocolate and let cool.

title: chicken breasts diane
directions: Place chicken between waxed paper and pound with a mallet, slightly.
Sprinkle with salt and pepper.
Heat 1 tablespoon each of oil and butter in a large skillet.
Cook breasts over high heat for 4 minutes on each side.
Do not cook longer.
Transfer to a warm serving platter.
Add next 5 ingredients to pan; cook 15 seconds, whisking constantly.
Whisk in broth and remaining butter and oil.
Pour sauce over chicken.
Serve immediately.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Mix cake mix, oil jell-o, 1/2 box strawberries, and flour in a large mixing bowl.
Add eggs one at a time while mixing.
Add nuts. Bake at 350 30 - 35 minutes.

title: hamburger and beans
directions: Cook hamburger meat and onions until done; drain and set aside.
Brown bacon; take up and crumble.
In a big pot, add hamburger mixture and bacon, then add remaining ingredients.
Cook 1 hour on stove on simmer.
Stir often.

title: party mix
directions: Melt oleo in a large baking pan.
Stir in salt.
Add cereal and nuts.
Mix and coat well.
Heat in a 250° oven for 1 hour. Stir-fry every 15 minutes.

title: clare's cucumber sandwiches
directions: Combine cream cheese and Ranch dressing mix.
Spread a small amount of cream cheese mixture on each rye bread piece.
Top each with a cucumber slice and sprinkle lightly with some dill weed.

title: easy chicken casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and place in square or rectangular dish. Bake for 1/2 hour, uncovered, at 425°.

title: quick easy lasagna
directions: Cook meat until brown.
Stir in spaghetti sauce.
In 8-inch square dish, put half of the meat mixture.
Top with half noodles. Top with half of soup mixture and milk.
Repeat the layers. Sprinkle with cheese.
Cook in 400° oven for 30 minutes until hot and bubbling.
Let stand 10 minutes.

title: mary ella paige's hamburg casserole
directions: Layer in casserole; pour soup over all.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, covered, or until vegetables are tender.

title: blueberry muffins
directions: Sift together all of the dry ingredients.
Add the remaining ingredients except the Blueberries.
Stir until the flour mixture is dampened.
Fold in the Blueberries.
Spoon into greased muffin tins.
Bake at 400 for 20 - 25 minutes or till tooth pick comes out clean.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: In large stewing pot, cover the chicken (1-inch over the chicken pieces) with water.
Add the celery, half of the onion, poultry seasoning and salt and pepper.
Slow boil until the chicken meat falls from the bones.
Remove from the heat.
Strain the broth into a cooking pot.
Add the remaining onions, parsley and 4 cups of water.
Simmer the liquid on the stove.
As the broth simmers, go through the strained chicken pieces and hand pick off all of the chicken meat, being careful not to get any bones.
Shred the meat into small pieces and return the meat to the simmering broth.
Simmer, covered, for 30 minutes.

title: seafood bisque
directions: Saute onion and celery in butter in saucepan.
Stir in flour. Gradually stir in water.
Add bouillon cube, ketchup, bay leaf and seasoned salt.
Heat to boiling.
Reduce heat and boil gently for 5 minutes.
Discard leaf.

title: hot nacho dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese on bottom of quiche pan or other shallow baking dish.
Spoon enough salsa to cover cream cheese. Top with grated cheese.
Microwave or bake until hot.
Serve with nacho chips.

title: cornish pasty
directions: Make a 2 crust pastry recipe or buy Pillsbury refrigerated pie crusts.
Mix steak, onion, potatoes, salt and pepper.
Place 1/2 mixture on one side of pastry. Fold over and crimp pastry edge to seal, as in a turnover.
Pierce a small hole in top. Repeat with other pastry round.
Place on cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: shrimp creole
directions: Cook onion and pepper in oil.
Add next six ingredients. Bring to a boil.
Cover and simmer 30 minutes.
Remove cloves and bay leaf.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Serve over rice.
Makes 4 servings.

title: pepperoni pinwheels(appetizer)
directions: Blend pepperoni, cheese, oregano and egg.
Separate crescent rolls into 8 rectangles.
Spread mixture over each rectangle. Start at short side and roll up and seal.
Cut each roll into 6 pieces and place cut side down on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Serve warm.
Can also be frozen and reheated.

title: seafood salad
directions: Chop crab flakes in half.
Combine all ingredients and put on top of green salad.
Cover with your favorite salad dressing and enjoy.

title: oatmeal fudge
directions: Bring first 4 ingredients to a boil for 2 minutes.
Add 2 to 3 cups oatmeal.
Drop spoonfuls onto wax paper and cool.

title: baked fish
directions: Put flour, salt, pepper and garlic salt in bag and shake.
Put fish into flour mixture and shake.
Take fish out of bag and lay on paper towel.
Melt oleo in baking dish.
Lay fish flesh side down on melted oleo; flip fish over and lay it on skin.
Add lemon juice to wine and pour over fish.
Bake at 320° for 20 minutes.
Then put under broiler for 5 minutes to brown.

title: crumb-topped tomatoes
directions: Cut each tomato into 3 thick slices.
Arrange tomato slices on microwave-safe serving plate.

title: orange jello dessert
directions: Dissolve jello in orange juice that has been brought to boiling.
Add ice cream.
Refrigerate until slighlty thickened. Stir in oranges and whipped cream.

title: coconut pie
directions: Beat ingredients.
Combine and bake at 325° until set and brown.
Makes 2 pies.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Stir eggs into Jiffy mix.
Add oleo and stir again.
Mix cream cheese, cooked broccoli, and diced onion, and add to Jiffy mix, but do not beat.
Pour into well greased 9 x 13-inch pan and bake at 400° until brown.
Be sure to preheat oven to 400°.
You may cook onion in oleo but it's not necessary.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix eggs, vanilla, sugar, vegetable oil and zucchini all together in a bowl.
Add remaining ingredients and stir well.
Put in 2 loaf pans and bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cake that doesn't last
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Pour in oil, mashed bananas, eggs (slightly beaten), pineapple and vanilla.
Stir, do not beat. Add nuts and stir.
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: corn pudding
directions: Blend margarine, flour, sugar and salt in 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Add frozen corn.
Beat eggs and cream together and pour over corn.
Bake at 325° for about an hour, until the pudding is nearly set.
If the corn was frozen, stir after about 15 minutes to distribute corn.

title: bob andy pie
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in a bowl and set aside. In another mixing bowl, beat eggs, milk, melted butter and vanilla. Pour in dry ingredients and beat until blended. Pour in pastry shell. Bake at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes or knife inserted near the center comes out clean.

title: marshmallow salad
directions: Use juices from cans and mix all the ingredients together. Chill and serve.

title: conch chowder
directions: Bruise and boil conchs.
Cut into small pieces.
Fry out onion and celery in 1 tablespoon oil.
Add sauces and water.
Add rest of ingredients.
Boil for 1 hour.

title: dole ambrosia
directions: Drain pineapple and oranges.
Use juice as a beverage.
Combine pineapple, oranges, bananas, grapes, marshmallows and coconut. Fold in yogurt and chill.

title: grape jelly meat balls
directions: Mix all ingredients and shape into small meat balls.
Brown in a large pan.

title: baked bean dip
directions: Spread softened cream cheese in bottom of baking dish.
Mix soup and salsa together and spread over cream cheese.
Top with Monterey Jack cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot with corn chips.
tags: Campbell's chili beef with beans soup

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Mix
all
ingredients
except Cheddar cheese and potato chips. Put
in an ovenproof casserole.
Top with cheese, then potato chips.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.

title: murf's chicken "n" dumplings
directions: Wash a whole fryer, put in large stock pot and cover with water.
Add 1 bay leaf, 1 small chopped onion, 1 stalk chopped celery with leaves, 1 clove minced garlic, salt and pepper to taste.
Bring to boil and simmer until chicken falls off the bone. Remove chicken from broth and debone.

title: barbecued chicken
directions: Wash the chicken and pat dry.
Set aside.
In large saucepan, combine remaining ingredients.
Bring to a boil.
Simmer, uncovered, for 10 minutes.

title: texas beans
directions: Cook pinto beans until tender.
Brown hamburger, then add to the pintos.
Add 2 teaspoons mustard, ketchup and brown sugar. Boil to taste.

title: duck with curry and honey
directions: Rinse the duck and pat dry.
Salt and pepper inside and out to your taste.
Place the onion stuck with the cloves in the cavity. Roast the duck at 325° for 1 hour.
Then begin basting the duck every 10 minutes with a mixture of the honey, brown sugar and curry powder.
The duck should cook for a total of 1 1/2 hours.

title: bran rolls
directions: Soak bran, sugar and shortening in boiling water in large mixing bowl.
Soak yeast in lukewarm water and let stand.
Add eggs and salt to mixture in mixing bowl, then add yeast mixture. Stir in flour.

title: bread pudding
directions: Place bread crumbs in baking dish.
Scald milk with butter; pour over crumbs.
Add sugar, eggs, salt and cinnamon.
Blend well.
Sprinkle top with nutmeg.
Bake in 350° oven for 40 minutes.
Serves 70 to 75.

title: neens almond roca
directions: In a large, heavy pan, melt butter.
Add sugar; stir until dissolved.
Add water, 1 tablespoon at a time (will crackle a little).
Add corn syrup.
Stir constantly until candy thermometer reaches 295° (this takes quite a while).
Immediately pour into greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Let cool; break into pieces.
Dip pieces into melted chocolate chips and sprinkle with chopped almonds. Let set on waxed paper.

title: oreo cookie cake
directions: Melt the margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour over the cookies that have been crushed into the pan.
Save 1/4 cup for top.
Spread butter and Oreos in pan and refrigerate for 15 minutes.
Mix cream cheese, powdered sugar and 8 ounce of Cool Whip.
Spread over cookies.
Mix chocolate pudding according to the directions on the box.
Spread over mixture and put in refrigerator for 1 hour or so.
Then put 8 ounces Cool Whip
on top and sprinkle with 1/4 cup crushed cookies.

title: layered sausage link casserole
directions: Pan-fry sausage links until browned.
Drain on paper towel. Peel and slice potatoes, then spread and press in bottom of greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Slice links into fourths and spread over potatoes.
Spread cheese over sausage.
Mix soup with milk and spread over cheese.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.
Top with onion rings for the last 10 minutes.

title: hot chicken salad
directions: Combine chicken, salt and pepper, celery, soup, mayonnaise and lemon juice.
Layer 1/2 mixture in a 9 x 9 inch baking dish. Sprinkle chopped eggs over chicken mixture.
Top with the remaining chicken mixture and the chow mein noodles.
Bake in preheated oven at 350 degrees for about 30 minutes (until bubbly). Serves 6.

title: beef porcupines
directions: Beat egg in a large bowl. Combine ground beef, rice and egg. Shape into 1-inch meat balls. Brown in skillet. These do not have to be completely done, just browned.

title: black walnut cookie
directions: Cream butter, vanilla and brown sugar.
Gradually add beaten eggs and cream until fluffy.
Add walnuts.
Combine flour, soda and salt; add 1/4 at a time.
Roll and wrap dough; chill several hours or overnight.
Slice and bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: tex mex made easy!
directions: In Pyrex pie dish, spread cream cheese over bottom of dish. Add chili.
Cover with Monterey cheese.
Microwave on High for 5 minutes.
Serve with tortilla chips.
Makes a hearty appetizer in 5 minutes.

title: superb banana pudding
directions: *Mix 1/2 Cool Whip; save the rest.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients and put in dish.

title: grandmother's sweet bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350.
Mix first 7 ingredients beginning with flour.
Blend until dough can be handled.
Let rise to double in size.
Knead again and add raisins.
Shape into loaves.
Let rise to double in size.
Bake at 350 degrees until brown.

title: robert's bread(serves large group)
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Add sugar, salt and oil to yeast mixture.
Let sit until frothy.
Add flours, alternating whole wheat and white.
(Use as little flour as possible for moister bread.)
Knead dough 10 to 15 minutes.
Round off and place in large, greased bowl.
Place damp cloth on top to keep from drying out.
Set in warm place (80° to 90°) for about 1 1/2 hours or until dough doubles.
Divide into loaves and place free-standing on cookie sheet or in greased bread pans.
Let stand 1/2 hour.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour to 45 minutes, according to size and color of loaves.
Makes four larger loaves or eight small loaves.

title: eagle brand salad
directions: Beat together milk and lemon juice; add rest of ingredients and refrigerate.

title: overnight chicken casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients except topping together.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Refrigerate overnight.
Before baking, cover with crushed Cheez-Its crackers.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: blueberry salad
directions: Mix together, put into a 13 x 9-inch dish and chill.

title: micro peanut brittle
directions: *Omit butter if coconut is added.

title: sugar-free fruit fantastic
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix.
Chill.
Serves 10 or more.

title: tuna casserole
directions: In 1-quart casserole, blend the soup and milk.
Add tuna, vegetables and noodles.
Top with crushed potato chips and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: apricot salad
directions: Mix gelatin.
Add marshmallows while warm.
Cut up bananas and mix with pineapple so they won't turn dark.
Add this to gelatin mixture before it jells.

title: broccoli-cheese soup
directions: Mix all ingredients and cook until done.

title: curried turkey turnovers
directions: In a 10-inch skillet, cook turkey and onion until turkey is brown.
Drain off any fat.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, the green pepper, carrot, raisins, curry powder, salt, cumin and pepper. Cover and simmer 10 minutes.
If necessary, remove cover and cook over high heat 3 to 4 minutes or until liquid is evaporated. Spoon filling into a bowl.
Cool.
Let the pie crusts stand at room temperature while the filling cools.

title: nourishing oatmeal cookies(makes 2 dozen)
directions: Combine softened butter with sugar and egg. Add rest of ingredients. Drop rounded teaspoonfuls on ungreased baking sheet and bake at 350° for approximately 10 minutes until edges browned. Cool on wire rack.

title: chicken and broccoli casserole
directions: Grease casserole dish.
Put broccoli in first, then chicken. In a bowl, mix all ingredients except cheese and pour over broccoli and chicken.
Add cheese to top.
Mix melted butter and bread crumbs and put on top, if desired.
Bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.

title: frozen spaghetti sauce
directions: Mix together; bring to a rapid boil.
Reduce heat and simmer 1 hour.
May be frozen or canned.
When ready to serve, add 1 pound ground beef.

title: granola
directions: Combine honey and vegetable oil.
Add to dry ingredients. Stir.
Spread thin on 2 cookie sheets.
Bake at 250° until brown, about 1 hour.
Stir occasionally.

title: yoohoo chocolate ice cream
directions: Mix together and pour into one gallon ice cream freezer. Pack freezer with ice and salt.
Freeze as usual.

title: sue's sausage upside-down cornbread
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
In a large skillet cook sausage, onion and green pepper until sausage is brown and crumbly.
Stir in flour and mix in tomato paste, salt, chili powder and black pepper. Remove from heat and stir in cheese cubes and olives. Spread evenly in a 9-inch square baking pan.
Prepare corn muffin mix according to package and then spread over sausage mixture. Bake for 30 to 35 minutes or until cornbread is done.
Let stand for 5 minutes and then loosen edges and invert onto serving plate. Serve immediately.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: microwave peach chutney
directions: In 2-quart microwave-safe bowl combine all ingredients. Microwave on High for 9 to 14 minutes or until mixture boils and thickens, stirring every 2 minutes.
Spoon into 3 clean, hot 8-ounce jars.
Screw lids on firmly.
Store in refrigerator up to 3 weeks.
Makes 3 cups.

title: lime dessert
directions: Cream cheese and mayonnaise and add crushed pineapple. Dissolve gelatin in hot water and add marshmallows.
Combine nuts with cream cheese, then add gelatin mixture and mix together.
Add milk and lemon juice.
Mix.
Chill for several hours and serve.

title: lemon meringue pie
directions: Prepare pastry for 9-inch pastry shell. Reserve 6 tablespoons sugar for the meringue.
Combine remaining sugar, cornstarch and salt in the top of a double boiler.
Stir in water. Cook over boiling water until thickened, stirring constantly.
Cover and cook 15 minutes. Stir a little of the hot mixture into the slightly beaten egg yolks.
Add to remaining hot mixture in top of double boiler and cook for 2 minutes over hot water.
Stir constantly. Add butter. Cool. Add 1 lemon rind and juice.
Pour into baked shell. Cover with meringue made from egg whites (room temperature) and reserved sugar.
Bake in a moderate oven at 325° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: haystacks
directions: Bring first four ingredients to a boil.
Add oatmeal or Cheerios, vanilla and peanut butter.
Drop by spoonfuls onto wax paper.
Cool.

title: stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake washed potatoes at 400° for about 1 hour or until done. Cut "lid" from top of potatoes or for smaller portions, cut potatoes in half lengthwise.
Carefully, scoop out potato from shells.
Beat with butter until all butter is melted.
Add sour cream, dressing mix and enough milk to make smooth but leave stiff enough to hold shape.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Stuff potato mixture back into shells and top with grated cheese and paprika. Heat in oven until piping hot.

title: sausage-cheese balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Form into 1 1/2-inch balls. Bake for 20 minutes at 375°.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Thaw and drain broccoli.
Cut into small pieces; put into casserole and pour over mushroom soup, sour cream and celery.
Top with cheese.
Heat in oven about 25 minutes.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions and combine with sour cream and chicken
soup.
Add
chicken
pieces and Worcestershire sauce. Melt oleo
and
mix with cracker crumbs.
Sprinkle over casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1/2 hour.

title: lobster thermidor
directions: Cut lobster in half; remove meat and break into small pieces. Cook mushrooms in 3 tablespoons butter; add paprika, mustard, parsley and sherry.
Heat just to boiling; melt remaining butter and blend in flour and milk.
Cook until thickened, stirring constantly.
Season with salt and pepper; add mushroom mixture and lobster.
Fill shells with mixture; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake at 425° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 2.

title: eggplant patrice
directions: Slice unpeeled eggplant 1/4 inch thick.
Place a layer of eggplant slices in a greased 1-quart casserole and add a layer of sliced tomatoes.
Cover with mixture of chopped green peppers and onions.
Sprinkle lightly with seasonings.
Add a layer of cheese. Repeat until dish is filled.
End with cheese (shrinks).
Cover and bake at 400° for 30 minutes.
Remove the cover and reduce to 350° for an extra 45 minutes.
Serves 8.
Enjoy!

title: rock and roll pie dough
directions: In a large Tupperware bowl with a seal, put flour, salt and sugar.
Add Crisco by spoonfuls.
Seal bowl, wrap and shake well until it looks like cornmeal.
Add 6 to 8 tablespoons ice water. Seal.
Roll.
It will form 2 balls.
Roll out into two pie shells.

title: caramel corn
directions: Put popped corn on 2 cookie sheets.
Put first 4 ingredients in saucepan.
Boil for 5 minutes, then add 1/4 teaspoon baking soda and 1 teaspoon vanilla.
Mix well.
Pour liquid over popped corn on cookie sheet.
Peanuts and almonds can be added to popped corn.
Bake at 250° for 1 hour, stirring every 15 minutes.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Put these all in order in baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream shortening, eggs, sugars and vanilla.
Add flour, then chips.
Bake at 375° for 8 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: cream of fiddlehead soup
directions: For thicker soup, combine 2 1/2 tablespoons flour with butter. Season to taste.
You may use this basic recipe to make either cream of broccoli or cream of cauliflower soup.
You may want to put part of the vegetables through a blender.

title: pear relish
directions: Tie in bag the pickling spice, mustard, and celery seed. Grind pears, peppers, and onions, drain.
Combine vinegar, sugar, salt, pepper, and spices and bring to a boil.
Add pears and then let boil for 20 minutes.
Place in hot sterilized jar; seal. Makes 7 -8 pints.

title: coffee can ice cream
directions: Baklavas is the most famous and best liked of all Greek pastries.
It arouses all the senses.
It looks appealing, is crunchy, excites all the taste buds and has a captivating aroma. One is not satisfied with just a single piece.

title: easy fettuccine alfredo-tomato
directions: Cook pasta 7 minutes, then add broccoli florets and continue cooking both for 3 more minutes or until both are firm-tender. Remove from heat. Reserve 1/3 cup liquid from pot, then drain pasta and broccoli in colander. Mix sour cream, cheese and the 1/3 cup liquid in a serving bowl. Add pasta, broccoli and cherry tomatoes to water and toss well to coat. Makes 4 servings.

title: applesauce cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together thoroughly.
Pour into greased tube pan.
Bake at 350° for one hour.

title: fruit salad
directions: Put bananas in lemon juice, then drain.
Mix and serve.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls in an 11 x 15-inch jelly roll pan, pressing edges together.
Bake at 350° until lightly browned. Cool crust.

title: amazing coconut pie
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Combine all ingredients but coconut in blender.
Cover and blend on low speed 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch pie plate.
Let stand 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Bake 40 minutes or until done.

title: italian sausage and peppers
directions: Cook turkey sausage in heavy skillet over medium heat until browned, turning occasionally.
Layer half of the onions on bottom of 3 - 4 quart crock-pot, then add half of the peppers.
Add all of the browned turkey sausage, then the rest of the onions and peppers.
Add bay leaves and garlic.

title: swiss cheese spread
directions: Combine all ingredients; chill.
Shape in any desired shape. Garnish with nuts or parsley.
Serve with fruit and crackers. Makes 1 cup.

title: stuffed zucchini
directions: Cut zucchini in half lengthwise and steam for 4 to 5 minutes (they should be firm). Scoop out seeds and place in greased baking pans.

title: easy chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken and debone.
Use the broth to cook pot pie in. Beat 1 egg into 1/2 cup milk; set aside.
Mix flour, Crisco and salt in larger bowl; add egg milk mixture.
Roll out on flour, then cut into 1 x 1-inch squares.
Add to boiling broth.
Cook for about 30 minutes.
Add chicken and serve.
Serves 6 to 8.

title: impossible cheeseburger pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease pie plate.
Brown beef and onion; drain.
Stir in salt and pepper.
Spread in plate.
Beat milk, baking mix and eggs until smooth.
Pour into plate.
Bake 25 minutes.
Top with tomato; sprinkle with cheese.
Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 5 to 8 minutes more.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: nutty fingers
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Shape into small fingers. Bake at 325° for 20 minutes. Roll in powdered sugar. Store in tin can.

title: old fashioned sweet potato pie
directions: Boil, skin and mash sweet potatoes.
Cream butter, eggs and sugar.
Mix the potatoes with the creamed ingredients.
Add the orange juice and rind.
Pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: marshmallow nut brownies
directions: Preheat oven to
and grease an 8-inch square cake pan. Melt chocolate and butter in double boiler over hot, but not boiling
water
(lowest heat), stirring occasionally.
Set aside to cool.
Sift
flour,
salt
and
baking
powder into a large bowl and
set aside.
Break eggs into another large bowl and beat until frothy.
Beat in sugar a little at a time.
Add the chocolate
mixture,
vanilla,
nuts and marshmallows; stir well. Stir
in
the
flour mixture and spread evenly into the pan.
Bake 30 minutes.
Let cool in pan for 10 to 15 minutes. Cut into 2-inch squares and remove to a cake rack.

title: bean casserole
directions: Cook bacon and onions; drain off fat.
Add brown sugar, mustard, ketchup and vinegar.
Add all canned beans.
Bake for 70 minutes at 350°.

title: baked stuffed scallops
directions: In a saucepan melt butter, add crackers, bread crumbs and seasoning.
Fold in cut scallops; place in ungreased 4 qt. casserole; pour cream evenly over top of scallops.
Bake 350° for 45 minutes, till golden.

title: no peek chicken
directions: Grease large casserole dish well.
First place rice with herbs on the bottom of the dish; then chicken breasts; then onion soup, celery soup, mushroom soup (in layers).
Cover with 2 scant cups of water.
Cover.
Bake at 350° for 2 hours without peeking.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: spoon rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water, dissolve.
In large bowl, cream margarine and sugar together.
Add beaten egg.
Add flour and dissolved yeast; stir until well blended.
Place in airtight bowl and refrigerate.
Will keep several days.
To bake, drop in greased muffin tin.
Bake in 350° oven for 20 minutes.

title: ranch party mix
directions: Place popcorn, crackers and pretzels in large bag.
Sprinkle popcorn mixture with remaining ingredients except butter.
Close bag and shake gently to distribute evenly.
Drizzle mixture with butter. Reclose bag and shake until all ingredients are evenly coated.
Pour popcorn mixture onto large baking sheet and spread evenly.
Bake at 300° for 8 minutes.
Cool and serve.

title: gingerbread
directions: Mix as any
cake
and
bake in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan at 325°.

title: sugar and spice cookies
directions: Crush cornflakes into fine crumbs.
Blend butter, sugar and vanilla.
Sift together flour and cinnamon.
Add with cornflake crumbs and nuts to butter mixture.
Mix well.

title: peanut butter glaze
directions: In small pan, combine chips and milk.
Cook over low heat until chips are melted.
Stir constantly.
Gradually add powdered sugar and vanilla.
Beat until spreading consistency.
Additional milk may be needed.
Makes about 2/3 cup glaze.
Great over chocolate cake.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Saute mushrooms in 2 tablespoons butter.
Add sherry; cook for a few minutes.
Make a cream sauce of 2 tablespoons butter and 2 tablespoons flour.
Rub these together and add hot milk.
Cook in a double boiler, stirring constantly, until smooth and of a good body, about 20 minutes.
Season with salt and pepper and nutmeg. Beat the yolks of the eggs into the cream; add to the sauce. Continue to stir.
After 5 minutes, add chicken.
Season to taste. Add mushrooms.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Mix in applesauce and spices.
Sift salt, soda and flour together and add applesauce to mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in nuts.
Pour into greased muffin tins and bake for approximately 15 minutes for large muffins and 8 to 10 minutes for smaller muffins. Sprinkle tops with powdered sugar while still warm.

title: pumpkin-gingercream pie
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients in a heavy saucepan.
Cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, 5 minutes; remove from heat. Sprinkle gelatin over cold water in a small bowl; let stand one minute.
Add gelatin mixture to egg yolk mixture, stirring until gelatin dissolves.
Stir in lemon extract and set aside to cool.

title: congealed salad
directions: Bring jello and pineapple to a boil; let cool. Add Cool Whip, buttermilk and nuts. Mix well. Place in 9 x 13-inch dish and refrigerate until congealed.

title: odell's apple cake
directions: Beat egg yolks (thick).
Gradually add sugar and continue beating.
Add boiling water and sifted dry ingredients.
Mix until smooth and add extract.
Fold in egg whites.
Spread batter in 10-inch iron skillet.
Slice apples thin and arrange in circular pattern on top of batter, pressing lightly.
Add topping.

title: cabbage and noodles
directions: Melt butter in large skillet, or cook bacon until crisp.
Saute onion until transparent.
Add cabbage and saute for 5 minutes or until tender-crisp.
Stir in caraway seed, salt and pepper. Meanwhile, cook noodles as directed on package.
Drain, stir into cabbage.
Add sour cream and cook another 5 minutes without boiling, stirring often.

title: carrot cake
directions: Combine sugar, oil and eggs; beat well.
Blend in flour and cinnamon.
Add carrots and nuts, mixing well.
Pour into a well-greased and lightly floured 10-inch tube pan or Bundt pan. Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until cake tests done.

title: pimento cheese spread
directions: Finely grate cheese into large bowl.
Drain pimento and chop and add to cheese.
Add mayonnaise (approximately 1/2 cup) and mix well.
Add additional mayonnaise to make spread desired consistency.
Add pepper to taste.

title: turtle cake
directions: Follow directions of cake mix on box.
Cover bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan with 1/2 batter.
Bake 10 minutes.
Let cool.

title: spaghetti casserole
directions: Combine noodles with butter, parmesan cheese and eggs.
Spoon into greased 9x13 pan.
Brown hamburger and onions, drain.
Spoon over noodles.
Top with sauce, cheese and pepperoni.
Cover with foil and bake at 350 for 30 minutes.
Remove foil and bake 10 more minutes.

title: 7 layer salad
directions: Combine the buttermilk with dressing mix.
Layer together in order given in a 9 x 13-inch glass casserole dish.
Make the day before use; store overnight in refrigerator.

title: peking roast
directions: Use knife to cut slits completely through meat like little tunnels.
Insert slivers of onion and garlic into slits.
Put beef in bowl with vinegar poured over it.
Refrigerate 24 to 48 hours, covered.
Throw away vinegar and put roast in a heavy pot and brown in oil until nearly burned on both sides.
Pour coffee over roast.
Add water and cover.
Simmer 6 hours and 20 minutes. Before serving, add salt and pepper for taste.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Spray baking dish with Pam.
Pour stuffing mix in dish.
Pour butter over mix.
Toss to wet mix.
Press on bottom and sides. Saute celery and onion.
Put chicken on top of stuffing mix.
Mix celery, onion, soup, sour cream and milk.
Pour over chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°, covered.

title: corn casserole
directions: Place in casserole and dot with 2 tablespoons butter.
Bake at 325° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: olive nut salad
directions: Mix an equal quantity of cream cheese with chopped olives. Roll into balls the size of a hickory nut.
Roll each in chopped nut meats.
Arrange 3 on a lettuce leaf for a portion and serve with French dressing.

title: fried okra
directions: Prepare okra.
Set aside.
Combine flour, salt and meal.
Add egg, milk and butter.
Mix good.
Coat okra in batter.
Deep fry in hot oil until golden brown.
Drain.
Salt to taste.

title: meatballs in sweet and sour sauce
directions: Combine all meatball ingredients in a medium mixing bowl and mix well.
Shape into 20 (1-inch) meatballs and place in glass baking dish.
Cover with wax paper.
Put in oven for 8 minutes on Roast.
Drain and let stand, covered, for 3 minutes.
During standing time, make Sweet and Sour Sauce.

title: deer stew
directions: Brown meat in skillet, then drain.
In crock-pot, add all ingredients together. Cook on low 6 to 8 hours.

title: caramel squares
directions: Put the 2 cups light brown sugar and margarine in an 11-inch skillet and melt completely.
When cool, add the two eggs, one at a time.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Cook at 400° for 15 minutes.

title: congealed salad
directions: Combine pineapple and sugar and bring to a boil.
Cool about 3 minutes.
Add gelatin.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cream cheese and cool.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Pour into 9-inch glass dish.
Chill until firm.
Serve over lettuce.

title: dutch oven potatoes
directions: Cook potatoes in skin; cool, peel, dice and salt to taste. Melt Velveeta.
Add green pepper (diced), 1 slice of bread (crumbled), parsley flakes and chopped onion.
Layer potatoes and cheese mixture before baking; pour melted butter and milk over top.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for about 1 hour or less.

title: pineapple rice casserole(italian rice & pineapple)
directions: Combine pineapple with juice, eggs, and sugar.
Fold into cooked rice.
Place in greased baking dish and dot with butter. Bake uncovered at 350 degrees for 1 1/4 hours, or until golden brown.
Serve warm the first day.
Serve warm or cold thereafter.

title: pistachio nut cake("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Mix first three dry ingredients together.
Next beat eggs and then add oil or combination and club soda.
Combine the liquids and mix well with the dry ingredients.
Take 1 cup of the batter and mix with chocolate syrup.
Add nuts to the other batter and pour into greased and floured tube pan.
Pour chocolate mixture on top. Bake 50 to 60 minutes at 350°.

title: salisbury steak
directions: Mix 1/4 cup soup, beef, bread crumbs, egg, onion and pepper. Shape firmly into 6 patties.
In skillet, brown patties and pour off fat.
Stir in remaining soup and water.
Cover and cook over low heat for 20 minutes or until done.
Stir occasionally.
For more gravy, add additional can of soup.

title: classic quiche
directions: Heat oven to 425°. Prepare crust. Unfold pastry circle according to package directions. Fit into 9-inch fluted tart pan with removable bottom. Press crust firmly over bottom and sides. Trim away excess. Prick bottom with fork. Bake empty for 8 minutes. Maintain oven temperature.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream as for cake and bake in unbaked pie crust for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: risotto milanese(rice)
directions: Saute onions in butter until soft and transparent.
Stir in rice, stirring until golden brown.
Add chicken broth and bring to a boil.
Add Marsala or vermouth, salt and pepper.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 18 minutes.
Add mushrooms and cheese.

title: nacho dip
directions: Brown meat, green pepper and onion together.
Drain excess grease.
Add tomatoes.
Divide meat in 3 portions.
Layer bottom of casserole dish with meat mixture. Sprinkle with chili powder, salt and pepper.
Layer with 1/3 of cheese.
Repeat layering 2 more times.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Let stand for 5 minutes before serving. Garnish with black olives and green olives (chopped).

title: jimmy casey's cheese spread
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Put them in a bowl and mix with a spoon until well blended.
Refrigerate until the spread firms up enough so that it can be easily spread on a cracker.
Serve with crackers or French bread.
Tightly cover leftover and refrigerate for another time.

title: quiche lorraine
directions: Brown pie shell 10 minutes after having pierced bottom with fork.
Use hand mixer at low speed to blend eggs, milk, mayonnaise and flour.
Dice cheese and mix in with fork.
Cook bacon and drain on paper towels.
Saute onion and mushrooms in bacon fat. Add cooked spinach, crumbled bacon, onion and mushrooms to quiche mixture.
Mix with fork.
Pour into shell.
Bake for 45 to 60 minutes in 350° oven.
