Cool slightly before serving.

title: mexican casserole
directions: Brown hamburger meat and onion.
Drain really well.
Put back on the fire and add chili powder, salt, pepper and tomato sauce. Remove from heat.
Add beans and rice.
Put in a casserole dish and cover with cheese.
Put in a 350° oven just long enough to melt the cheese.
Serve with crackers or chips.

title: savory sloppy joes
directions: Brown meat; stir in barbecue sauce, green peppers and onion; cover and cook for 15 minutes.
Put meat on bun and serve.

title: monkey bread
directions: Grease Bundt pan. Cut biscuits into fourths. Mix sugar and cinnamon in a plastic bag.
Put several pieces of cut biscuit into the bag of sugar and cinnamon mixture and shake (a few at a time). Arrange biscuits in pan.
Pour butter and remaining sugar mixture over biscuits.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix up 3 egg whites with sugar (use mixer).
Add to this mix 3 egg yolks and flour; mix for 10 minutes.
Peel apples and cut into large pieces; add to mix.
Stir gently.
Put oven on 330° and put it in for 45 minutes.

title: green mountain salad
directions: Drain juice from fruit cocktail and pineapple to make 1 cup. Set back and put fruit in refrigerator.
Cut marshmallows and cream cheese in large mixing bowl.
Add jello and cup of hot water; mix thoroughly on low speed or with rotary beater; add 1 cup of juice.
Place in freezer part of refrigerator until thickened.

title: eggplant dirty rice
directions: Brown beef, sausage and chicken liver.
Fry eggplant.
Saute onion, garlic, pepper and celery.
Cook rice.
Mix together.

title: ugly duckling cake
directions: Mix cake mix, fruit cocktail, 1 cup coconut and eggs.
Then beat 2 minutes.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Bake at 425° for 45 minutes or until cake springs back to touch in saucepan.
Melt butter; add sugar and milk bring to a boil and cook 2 minutes.
Remove and add coconut.
Mix and ice hot cake.
Served warm; cool with whipped topping.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients well.
Add eggs and peanut butter. Mix well.
Place in unbaked pie shell.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°. Reduce oven to 350°; bake 30 to 40 minutes.

title: strawberry pizza
directions: Mix cream cheese and
sugar.
Fold in Cool Whip. Spread equally on crust. Top with sliced strawberries.

title: peanut butter eggs
directions: Mix well.
Form into egg shapes and dip in chocolate.

title: hot grits
directions: Cook grits according to package directions in 8 cups of water. Mix in other ingredients.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.
Serves 14.
Can be cut in half.
To cut cholesterol, use Egg Beaters.

title: beef balls
directions: Mix all ingredients; shape in ball.
Roll in pecans.
You can omit pecans.
Serve with crackers.

title: coconut cake
directions: Bake cake in a long, flat pan.
When cake is done, cool and punch holes in cake.
Pour coconut oil over cake.
Top with Cool Whip and sprinkle with coconut.
Keep refrigerated.

title: hickory nut cake
directions: Sift flour, sugar, baking powder and salt together in bowl. Add shortening, 2/3 cup milk and flavoring; beat two minutes.
Add remaining milk and unbeaten egg whites and nuts.
Pour into two generously floured 9-inch round cake pans.
Bake at 350` for 35 minutes.

title: easy time holiday squares
directions: Gradually add sugar to butter, creaming until light and fluffy. At medium speed, add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each. At low speed, add flour and lemon extract.

Pour batter into well greased 10 x 15 x 1-inch jelly roll pan. (I use large cookie sheet.) Mark off (with knife) 24 squares. Place 1 teaspoon pie filling in center of each square. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes. While warm, sift confectioners sugar over cake. Cool; cut in squares. (May substitute any flavor pie filling.)

title: sloppy joe burgers
directions: Brown hamburger and keep warm.
Mix sauce and add vegetables. Cook until warm and pour over warm drained meat.
Heat all this through and spread over hamburger buns.
Serves 25.

title: orange salad dessert
directions: Empty cottage cheese into a bowl.
Sprinkle jello over mixture.
Drain oranges and pineapple.
Add the fruit to the jello mixture.
Chill.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Refrigerate well.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Separate crescent roll dough into rectangles.
Place rectangles in ungreased jelly roll pan, sealing perforations to form a solid sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Cool completely.
Combine mayonnaise, cream cheese and dry dressing mix with mixer.
Spread evenly over cooled crust.
Sprinkle with cheese and veggies.
Cut into squares to serve.
Keep refrigerated.

title: red devil's food cake
directions: Sift flour once; measure.
Add soda and salt and sift together three times.
Cream butter and sugar.
Cream well and add egg. Beat well and add chocolate.
Add flour alternately with milk a small amount at a time.
Add vanilla; bake in greased pan, 8 x 8 x 2-inches, in moderate oven (325°) for 1 hour or until done.
Cake may be baked in two 8-inch layer pans in moderate oven (350°) for 30 minutes.

title: reuben casserole
directions: Crumble beef and place in buttered 2-quart casserole.
Spread on dressing. Drain sauerkraut and spread on top of beef. Add grated cheese. Top with bread cubes that have been tossed with butter. Bake, uncovered, 30 minutes at 350° until hot and bubbly.

title: raspberry punch
directions: Mix Kool-Aid
and juices and keep cool.
Place in punch bowl just
before
serving
and add ginger ale.
Float sherbet last. Serves 35 to 40.

title: sondra's chop suey
directions: Dice meats and boil until pink is gone; drain.
Add celery, onion, soy sauce and syrup.
Mix beef bouillon cubes in 1 cup water and dissolve.
Pour over meat mixture.
Cook until meat is tender.
Add drained bean sprouts; toss and cook 2 minutes.
Turn off and add noodles.

title: chocolate waffles
directions: Preheat lightly greased waffle iron.

title: butterscotch cookies
directions: Melt butterscotch chips and peanut butter together in a pan over hot (not boiling) water.
Stir to blend, then pour over corn flakes which have been placed in a large bowl.
Mix gently and well with two forks.
Drop by teaspoonful on wax paper.
Makes 4 dozen cookies.

title: onion pie
directions: Beat together egg, flour, sour cream and salt.
Add onions and cheese.
Mix with spoon.
Pour into pie shell and bake for 30 to 45 minutes at 325°.
Done when center of pie is set.

title: fourth of july potato salad
directions: Boil potatoes until fork tender; drain them and cut into bite size pieces.
Put them in a large bowl.
Fry the bacon crisp and reserve.
Pour out all but about 3 tablespoons of the bacon fat and saute the shallots in the fat very slowly until soft.
Pour the shallots and the bacon fat over the hot potatoes.
Add the oil, vinegar, parsley, onion, celery and crumbled bacon.
Toss very gently, but thoroughly.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serve at room temperature.
Cover and refrigerate leftovers.
Serves 8. Great for summer barbecues!

title: congo cookies
directions: Cream sugar and shortening. Mix dry ingredients. Add egg, one at a time.
Add dry ingredients, nuts, vanilla and chocolate bits. Bake in a greased pan at 350° for 15 or 20 minutes. Cut in squares.

title: bread pudding
directions: Combine egg, milk, sweetener and vanilla in small baking dish. Break up bread into egg mixture.
Sprinkle nutmeg on top.
Stand baking dish in pie pan with water around it.
Bake at 325° until knife stuck in center comes out clean.
Recipe equals whole breakfast.
(Could also count toward lunch protein.)

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Peel potatoes; slice medium thin and cook until tender.
Drain water.
Put potatoes in a baking dish.
Melt butter on medium heat; add flour until smooth.
Add salt and milk, stirring constantly, until thickened.
Add 3/4 cup cheese to sauce.
Pour over potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in dish for 1 hour at 375°.

title: cheese dip
directions: Melt in top of double boiler.
Stir well.

title: gooseberry pie
directions: Mix together berries, tapioca, sugar, salt, orange peel and butter.
Let stand for 215 minutes.
Pour into pastry shell. Cover with top crust and slit to vent.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes.
Reduce the temperature to 350° and bake for 30 minutes.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: In a large kettle, cover whole chicken with water (no need to cut up but remove gizzards, etc.).
Add half stalk of celery, cut into 4-inch lengths.
Bring to boil.
Cover; reduce heat and simmer until chicken is done (it will fall off the bone when done (about 30 to 45 minutes, depending on size).
Remove chicken to platter, leaving broth in kettle.
Let chicken cool some.
Remove skin and discard.
Pull chicken off bones; cut into bite-sized pieces.
Discard bones.
Set chicken aside.
While chicken is cooling, begin chopping vegetables.
After chicken is deboned, melt butter/margarine in large skillet.
Add vegetables, 1/2 cup at a time.
Saute until just tender.
Stir often.
While vegetables are cooling, reheat chicken stock to a boil to cook spaghetti in.
Add more water, if necessary.
Grate Velveeta cheese.
Set aside.
Cook spaghetti per package directions and drain.
Reserve stock water.
Mix cooked spaghetti, cooked vegetables and butter they were cooked in, chicken pieces and grated cheese.
Season and mix well.

title: carrot salad
directions: Peel and grate carrots.
Mix with raisins, pineapple, celery, mayonnaise and sugar.
Cover and store in refrigerator.
This will keep a week or more.

title: banana bread
directions: Sift flour, soda and salt together.
Cream shortening and sugar thoroughly.
Add eggs and bananas, beating until light. Alternately add flour mixture and milk.
Beat after each addition until smooth; add nuts.
Pour batter into greased 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Bake in moderate oven at 350° for 1 hour 5 minutes or until done.
Remove pan; cool on rack.
Wrap in foil or plastic wrap and store overnight before slicing.
Yields 1 loaf.

title: hamburger supreme
directions: Combine hamburger, onions, salt, pepper and eggs.
Mix well and shape into patties 1/2-inch thick.
Roll in flour and brown on both sides in hot salad oil.
Remove patties when brown.
Pour off all but 3 or 4 tablespoons fat.
Add flour, salt and pepper; mix well.
Add milk and mushroom soup and stir until thick.
Return patties to pan and cook 15 minutes longer or place in casserole and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: cherry dreams
directions: Make your graham cracker crumbs and mix with margarine.
Press more than half into a 9 x 13-inch pan, saving rest for topping. Cream sugar and cheese; whip Dream Whip with milk until it peaks. Whip together the cream cheese mixture and Dream Whip.
Add the cheese mixture, just half of it.
Then layer with 2 cans of cherry pie filling, then rest of cheese mixture, then sprinkle rest of crumbs on top.
Refrigerate overnight.

title: cinnamon puffs
directions: Dissolve yeast in 1/4 cup milk, cooled.
Pour 1 cup hot milk over oatmeal, butter, sugar and salt.
Mix eggs, yeast and 2 cups flour and mix.
Add 1 cup flour, more or less.
Don't make it too stiff.
Let rise 1 hour; knead down.
Let rest for 15 to 20 minutes.
Form into large ball.
Divide into quarters; divide quarters into 8 pieces.
Form into balls and put on cookie sheet. Let rise until double.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes.
Melt 1 cup butter.
Roll balls in melted margarine and in mixture of 1 cup sugar to 2 teaspoons cinnamon.
Roll in mixture while still warm.

title: german sweet chocolate cake
directions: Melt chocolate in boiling water.
Cool.
Sift flour with soda and salt.
Cream butter.
Gradually beat in sugar and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg yolks, one at a time, beating after each.
Blend in vanilla and chocolate; mix until blended.
Add flour mixture alternately with buttermilk, beating after each addition until smooth.
Fold in egg whites.

title: hot fudge sauce
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in heavy saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly.
Stir in salt and sweetened condensed milk. Cook for 5 minutes or until slightly thickened, stirring constantly.
Blend in vanilla.
Serve warm or cold over ice cream. Yield: 1 1/2 cups.

title: homemade stew
directions: Brown meat.
Add all ingredients; place in crock-pot.
Cook all until tender.
If desired, you can thicken with cornstarch.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute onions in margarine.
Cook broccoli according to package directions and drain.

title: deviled ham puff
directions: Grease a shallow baking dish or 2-quart casserole well.
Blend the Tabasco and Worcestershire sauce with the deviled ham and spread evenly on each slice of bread.
Cut the bread into 1-inch squares.
Place one layer on bottom of baking dish and sprinkle with 1/2 the cheese.
Place remaining bread squares on top of cheese and sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Blend eggs, milk, pimento, salt and pepper.
Pour over layers of bread and cheese. Let stand for about 15 minutes.
Bake in a 350° oven until puffed and brown (about 30 minutes).
Serve at once.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Place deboned chicken into baking dish.
Heat soups and sour cream until blended and pour over chicken.
Sprinkle top with Pepperidge Farm stuffing and pour 2 cups broth plus 1 stick melted butter over stuffing.
Bake at 250° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: pepper steak
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch cubes.
Saute steak cubes, bell pepper and onion in 2 tablespoons of corn oil until slightly brown.
Add soy sauce and cover with hot water.
Add salt and pepper.
Cover and cook slowly for 2 hours or until steak is tender.
Serve over chow mein noodles or rice.

title: candy bar brownies
directions: Combine, stir well.
Add 1 cup sifted unbleached flour.
Add 6 1.4 ounce Heath or Skor Candy Bars chipped coarsely, 1 cup chopped pecans toasted for 10 minutes at 350°.
Bake 25 - 30 minutes in 8 inch pan.
Cool completely before cutting.

title: meat loaf
directions: Form first 7 ingredients into loaf pan.
Then mix the rest of the ingredients.
Mix well and pour over meat loaf.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: ruth's biscuit ring
directions: In Bundt pan, pour 1/2 butter. Sprinkle poppy seeds. Stand up biscuits in pan. Pour remaining butter over tops. Bake 15 to 20 minutes according to temperature on can. Remove from pan.

title: knox blocks finger jello
directions: In a large bowl, combine Knox and flavored gelatins.
Add boiling water and stir until gelatines are dissolved.
Pour into large shallow baking pan (13 x 9-inch) and chill until firm.
Cut into squares to serve.
Makes about 100 (1-inch) squares.

title: baked beans
directions: Mix pork and beans in a large casserole dish with catsup, onions, sugar and syrup.
Add A.1. sauce, Worcestershire sauce, mustard and liquid smoke; stir.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Place strips of bacon over the top of casserole to cover.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: onion casserole
directions: Slice onions into rings; saute in oil.
Add salt, pepper and sugar.
Add chicken broth. Simmer 3 minutes.
Place in casserole dish and sprinkle with cheese and cracker crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
This dish is good served with pinto beans and beef patties and hush puppies.

title: lois' chili
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and garlic.
Drain fat.
Add other ingredients.
Simmer until thickened.
Best if made a day ahead.

title: recipe for 1-2-3-4 batter
directions: Add first 4 ingredients. Add soda to buttermilk. Add this to other ingredients and mix well.

title: crispy chicken nuggets
directions: Cut each chicken breast into 3 pieces.
Put flour, cornflake crumbs, salt and pepper in a large Baggie.
Rinse chicken in water and shake off excess.
Drop chicken pieces in Baggie and shake to coat.
Leave chicken sitting in flour mixture for 10 minutes.
Mix eggs, milk, salt and pepper.
Remove chicken from Baggie and dip into egg mixture.
Let chicken sit in egg mixture for 10 minutes. Again, dip chicken in flour mixture and deep fry in hot oil for approximately 8 minutes until golden brown.
Serve with barbecue sauce or sweet and sour sauce.

title: primavera with a twist
directions: Cook pasta according to package directions and drain.
Cook asparagus according to package directions; drain.
In 2 1/2-quart casserole, combine pasta, asparagus, red pepper and ham.
In medium saucepan, melt butter.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute. Gradually add milk, broth and dill; stir until mixture boils and thickens.
Add to casserole and mix well.
Cover and bake in a preheated 350° oven for 30 minutes, until bubbly or microwave on High for 8 to 10 minutes, stirring after 4 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1/2 cup margarine and add to graham cracker crumbs; mix well and pat in a 13 x 9 1/2 x 2-inch pan.
Combine sugar, eggs, 1/2 cup softened margarine and vanilla; beat until smooth.
Spread over graham cracker crust.
Add a layer of banana slices and spread pineapple on top of bananas.
Spread whipped topping evenly over pineapple.
Sprinkle with nuts and cherries.

title: cabbage soup
directions: Melt butter or margarine in large soup kettle and cook cabbage and onions for about 15 minutes, stirring to keep from sticking. Sprinkle with flour and mix well. Gradually add water, while stirring; heat until mixture reaches boiling point. Add all other ingredients and simmer over low heat for about 1 hour.

title: chicken and rice
directions: In a 2-quart baking dish, mix soup, water, rice and spices. Place chicken on rice mixture. Cover and bake at 375° for 45 minutes.

title: golden raisin buns
directions: Combine water, butter, sugar and salt in a saucepan; bring to a boil.
Add flour all at once, then over low heat, beat with a wooden spoon about 1 minute or until mixture leaves sides of pan and forms a smooth, thick dough.
(Yes, this uses only 1 teaspoon of sugar!)
Remove from heat.
Continue beating about 2 minutes to cool slightly.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating after each until mixture has a satiny sheen.
Stir in raisins.
Drop heaping measuring tablespoonfuls about 2 inches apart on greased baking sheets.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes or until golden, firm and doubled, at 375°.
Remove to wire rack to cool slightly.
While still warm, gently spread frosting over tops and sides.
Makes 20.
(Do not overbake!)

title: baked salmon with onions
directions: Pour 1/2 cup warm water over raisins; set aside to plump. Slice onions.
In large frying pan, heat oil over medium heat.
Add onions; cook until tender, about 20 minutes.
Drain raisins and add to onions with vinegar and zests.
Cook 1 minute.
Add 1 teaspoon salt and 1/2 teaspoon pepper.
Sprinkle fish with salt and pepper. Spread onion mixture on top.
Bake until fish is cooked through, about 10 minutes.
Sprinkle with pine nuts just before serving.

title: lazy day cabbage rolls
directions: Cut cabbage in half.
Cut one-half into quarters and set aside.
The other half chop into small pieces.
Brown hamburger and onion lightly.
Drain.
Add rice, tomatoes, soup, water and chopped cabbage.
Mix well and pour into casserole.
Put cabbage wedges on top and cover.
Bake in a 350° oven until cabbage is tender.

title: sour cream fruit salad
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Refrigerate overnight. Yield: 8 to 10 servings.

title: carrot salad
directions: Mix together last 6 ingredients.
Pour over carrots, onion and green pepper and let stand 2 days before serving.
Will keep in refrigerator several days.

title: cheese and spinach puffs
directions: Combine spinach and onions (cook as directed and drain well). Combine eggs, cheeses, salad dressing, margarine, garlic powder and muffin mix.
Add spinach and onion mixture.
Chill.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Freeze.
As needed, bake at 350° for 12 minutes until light brown.

title: karo crazy crunch
directions: Mix corn and nuts on a cookie sheet.
Combine sugar, margarine and syrup in 1 1/2-quart saucepan.
Boil over medium heat, stirring until mixture turns light caramel color; remove from heat.
Stir in vanilla.
Beat 1 minute.

title: pineapple cheesecake
directions: Mix crust ingredients and line pie pan with the crumb crust and set aside.

title: pea salad
directions: In a large mixing bowl, add drained green peas, onion, celery and pimiento; stir slowly to mix.
Add pepper and salt to taste. Slowly add the salad dressing, vinegar and eggs.
Add sugar to taste.

title: cherry dessert
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Spread pie filling on bottom. Sprinkle the cake mix evenly on top.
Melt margarine and spoon over this.
Sprinkle on coconut and nuts.
Bake at 350°
for 40 minutes.

title: snowball cake
directions: Mix Jell-O in 4 tablespoons ice water.
Add one cup boiling water, salt and pineapple juice.
Set in refrigerator until it begins to thicken.
Put 2 packages of Dream Whip into mix.
Pinch cake into small bits.
Pour into Jell-O mix.
Spread pineapple on. (Nuts may be added, if you desire.)
Spread remaining Dream Whip on top, with coconut.

title: mallow fruit ambrosia
directions: Combine marshmallows, fruit and coconut; mix lightly.
Spoon into individual dessert dishes. Combine sour cream and honey; mix well.
Spoon over fruit.

title: french potato balls
directions: Mash potatoes with mayonnaise, mustard, garlic, parsley, chives, salt, pepper and sufficient flour to make firm dough. Roll into balls. Dip in egg mixture, then roll in bread crumbs. Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Deep fry in oil until brown.

title: crock-pot scalloped potatoes
directions: Layer potatoes, cheese, onions and ham in a crock-pot.
Add on can of mushroom soup on top.
Cook for 2 to 3 hours on high heat.

title: crock-pot pinto beans
directions: Soak pinto beans overnight in crock-pot.
Rinse one to two times with tap water.
Thoroughly cover beans with tap water.
Add cured ham slices.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Cook on low setting for twelve hours.

title: carrot cake
directions: Hand mix all of the above ingredients, except for confectioners sugar and milk.
Pour thick mixture into greased tube pan with removable bottom.
Bake in a 350° oven for 1 1/2 hours.
Remove from oven.
Mix enough milk with the confectioners sugar to make a glaze.
Glaze cake while hot.

title: wicked awesome crabmeat dip
directions: Mix all ingredients, except almonds.
Put in glass pie plate and cover with slivered almonds.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serve hot.

title: chicken salad italian
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Can use canned chicken.

title: eggnog pie
directions: Soften gelatin in cold water for 5 minutes.
Combine egg yolks, 1/4 cup sugar, nutmeg, salt and milk.
Cook in double boiler until thick, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat and add softened gelatin and fold in egg whites which have been beaten stiff with 1/4 cup sugar.
Add bourbon or bourbon flavoring to taste.
Fold in 1 cup of whipped cream.
Pour into shells and refrigerate until serving time.

title: tangy sweet-sour sauce
directions: Heat to blend flavors.
Serve at room temperature.
Keeps several weeks refrigerated.

title: broccoli cornbread
directions: Mix and pour into hot oiled skillet.
Bake at 350°.

title: barbecue sauce for chicken
directions: Combine all ingredients and let stand 1 hour to mingle flavors.
Extra good on chicken wings.

title: meat pie
directions: Brown meat in 4 tablespoons fat. Add onion, salt and pepper. When brown, combine with corn, spaghetti and tomato soup. Cover with crust and bake until crust is brown.

title: marinated carrots
directions: Cook carrots slightly, drain, cool and add onion and green pepper.
Make sauce.

title: banana fruit drink
directions: In blender pour orange juice and milk.
Peel banana.
Now mix (top on).
Stop.
Put in ice cubes and crush.
It will be loud, remember the top.
Now pour.
It is a refreshing summer drink.

title: potatoes and ham
directions: Spray casserole with Pam; cut up potatoes.
Add all ingredients, except crumbs.
Mix.
Top with crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: squash-walnut casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Spoon into 1-quart baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes or until heated thoroughly.
Can cover and refrigerate for 24 hours.
Use any kind of squash or combinations.
Good with sweet potatoes.

title: old-fashioned coleslaw
directions: Place mayonnaise, sugar, vinegar, celery seeds, mustard, and salt in a large bowl.
Whisk until blended.
Stir in cabbage, carrots, onion, and green pepper until all ingredients are well coated.
Cover and chill until ready to serve.

title: amish sugar cookies
directions: Combine sugars, margarine and oil.
Beat well; add eggs and beat again.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop small balls of dough on ungreased cookie sheet and flatten with a fork or dip bottom of a glass dipped in sugar and flatten.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 15 minutes.
You may use nuts, raisins or chocolate chips.
These are very easy cookies and fun to make.

title: chinese fried rice with hamburger
directions: Crumble meat in heavy skillet with oil and onion.
Stir-fry until meat is nicely browned.
Pour off oil.
Add fried rice, mixing thoroughly with beef.
Add water and soy sauce.
Stir and cover.
Cook over low heat for 5 minutes.

title: cajun seafood gumbo soup
directions: Use iron skillet.
Heat oil until it begins to smoke.
(If oil is not hot enough, flour will lump; if too hot, it will burn.) Slowly add flour, stirring constantly, until it is dark brown (for a couple of minutes).

title: toll house pie
directions: Beat eggs at high speed until foamy.
Beat in flour, sugar and butter.
Blend in chocolate chips and walnuts.
Pour in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 325° for 55 to 60 minutes.
Makes 2 pies.

title: buttermilk cake
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy.
Add sugar slowly beating it in.
Sift dry ingredients together 2 or 3 times, then add alternately with buttermilk to the first mixture.
Add vanilla and lemon extract.
Bake in tube pan about 45 minutes at 350°.
May be eaten with or without frosting.

title: old fashioned tea cakes
directions: Cream shortening and sugar together.
Beat in eggs.
Add salt and flavoring.
Stir in enough flour to make a medium stiff dough. Roll out on floured board.
Cut with cookie cutter.
Bake in a 350° oven until lightly browned.

title: sugarless diet cookies
directions: Beat diet margarine, egg and vanilla until fluffy. Stir together flour, baking soda, cinnamon and salt, if using. Beat into egg mixture. Stir in fruit and nuts. Dough will be stiff. Drop batter by the teaspoonful
onto a nonstick cookie sheet which has been sprayed with cooking spray. Bake 10 to 12 minutes until golden brown.

title: pasta with broccoli and chicken
directions: Saute garlic and onion in olive oil until golden.
Add diced chicken and broccoli.
Mix bouillon cube with wine or water and add to chicken mixture.
Cook, covered, but with lid ajar (to keep the bright green color in the broccoli), for 3 minutes over medium heat.
Meanwhile, cook pasta and drain.
Add chicken mixture and top with Parmesan cheese.
Serves 4.

title: toledo bend casserole
directions: Flatten biscuits and put into a 9 x 12-inch casserole dish, covering the bottom of dish. Brown sausage until almost done. Spread on top of biscuit dough. Scramble egg until just a little bit runny; pour on top of sausage and top with cheese. Bake at 375° for about 30 minutes, or until the crust is brown.

title: tomato relish
directions: Grind or cut up tomatoes, onions and peppers.
Mix all ingredients and boil on low to medium heat until it is the exact consistency you prefer.

title: chicken cheese ball
directions: After you mix ingredients together, put in refrigerator and let it get cold so it will form a ball.
Then roll it in the pecans and serve with crackers.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and onions about 15 minutes.
Add small amount of water.
Cover and cook on low heat about 45 minutes. Add the tomato paste, catsup, chili powder, beans and salt to taste.
Add enough water to make about 1/2 gallon of chili and cook 30 minutes longer.

title: cardiac brownies
directions: Combine all ingredients (except nuts) with electric mixer. Fold in chopped nuts.
Spray an 8-inch square pan with nonstick spray.
Pour batter into pan.
Bake for 30 to 35 minutes at 350°. Each contains 165 calories.
Low-fat recipe.

title: ladyfinger cake
directions: Blend room temperature cream cheese with sugars and vanilla. Whip cream and blend into cream cheese mixture.
Line spring-form pan with ladyfingers.
Spoon half of the mixture on ladyfingers. Add a layer of ladyfingers on top of that and add remaining mixture.
Top with fruit of choice (blueberry or strawberry is recommended).
Refrigerate.

title: ladyfingers
directions: Cream butter and sugar; add vanilla and water, then flour and the nuts.
Make a little roll in the shape of your fingers.
Lay on cookie sheet and bake 18 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Roll in powdered sugar when they cool.
I roll mine in powdered sugar then lay them in a Tupperware container and put them in the refrigerator.
I also roll mine again when I lay them out to eat. Can be frozen real good.

title: chicken tetrazzini
directions: Prepare spaghetti as directed on box.
Boil chicken and cut into pieces to make 1 cup.
Mix soups and sour cream together.

title: impossible bacon pie
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease 10 1/2-inch pie plate.
Sprinkle bacon, cheese and onion in pie plate.
Beat remaining ingredients until smooth, 1 minute with hand beater.
Pour into pie plate. Bake until knife inserted comes out clean, 35 to 40 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes before serving.

title: summer salad
directions: Mix oil, vinegar, sugar and pepper together; set aside.
Boil chicken until done and cool.
Cut into small cubes.
Chop cabbage (not core) into 1-inch pieces.
Slice green onions small.
Break up Ramen noodles in small pieces (do not use seasoning packets and don't cook noodles).
Mix all in large bowl.
Pour oil mixture over all; toss well.
Refrigerate overnight.
When cabbage has wilted and noodles are soft, it is ready to eat.
Toss again before serving.

title: italian pot pie
directions: In large skillet, brown ground beef and onion. Drain. Stir in water, pepper, tomato sauce and tomato paste. Simmer for 15 minutes, stirring occasionally. Remove from heat. Stir in vegetables and 1 1/2 cups of cheese. Spoon mixture into a 12 x 8-inch baking dish. Cut biscuits in half and place near outer edge of hot meat mixture. Sprinkle remaining cheese in center. Brush biscuits with butter and sprinkle with oregano. Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until biscuits are brown.

title: dinner in a skillet
directions: Brown chops in small amount of shortening.
Add remaining ingredients.
Cover and cook on top of stove until chops are tender.

title: potatoes
directions: Mix hash browns, 1/4 pound melted butter, chicken soup, sour cream, onion and cheese in a large bowl.
Place in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with mixture of 1/4 pound melted butter and corn flakes, spreading on top.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: thumbprint cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Beat butter and sugar until creamy. Beat in egg yolks and vanilla.
In another bowl, stir together flour and salt.
Gradually add to butter mixture; blend thoroughly. In a small bowl, lightly beat egg whites.
Roll dough into 1-inch balls.
Dip ball into egg whites then roll in walnuts.
Push thumb in center and fill with jam.
Bake for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix the ingredients together and pour into a small aluminum loaf pan (3 1/2 x 6-inch) sprayed with Pam.
Bake at 325° for 40 minutes.
Cool on a cake rack and top with apple spice icing, if desired.

title: chicken dijon
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown onions and garlic in olive oil. Strain out onions and garlic; save.
In the same oil brown chicken breasts and cook until juice runs clear.
(You can cut chicken breasts in smaller pieces.)
Remove chicken; return onions and garlic.
Add chicken bouillon and Dijon mustard.
Cook until simmering.
Thicken with flour.
(Mix flour and a little water until smooth; then add.)
Return chicken and heat through.
Serve over favorite pasta.

title: oyster stew
directions: Mix together; bring to a boil.
Thicken, if desired.

title: congealed fruit salad
directions: Heat pineapple, stir jello into the pineapple and bring just to a boil.
Add buttermilk and Cool Whip.
Chill.
Will be ready to eat in an hour.

title: potato salad
directions: Combine potatoes, onions and eggs in a large bowl. Blend sour cream with remaining ingredients. Add to potato mixture, tossing gently to combine.
If desired, garnish with hard-cooked egg slices and radishes.
Cover and chill 4 to 6 hours.

title: pineapple buttermilk salad
directions: Combine sugar and pineapple in a saucepan and bring to a boil. Remove from heat and add Jell-O and stir to dissolve Jell-O. Cool.
Add buttermilk and pecans; stir until combined.
Fold in Cool Whip.
If desired, put in mold.

title: forgotten cookies
directions: Beat egg whites stiff, adding sugar and salt gradually.
Add vanilla.
Mix in chips and nuts.
Drop by spoonful on a foil lined cookie sheet.
Heat oven to 300°.
Put cookies in a heated oven and turn off heat.
Leave in oven overnight without opening oven.

title: slush punch
directions: Mix Jell-O, sugar and boiling water.
Add juices and cold water.
Put into small containers.
Freeze.
Unthaw a bit and put in with pop in punch bowl.

title: babka (without yeast)
directions: Combine sugar and margarine and mix well.
Add egg yolks, vanilla, lemon juice, flour and baking powder, beating continuously until well blended.
Bake in greased and floured 9-inch tube pan for 3/4 hour at 375°.

title: cranberry orange relish
directions: Put orange and cranberries through food chopper.
Add sugar and mix well.
Sprinkle gelatin on 1/2 cup of cranberry juice to soften.
Place over low heat and stir until gelatin is dissolved. Remove from heat and stir in remaining 1/2 cup cranberry juice and orange-cranberry mixture.
Turn into individual molds.
Chill until firm.

title: crunchy nappa salad
directions: Mix chopped onions and celery with cabbage.
In skillet, brown sesame seed, almonds and Ramen noodles.
Use low heat, stirring frequently.
(Best to put sesame seed in later, they brown faster.)
Sprinkle crunchy nut mixture over salad, toss, then add dressing.
Salt and pepper to taste.

title: cheese ball
directions: Mix well and place in round mold.
Refrigerate.
Unmold and cover with chutney.
Serve with crackers.

title: quick lasagna
directions: Saute meat; add Ragu and 1 cup water.
Simmer for awhile. Mix all other ingredients, except noodles.

title: minute steak rolls
directions: Sprinkle steaks with marjoram, garlic salt and pepper.
Cut butter into 4 sticks of equal size.
Place 1 stick of butter on each steak and roll ends over to completely cover butter; skewer to keep closed.
Broil over medium coals, turning often until steak is browned on outside, rare inside, about 10 to 12 minutes.

title: aunt carol's steak
directions: Place ingredients in a plastic bag, adding meat last.
Tie bag and marinate overnight.
Broil; cut in thin slices across the grain on an angle.
If you wish to use the marinade as a sauce, make fresh batch.
Do not use the marinade that has held the raw meat!

title: sweet hot mustard(i do mean hot)
directions: In a glass bowl, combine the vinegar and mustard; allow to stand overnight.
The next day, place the eggs in the top of a double boiler and beat slightly.
Add the sugar and beat smooth, then beat in the vinegar-mustard mixture.
Cook over simmering water until the mustard is thickened and begins to bubble in the middle.
Transfer to an electric mixer bowl and beat for 5 minutes; add the salt.
Pour into a 1-quart glass jar or 4 (8 ounce) jars and store in the refrigerator.
(Keeps indefinitely.)

title: peach cobbler
directions: Put butter in deep baking dish and set in 350° oven to melt. Make a batter of the sugar, flour, baking powder and salt.
Add milk and when mixed pour melted butter.
Do not stir.
Last, empty the can of peaches on top of batter.
Do not stir.
Bake one hour at 350°.
You may use apples, pears or cherries (I also use Lucky Leaf pie filling, 21 ounce can).

title: pasta supper(serves 6)
directions: Wash meat and pat dry with paper towels.
In a Dutch oven or heavy kettle, heat the oil, add beef chunks, onion, bell pepper, oregano and garlic.
Stir-fry over moderate heat until meat is brown.
Add salt, tomato sauce, achiote, olives, capers and bay leaf.
Mix and cook for 5 minutes.
Add water, bring to a rapid boil, cover and simmer over low heat for 30 minutes.
Add potatoes, stir to combine and bring to a rapid boil.
Cover and simmer for another 30 minutes.
Serve over white or yellow rice.

title: harvest rice
directions: Cook carrots in water until crisp-tender, about 5 minutes. Add apple juice, lemon juice, brown sugar and salt.
Bring to boil.
Stir in brown rice, cinnamon and raisins.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer until rice is tender and liquid is absorbed, about 45 minutes.
Gently stir in green onions an apples.
Heat through.
Turn into serving dish.
Top with sesame seed.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix pumpkin, sugar, mace, flour, ginger, nutmeg and salt together.
Beat eggs and add with canned milk.
Bake at 450° for 15 minutes, then turn down oven to 350° for 30 minutes.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix the instant pudding and milk until thick.
Fold in the sour cream and most of the Cool Whip.
In a 9 x 13-inch pan layer pudding, vanilla wafers and bananas.
Top with remainder of the Cool Whip.

title: caramel crunch squares
directions: Combine flour, oats and brown sugar.
Cut in butter until coarse crumbs.
Stir in nuts and pat into oblong pan and bake at 350° for about 15 minutes or until light brown.
Stir while mixture is still warm to form crumbs.
Cool.
Pat 1/2 of crumbs into 9-inch square pan.
Drizzle 1/2 of caramel topping over crumbs, then evenly spread with ice cream.	Top with remaining crumbs and drizzle remaining topping.
Freeze until firm.
Cut in squares.
Great for summer entertaining.

title: kirvin's tea room sweet potato pie
directions: Stir margarine into sweet potatoes.
Add sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well. Add remaining ingredients.
Mix thoroughly.
Pour into pie shells and bake at 350° for 1 hour. Makes two pies.

title: dutch honey
directions: Stir together and boil for 3 minutes.

title: strawberry freeze
directions: Blend cream cheese and sugar.
Add other ingredients.
Mix well, pour into casserole dish and cover tightly.
Place in freezer.
Take out about 15 minutes before serving.

title: chocolate sauce(for ice cream)
directions: Mix all ingredients together except vanilla. Bring to a full boil and boil for 10 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add vanilla. Stir and set aside until needed.
Store leftovers in refrigerator. Better if not doubled.

title: broccoli casserole
directions: Saute celery and onions (mushrooms optional) in salad oil. Add thawed broccoli; steam for 10 minutes.
Add soup, milk, water, cheese and uncooked rice.
Mix together in a 1 1/2-quart casserole dish.
Heat at 350° for 25 minutes.
